P_HTM[3112]="*vīriyaṃ karaṇīyaṃ … pe ….**arouse energy …*";
P_HTM[3113]="*(159–169.: 430–440.)**(159–169)*";
P_HTM[3114]="*“Jarāmaraṇaṃ, bhikkhave, ajānatā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3115]="*sātaccaṃ karaṇīyaṃ … pe ….**persist …*";
P_HTM[3116]="*(170–180.: 441–451.)**(170–180)*";
P_HTM[3117]="*“Jarāmaraṇaṃ, bhikkhave, ajānatā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3118]="*sati karaṇīyā … pe ….**be mindful …*";
P_HTM[3119]="*(181–191.: 452–462.)**(181–191)*";
P_HTM[3120]="*“Jarāmaraṇaṃ, bhikkhave, ajānatā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3121]="*sampajaññaṃ karaṇīyaṃ … pe ….**employ situational awareness …*";
P_HTM[3122]="*(192–202.: 463–473.)**(192–202)*";
P_HTM[3123]="*“Jarāmaraṇaṃ, bhikkhave, ajānatā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3124]="*appamādo karaṇīyo … pe ….**be diligent …”*";
P_HTM[3125]="*(203–213.: 474–484.)**(203–213)*";
P_HTM[3126]="*Antarapeyyālo navamo.* **";
P_HTM[3127]="*Satthā sikkhā ca yogo ca,* **";
P_HTM[3128]="*chando ussoḷhipañcamī;* **";
P_HTM[3129]="*Appaṭivāni yātappaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[3130]="*vīriyaṃ sātaccamuccati;* **";
P_HTM[3131]="*Sati ca sampajaññañca,* **";
P_HTM[3132]="*appamādena dvādasāti.* **";
P_HTM[3133]="*Suttantā antarapeyyālā niṭṭhitā.* **";
P_HTM[3134]="*Pare te dvādasa honti,* **";
P_HTM[3135]="*suttā dvattiṃsa satāni;* **";
P_HTM[3136]="*Catusaccena te vuttā,* **";
P_HTM[3137]="*peyyālaantaramhi yeti.* **";
P_HTM[3138]="*Antarapeyyālesu uddānaṃ samattaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3139]="*Nidānasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ.**The Linked Discourses on causality are complete.*";
P_HTM[3140]="*13. Abhisamayasaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[3141]="*1. Buddhavaggo**Comprehension*";
P_HTM[3142]="*1. Nakhasikhāsuttaṃ**A Fingernail*";
P_HTM[3143]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[3144]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[3145]="*Atha kho bhagavā parittaṃ nakhasikhāyaṃ paṃsuṃ āropetvā bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha, picking up a little bit of dirt under his fingernail, addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[3146]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**“What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[3147]="*katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ, yo vāyaṃ mayā paritto nakhasikhāyaṃ paṃsu āropito, ayaṃ vā mahāpathavī”ti?**Which is more: the little bit of dirt under my fingernail, or this great earth?”*";
P_HTM[3148]="*“Etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ, yadidaṃ mahāpathavī.**“Sir, the great earth is far more.*";
P_HTM[3149]="*Appamattako bhagavatā paritto nakhasikhāyaṃ paṃsu āropito.**The little bit of dirt under your fingernail is tiny.*";
P_HTM[3150]="*Neva satimaṃ kalaṃ upeti na sahassimaṃ kalaṃ upeti na satasahassimaṃ kalaṃ upeti mahāpathaviṃ upanidhāya bhagavatā paritto nakhasikhāyaṃ paṃsu āropito”ti.**Compared to the great earth, it’s not nearly a hundredth, a thousandth, or a hundred thousandth part.”*";
P_HTM[3151]="*“Evameva kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa diṭṭhisampannassa puggalassa abhisametāvino etadeva bahutaraṃ dukkhaṃ yadidaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ;**“In the same way, for a noble disciple accomplished in view, a person with comprehension, the suffering that’s over and done with is more,*";
P_HTM[3152]="*appamattakaṃ avasiṭṭhaṃ.**what’s left is tiny.*";
P_HTM[3153]="*Neva satimaṃ kalaṃ upeti na sahassimaṃ kalaṃ upeti na satasahassimaṃ kalaṃ upeti purimaṃ dukkhakkhandhaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ upanidhāya yadidaṃ sattakkhattuṃparamatā.**Compared to the mass of suffering in the past that’s over and done with, it’s not nearly a hundredth, a thousandth, or a hundred thousandth part, since there are at most seven more lives.*";
P_HTM[3154]="*Evaṃ mahatthiyo kho, bhikkhave, dhammābhisamayo;**That’s how very beneficial it is to comprehend the teaching*";
P_HTM[3155]="*evaṃ mahatthiyo dhammacakkhupaṭilābho”ti.**and gain the vision of the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[3156]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3157]="*2. Pokkharaṇīsuttaṃ**A Lotus Pond*";
P_HTM[3158]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3159]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, pokkharaṇī paññāsayojanāni āyāmena paññāsayojanāni vitthārena paññāsayojanāni ubbedhena, puṇṇā udakassa samatittikā kākapeyyā.**“Mendicants, suppose there was a lotus pond that was fifty leagues long, fifty leagues wide, and fifty leagues deep, full to the brim so a crow could drink from it.*";
P_HTM[3160]="*Tato puriso kusaggena udakaṃ uddhareyya.**Then a person would pick up some water on the tip of a blade of grass.*";
P_HTM[3161]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[3162]="*katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ, yaṃ vā kusaggena udakaṃ ubbhataṃ yaṃ vā pokkharaṇiyā udakan”ti?**Which is more: the water on the tip of the blade of grass, or the water in the lotus pond?”*";
P_HTM[3163]="*“Etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ, yadidaṃ pokkharaṇiyā udakaṃ.**“Sir, the water in the lotus pond is certainly more.*";
P_HTM[3164]="*Appamattakaṃ kusaggena udakaṃ ubbhataṃ.**The water on the tip of a blade of grass is tiny.*";
P_HTM[3165]="*Neva satimaṃ kalaṃ upeti na sahassimaṃ kalaṃ upeti na satasahassimaṃ kalaṃ upeti pokkharaṇiyā udakaṃ upanidhāya kusaggena udakaṃ ubbhatan”ti.**Compared to the water in the lotus pond, it’s not nearly a hundredth, a thousandth, or a hundred thousandth part.”*";
P_HTM[3166]="*“Evameva kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa diṭṭhisampannassa puggalassa abhisametāvino etadeva bahutaraṃ dukkhaṃ yadidaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ; appamattakaṃ avasiṭṭhaṃ.**“In the same way, for a person with comprehension, a noble disciple accomplished in view, the suffering that’s over and done with is more, what’s left is tiny.*";
P_HTM[3167]="*Neva satimaṃ kalaṃ upeti na sahassimaṃ kalaṃ upeti na satasahassimaṃ kalaṃ upeti purimaṃ dukkhakkhandhaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ upanidhāya, yadidaṃ sattakkhattuṃparamatā.**Compared to the mass of suffering in the past that’s over and done with, it’s not nearly a hundredth, a thousandth, or a hundred thousandth part, since there are at most seven more lives.*";
P_HTM[3168]="*Evaṃ mahatthiyo kho, bhikkhave, dhammābhisamayo; evaṃ mahatthiyo dhammacakkhupaṭilābho”ti.**That’s how very beneficial it is to comprehend the teaching and gain the vision of the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[3169]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3170]="*3. Sambhejjaudakasuttaṃ**Where the Waters Flow Together*";
P_HTM[3171]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3172]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yatthimā mahānadiyo saṃsandanti samenti, seyyathidaṃ—**“Mendicants, there are places where the great rivers—the Ganges, Yamuna, Aciravatī, Sarabhū, and Mahī—come together and converge.*";
P_HTM[3173]="*gaṅgā yamunā aciravatī sarabhū mahī, tato puriso dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni uddhareyya.**Suppose a person was to draw two or three drops of water from such a place.*";
P_HTM[3174]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[3175]="*katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ, yāni vā dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni ubbhatāni yaṃ vā sambhejjaudakan”ti?**Which is more: the two or three drops drawn out or the water in the confluence?”*";
P_HTM[3176]="*“Etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ yadidaṃ sambhejjaudakaṃ;**“Sir, the water in the confluence is certainly more.*";
P_HTM[3177]="*appamattakāni dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni ubbhatāni.**The two or three drops drawn out are tiny.*";
P_HTM[3178]="*Neva satimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na sahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na satasahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti sambhejjaudakaṃ upanidhāya dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni ubbhatānī”ti.**Compared to the water in the confluence, it’s not nearly a hundredth, a thousandth, or a hundred thousandth part.”*";
P_HTM[3179]="*“Evameva kho, bhikkhave … pe …**“In the same way, for a noble disciple, the suffering that’s over and done with is more …”*";
P_HTM[3180]="*dhammacakkhupaṭilābho”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3181]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3182]="*4. Dutiyasambhejjaudakasuttaṃ**Where the Waters Flow Together (2nd)*";
P_HTM[3183]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3184]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yatthimā mahānadiyo saṃsandanti samenti, seyyathidaṃ—**“Mendicants, there are places where the great rivers—the Ganges, Yamuna, Aciravatī, Sarabhū, and Mahī—come together and converge.*";
P_HTM[3185]="*gaṅgā yamunā aciravatī sarabhū mahī, taṃ udakaṃ parikkhayaṃ pariyādānaṃ gaccheyya ṭhapetvā dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni.**Suppose that water dried up and evaporated except for two or three drops.*";
P_HTM[3186]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[3187]="*katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ, yaṃ vā sambhejjaudakaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ yāni vā dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni avasiṭṭhānī”ti?**Which is more: the water in the confluence that has dried up and evaporated, or the two or three drops left?”*";
P_HTM[3188]="*“Etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ sambhejjaudakaṃ yadidaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ;**“Sir, the water in the confluence that has dried up and evaporated is certainly more.*";
P_HTM[3189]="*appamattakāni dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni avasiṭṭhāni.**The two or three drops left are tiny.*";
P_HTM[3190]="*Neva satimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na sahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na satasahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti sambhejjaudakaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ upanidhāya dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni avasiṭṭhānī”ti.**Compared to the water in the confluence that has dried up and evaporated, it’s not nearly a hundredth, a thousandth, or a hundred thousandth part.”*";
P_HTM[3191]="*“Evameva kho, bhikkhave … pe …**“In the same way, for a noble disciple, the suffering that’s over and done with is more …”*";
P_HTM[3192]="*dhammacakkhupaṭilābho”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3193]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3194]="*5. Pathavīsuttaṃ**The Earth*";
P_HTM[3195]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3196]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso mahāpathaviyā satta kolaṭṭhimattiyo guḷikā upanikkhipeyya.**“Mendicants, suppose a person was to place seven clay balls the size of jujube seeds on the great earth.*";
P_HTM[3197]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[3198]="*katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ, yā vā satta kolaṭṭhimattiyo guḷikā upanikkhittā yā vā mahāpathavī”ti?**Which is more: the seven clay balls the size of jujube seeds, or the great earth?”*";
P_HTM[3199]="*“Etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ, yadidaṃ mahāpathavī;**“Sir, the great earth is certainly more.*";
P_HTM[3200]="*appamattikā satta kolaṭṭhimattiyo guḷikā upanikkhittā.**The seven clay balls the size of jujube seeds are tiny.*";
P_HTM[3201]="*Neva satimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na sahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na satasahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti mahāpathaviṃ upanidhāya satta kolaṭṭhimattiyo guḷikā upanikkhittā”ti.**Compared to the great earth, it’s not nearly a hundredth, a thousandth, or a hundred thousandth part.”*";
P_HTM[3202]="*“Evameva kho, bhikkhave … pe …**“In the same way, for a noble disciple, the suffering that’s over and done with is more …”*";
P_HTM[3203]="*dhammacakkhupaṭilābho”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3204]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3205]="*6. Dutiyapathavīsuttaṃ**The Earth (2nd)*";
P_HTM[3206]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3207]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, mahāpathavī parikkhayaṃ pariyādānaṃ gaccheyya, ṭhapetvā satta kolaṭṭhimattiyo guḷikā.**“Mendicants, suppose the great earth was worn away and eroded except for seven clay balls the size of jujube seeds.*";
P_HTM[3208]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[3209]="*katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ, yaṃ vā mahāpathaviyā parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ yā vā satta kolaṭṭhimattiyo guḷikā avasiṭṭhā”ti?**Which is more: the great earth that has been worn away and eroded, or the seven clay balls the size of jujube seeds that are left?”*";
P_HTM[3210]="*“Etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ, mahāpathaviyā, yadidaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ;**“Sir, the great earth that has been worn away and eroded is certainly more.*";
P_HTM[3211]="*appamattikā satta kolaṭṭhimattiyo guḷikā avasiṭṭhā.**The seven clay balls the size of jujube seeds are tiny.*";
P_HTM[3212]="*Neva satimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na sahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na satasahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti mahāpathaviyā parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ upanidhāya satta kolaṭṭhimattiyo guḷikā avasiṭṭhā”ti.**Compared to the great earth that has been worn away and eroded, it’s not nearly a hundredth, a thousandth, or a hundred thousandth part.”*";
P_HTM[3213]="*“Evameva kho, bhikkhave … pe …**“In the same way, for a noble disciple, the suffering that’s over and done with is more …”*";
P_HTM[3214]="*dhammacakkhupaṭilābho”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3215]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3216]="*7. Samuddasuttaṃ**The Ocean*";
P_HTM[3217]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3218]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso mahāsamuddato dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni uddhareyya.**“Mendicants, suppose a man was to draw up two or three drops of water from the ocean.*";
P_HTM[3219]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[3220]="*katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ, yāni vā dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni ubbhatāni yaṃ vā mahāsamudde udakan”ti?**Which is more: the two or three drops drawn out or the water in the ocean?”*";
P_HTM[3221]="*“Etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ, yadidaṃ mahāsamudde udakaṃ;**“Sir, the water in the ocean is certainly more.*";
P_HTM[3222]="*appamattakāni dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni ubbhatāni.**The two or three drops drawn out are tiny.*";
P_HTM[3223]="*Neva satimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na sahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na satasahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti mahāsamudde udakaṃ upanidhāya dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni ubbhatānī”ti.**Compared to the water in the ocean, it’s not nearly a hundredth, a thousandth, or a hundred thousandth part.”*";
P_HTM[3224]="*“Evameva kho, bhikkhave … pe …**“In the same way, for a noble disciple, the suffering that’s over and done with is more …”*";
P_HTM[3225]="*dhammacakkhupaṭilābho”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3226]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3227]="*8. Dutiyasamuddasuttaṃ**The Ocean (2nd)*";
P_HTM[3228]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3229]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, mahāsamuddo parikkhayaṃ pariyādānaṃ gaccheyya, ṭhapetvā dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni.**“Mendicants, suppose the water in the ocean dried up and evaporated except for two or three drops.*";
P_HTM[3230]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[3231]="*katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ, yaṃ vā mahāsamudde udakaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ yāni vā dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni avasiṭṭhānī”ti?**Which is more: the water in the ocean that has dried up and evaporated, or the two or three drops left?”*";
P_HTM[3232]="*“Etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ mahāsamudde udakaṃ, yadidaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ;**“Sir, the water in the ocean that has dried up and evaporated is certainly more.*";
P_HTM[3233]="*appamattakāni dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni avasiṭṭhāni.**The two or three drops left are tiny.*";
P_HTM[3234]="*Neva satimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na sahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na satasahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti mahāsamudde udakaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ upanidhāya dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni avasiṭṭhānī”ti.**Compared to the water in the ocean that has dried up and evaporated, it’s not nearly a hundredth, a thousandth, or a hundred thousandth part.”*";
P_HTM[3235]="*“Evameva kho, bhikkhave … pe …**“In the same way, for a noble disciple, the suffering that’s over and done with is more …”*";
P_HTM[3236]="*dhammacakkhupaṭilābho”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3237]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3238]="*9. Pabbatasuttaṃ**A Mountain*";
P_HTM[3239]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3240]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso himavato pabbatarājassa satta sāsapamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā upanikkhipeyya.**“Mendicants, suppose a person was to place seven pebbles the size of mustard seeds on the Himalayas, the king of mountains.*";
P_HTM[3241]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[3242]="*katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ, yā vā satta sāsapamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā upanikkhittā yo vā himavā pabbatarājā”ti?**Which is more: the seven pebbles the size of mustard seeds, or the Himalayas, the king of mountains?”*";
P_HTM[3243]="*“Etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ yadidaṃ himavā pabbatarājā;**“Sir, the Himalayas, the king of mountains, is certainly more.*";
P_HTM[3244]="*appamattikā satta sāsapamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā upanikkhittā.**The seven pebbles the size of mustard seeds are tiny.*";
P_HTM[3245]="*Neva satimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na sahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na satasahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti himavantaṃ pabbatarājānaṃ upanidhāya satta sāsapamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā upanikkhittā”ti.**Compared to the Himalayas, it’s not nearly a hundredth, a thousandth, or a hundred thousandth part.”*";
P_HTM[3246]="*“Evameva kho … pe …**“In the same way, for a noble disciple, the suffering that’s over and done with is more …”*";
P_HTM[3247]="*dhammacakkhupaṭilābho”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3248]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3249]="*10. Dutiyapabbatasuttaṃ**A Mountain (2nd)*";
P_HTM[3250]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3251]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, himavā pabbatarājā parikkhayaṃ pariyādānaṃ gaccheyya, ṭhapetvā satta sāsapamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā.**“Mendicants, suppose the Himalayas, the king of mountains, was worn away and eroded except for seven pebbles the size of mustard seeds.*";
P_HTM[3252]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[3253]="*katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ, yaṃ vā himavato pabbatarājassa parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ yā vā satta sāsapamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā avasiṭṭhā”ti?**Which is more: the portion of the Himalayas, the king of mountains, that has been worn away and eroded, or the seven pebbles the size of mustard seeds that are left?”*";
P_HTM[3254]="*“Etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ himavato pabbatarājassa yadidaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ;**“Sir, the portion of the Himalayas, the king of mountains, that has been worn away and eroded is certainly more.*";
P_HTM[3255]="*appamattikā satta sāsapamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā avasiṭṭhā.**The seven pebbles the size of mustard seeds are tiny.*";
P_HTM[3256]="*Neva satimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na sahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na satasahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti himavato pabbatarājassa parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ upanidhāya satta sāsapamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā avasiṭṭhā”ti.**Compared to the Himalayas, it’s not nearly a hundredth, a thousandth, or a hundred thousandth part.”*";
P_HTM[3257]="*“Evameva kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa diṭṭhisampannassa puggalassa abhisametāvino etadeva bahutaraṃ dukkhaṃ yadidaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ;**“In the same way, for a noble disciple accomplished in view, a person with comprehension, the suffering that’s over and done with is more,*";
P_HTM[3258]="*appamattakaṃ avasiṭṭhaṃ.**what’s left is tiny.*";
P_HTM[3259]="*Neva satimaṃ kalaṃ upeti na sahassimaṃ kalaṃ upeti na satasahassimaṃ kalaṃ upeti purimaṃ dukkhakkhandhaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ upanidhāya yadidaṃ sattakkhattuṃparamatā.**Compared to the mass of suffering in the past that’s over and done with, it’s not nearly a hundredth, a thousandth, or a hundred thousandth part, since there are at most seven more lives.*";
P_HTM[3260]="*Evaṃ mahatthiyo kho, bhikkhave, dhammābhisamayo, evaṃ mahatthiyo dhammacakkhupaṭilābho”ti.**That’s how very beneficial it is to comprehend the teaching and gain the vision of the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[3261]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3262]="*11. Tatiyapabbatasuttaṃ**A Mountain (3rd)*";
P_HTM[3263]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3264]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso sinerussa pabbatarājassa satta muggamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā upanikkhipeyya.**“Mendicants, suppose a person was to place down on Sineru, the king of mountains, seven pebbles the size of mung beans.*";
P_HTM[3265]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[3266]="*katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ, yā vā satta muggamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā upanikkhittā yo vā sineru pabbatarājā”ti?**Which is more: the seven pebbles the size of mung beans, or Sineru, the king of mountains?”*";
P_HTM[3267]="*“Etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ yadidaṃ sineru pabbatarājā;**“Sir, Sineru, the king of mountains, is certainly more.*";
P_HTM[3268]="*appamattikā satta muggamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā upanikkhittā.**The seven pebbles the size of mung beans are tiny.*";
P_HTM[3269]="*Neva satimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na sahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na satasahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti sineruṃ pabbatarājānaṃ upanidhāya satta muggamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā upanikkhittā”ti.**Compared to Sineru, it’s not nearly a hundredth, a thousandth, or a hundred thousandth part.”*";
P_HTM[3270]="*“Evameva kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa diṭṭhisampannassa puggalassa adhigamaṃ upanidhāya aññatitthiyasamaṇabrāhmaṇaparibbājakānaṃ adhigamo neva satimaṃ kalaṃ upeti na sahassimaṃ kalaṃ upeti na satasahassimaṃ kalaṃ upeti.**“In the same way, compared with the achievements of a noble disciple accomplished in view, the achievements of the ascetics, brahmins, and wanderers who follow other paths is not nearly a hundredth, a thousandth, or a hundred thousandth part.*";
P_HTM[3271]="*Evaṃ mahādhigamo, bhikkhave, diṭṭhisampanno puggalo, evaṃ mahābhiñño”ti.**So great is the achievement of the person accomplished in view, so great is their direct knowledge.”*";
P_HTM[3272]="*Ekādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3273]="*Abhisamayasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ.**The Linked Discourses on comprehension are complete.*";
P_HTM[3274]="*Nakhasikhā pokkharaṇī,* **";
P_HTM[3275]="*sambhejjaudake ca dve;* **";
P_HTM[3276]="*Dve pathavī dve samuddā,* **";
P_HTM[3277]="*tayo ca pabbatūpamāti.* **";
P_HTM[3278]="*14. Dhātusaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[3279]="*1. Buddhavaggo**Diversity*";
P_HTM[3280]="*1. Dhātunānattasuttaṃ**Diversity of Elements*";
P_HTM[3281]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3282]="*“Dhātunānattaṃ vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the diversity of elements.*";
P_HTM[3283]="*Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[3284]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[3285]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[3286]="*“Katamañca, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ?**“And what is the diversity of elements?*";
P_HTM[3287]="*Cakkhudhātu rūpadhātu cakkhuviññāṇadhātu, sotadhātu saddadhātu sotaviññāṇadhātu, ghānadhātu gandhadhātu ghānaviññāṇadhātu, jivhādhātu rasadhātu jivhāviññāṇadhātu, kāyadhātu phoṭṭhabbadhātu kāyaviññāṇadhātu, manodhātu dhammadhātu manoviññāṇadhātu—**The eye element, sight element, and eye consciousness element. The ear element, sound element, and ear consciousness element. The nose element, smell element, and nose consciousness element. The tongue element, taste element, and tongue consciousness element. The body element, touch element, and body consciousness element. The mind element, thought element, and mind consciousness element.*";
P_HTM[3288]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhātunānattan”ti.**This is called the diversity of elements.”*";
P_HTM[3289]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3290]="*2. Phassanānattasuttaṃ**Diversity of Contacts*";
P_HTM[3291]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3292]="*“Dhātunānattaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ.**“Mendicants, diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of contacts.*";
P_HTM[3293]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ?**And what is the diversity of elements?*";
P_HTM[3294]="*Cakkhudhātu sotadhātu ghānadhātu jivhādhātu kāyadhātu manodhātu—**The eye element, ear element, nose element, tongue element, body element, and mind element.*";
P_HTM[3295]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ.**This is called the diversity of elements.*";
P_HTM[3296]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ?**And how does diversity of elements give rise to diversity of contacts?*";
P_HTM[3297]="*Cakkhudhātuṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati cakkhusamphasso.**The eye element gives rise to eye contact.*";
P_HTM[3298]="*Sotadhātuṃ paṭicca …**The ear element …*";
P_HTM[3299]="*ghānadhātuṃ paṭicca …**nose …*";
P_HTM[3300]="*jivhādhātuṃ paṭicca …**tongue …*";
P_HTM[3301]="*kāyadhātuṃ paṭicca …**body …*";
P_HTM[3302]="*manodhātuṃ paṭicca uppajjati manosamphasso.**The mind element gives rise to mind contact.*";
P_HTM[3303]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattan”ti.**That’s how diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of contacts.”*";
P_HTM[3304]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3305]="*3. Nophassanānattasuttaṃ**Not Diversity of Contacts*";
P_HTM[3306]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3307]="*“Dhātunānattaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ, no phassanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhātunānattaṃ.**“Mendicants, diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of contacts. Diversity of contacts doesn’t give rise to diversity of elements.*";
P_HTM[3308]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ?**And what is the diversity of elements?*";
P_HTM[3309]="*Cakkhudhātu … pe …**The eye element, ear element, nose element, tongue element, body element, and mind element.*";
P_HTM[3310]="*manodhātu—* **";
P_HTM[3311]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ.**This is called the diversity of elements.*";
P_HTM[3312]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ, no phassanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhātunānattaṃ?**And how does diversity of elements give rise to diversity of contacts, while diversity of contacts doesn’t give rise to diversity of elements?*";
P_HTM[3313]="*Cakkhudhātuṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati cakkhusamphasso, no cakkhusamphassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati cakkhudhātu … pe …**The eye element gives rise to eye contact. Eye contact doesn’t give rise to the eye element. …*";
P_HTM[3314]="*manodhātuṃ paṭicca uppajjati manosamphasso, no manosamphassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati manodhātu.**The mind element gives rise to mind contact. Mind contact doesn’t give rise to the mind element.*";
P_HTM[3315]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ, no phassanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhātunānattan”ti.**That’s how diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of contacts, while diversity of contacts doesn’t give rise to diversity of elements.”*";
P_HTM[3316]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3317]="*4. Vedanānānattasuttaṃ**Diversity of Feelings*";
P_HTM[3318]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3319]="*“Dhātunānattaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ, phassanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati vedanānānattaṃ.**“Mendicants, diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of contacts, and diversity of contacts gives rise to diversity of feelings.*";
P_HTM[3320]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ?**And what is the diversity of elements?*";
P_HTM[3321]="*Cakkhudhātu … pe … manodhātu—**The eye element, ear element, nose element, tongue element, body element, and mind element.*";
P_HTM[3322]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ.**This is called the diversity of elements.*";
P_HTM[3323]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ, phassanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati vedanānānattaṃ?**And how does diversity of elements give rise to diversity of contacts, and diversity of contacts gives rise to diversity of feelings?*";
P_HTM[3324]="*Cakkhudhātuṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati cakkhusamphasso, cakkhusamphassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati cakkhusamphassajā vedanā … pe …**The eye element gives rise to eye contact. Eye contact gives rise to the feeling born of eye contact. …*";
P_HTM[3325]="*manodhātuṃ paṭicca uppajjati manosamphasso, manosamphassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati manosamphassajā vedanā.**The mind element gives rise to mind contact. Mind contact gives rise to the feeling born of mind contact.*";
P_HTM[3326]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ, phassanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati vedanānānattan”ti.**That’s how diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of contacts, and diversity of contacts gives rise to diversity of feelings.”*";
P_HTM[3327]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3328]="*5. Dutiyavedanānānattasuttaṃ**Diversity of Feelings (2nd)*";
P_HTM[3329]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3330]="*“Dhātunānattaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ, phassanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati vedanānānattaṃ, no vedanānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ, no phassanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhātunānattaṃ.**“Mendicants, diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of contacts. Diversity of contacts gives rise to diversity of feelings. Diversity of feelings doesn’t give rise to diversity of contacts. Diversity of contacts doesn’t give rise to diversity of elements.*";
P_HTM[3331]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ?**And what is the diversity of elements?*";
P_HTM[3332]="*Cakkhudhātu … pe … manodhātu—**The eye element, ear element, nose element, tongue element, body element, and mind element.*";
P_HTM[3333]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ.**This is called the diversity of elements.*";
P_HTM[3334]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ, phassanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati vedanānānattaṃ, no vedanānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ, no phassanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhātunānattaṃ?**And how does diversity of elements give rise to diversity of contacts, and diversity of contacts give rise to diversity of feelings, while diversity of feelings doesn’t give rise to diversity of contacts, and diversity of contacts doesn’t give rise to diversity of elements?*";
P_HTM[3335]="*Cakkhudhātuṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati cakkhusamphasso, cakkhusamphassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati cakkhusamphassajā vedanā, no cakkhusamphassajaṃ vedanaṃ paṭicca uppajjati cakkhusamphasso, no cakkhusamphassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati cakkhudhātu … pe …**The eye element gives rise to eye contact. Eye contact gives rise to feeling born of eye contact. Feeling born of eye contact doesn’t give rise to eye contact. Eye contact doesn’t give rise to the eye element. …*";
P_HTM[3336]="*manodhātuṃ paṭicca uppajjati manosamphasso, manosamphassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati manosamphassajā vedanā, no manosamphassajaṃ vedanaṃ paṭicca uppajjati manosamphasso, no manosamphassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati manodhātu.**The mind element gives rise to mind contact. Mind contact gives rise to feeling born of mind contact. Feeling born of mind contact doesn’t give rise to mind contact. Mind contact doesn’t give rise to the mind element.*";
P_HTM[3337]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ, phassanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati vedanānānattaṃ, no vedanānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ, no phassanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhātunānattan”ti.**That’s how diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of contacts, and diversity of contacts gives rise to diversity of feelings, while diversity of feelings doesn’t give rise to diversity of contacts, and diversity of contacts doesn’t give rise to diversity of elements.”*";
P_HTM[3338]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3339]="*6. Bāhiradhātunānattasuttaṃ**External Diversity of Elements*";
P_HTM[3340]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3341]="*“Dhātunānattaṃ vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the diversity of elements.*";
P_HTM[3342]="*Taṃ suṇātha … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3343]="*katamañca, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ?**And what is the diversity of elements?*";
P_HTM[3344]="*Rūpadhātu saddadhātu gandhadhātu rasadhātu phoṭṭhabbadhātu dhammadhātu—**The sight element, the sound element, the smell element, the taste element, the touch element, and the thought element.*";
P_HTM[3345]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhātunānattan”ti.**This is called the diversity of elements.”*";
P_HTM[3346]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3347]="*7. Saññānānattasuttaṃ**Diversity of Perceptions*";
P_HTM[3348]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3349]="*“Dhātunānattaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati saññānānattaṃ, saññānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saṅkappanānattaṃ, saṅkappanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati chandanānattaṃ, chandanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariḷāhanānattaṃ, pariḷāhanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariyesanānānattaṃ.**“Mendicants, diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of perceptions. Diversity of perceptions gives rise to diversity of intentions. Diversity of intentions gives rise to diversity of desires. Diversity of desires gives rise to diversity of passions. Diversity of passions gives rise to diversity of searches.*";
P_HTM[3350]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ?**And what is the diversity of elements?*";
P_HTM[3351]="*Rūpadhātu … pe … dhammadhātu—**The sight element, the sound element, the smell element, the taste element, the touch element, and the thought element.*";
P_HTM[3352]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ.**This is called the diversity of elements.*";
P_HTM[3353]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saññānānattaṃ, saññānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saṅkappanānattaṃ, saṅkappanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati chandanānattaṃ, chandanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariḷāhanānattaṃ, pariḷāhanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariyesanānānattaṃ?**And how does diversity of elements give rise to diversity of perceptions, and diversity of perceptions give rise to diversity of thoughts, and diversity of thoughts give rise to diversity of desires, and diversity of desires give rise to diversity of passions, and diversity of passions give rise to diversity of searches?*";
P_HTM[3354]="*Rūpadhātuṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati rūpasaññā, rūpasaññaṃ paṭicca uppajjati rūpasaṅkappo, rūpasaṅkappaṃ paṭicca uppajjati rūpacchando, rūpacchandaṃ paṭicca uppajjati rūpapariḷāho, rūpapariḷāhaṃ paṭicca uppajjati rūpapariyesanā … pe …**The sight element gives rise to the perception of sights. The perception of sights gives rise to thoughts about sights. Thoughts about sights give rise to the desire for sights. The desire for sights gives rise to the passion for sights. The passion for sights gives rise to searching for sights. …*";
P_HTM[3355]="*dhammadhātuṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammasaññā, dhammasaññaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammasaṅkappo, dhammasaṅkappaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammacchando, dhammacchandaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammapariḷāho, dhammapariḷāhaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammapariyesanā.**The thought element gives rise to the perception of thoughts. The perception of thoughts gives rise to thoughts about thoughts. Thoughts about thoughts give rise to the desire for thoughts. The desire for thoughts gives rise to the passion for thoughts. The passion for thoughts gives rise to searching for thoughts.*";
P_HTM[3356]="*Evaṃ, kho, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saññānānattaṃ, saññānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saṅkappanānattaṃ, saṅkappanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati chandanānattaṃ, chandanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariḷāhanānattaṃ, pariḷāhanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariyesanānānattan”ti.**That’s how diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of perceptions, and diversity of perceptions gives rise to diversity of intentions, and diversity of intentions gives rise to diversity of desires, and diversity of desires gives rise to diversity of passions, and diversity of passions gives rise to diversity of searches.”*";
P_HTM[3357]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3358]="*8. Nopariyesanānānattasuttaṃ**No Diversity of Searches*";
P_HTM[3359]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3360]="*“Dhātunānattaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati saññānānattaṃ, saññānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saṅkappanānattaṃ, saṅkappanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati chandanānattaṃ, chandanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariḷāhanānattaṃ, pariḷāhanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariyesanānānattaṃ;**“Mendicants, diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of perceptions. Diversity of perceptions gives rise to diversity of intentions. Diversity of intentions gives rise to diversity of desires. Diversity of desires gives rise to diversity of passions. Diversity of passions gives rise to diversity of searches.*";
P_HTM[3361]="*no pariyesanānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariḷāhanānattaṃ, no pariḷāhanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati chandanānattaṃ, no chandanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saṅkappanānattaṃ, no saṅkappanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saññānānattaṃ, no saññānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhātunānattaṃ.**Diversity of searches doesn’t give rise to diversity of passions. Diversity of passions doesn’t give rise to diversity of desires. Diversity of desires doesn’t give rise to diversity of thoughts. Diversity of thoughts doesn’t give rise to diversity of perceptions. Diversity of perceptions doesn’t give rise to diversity of elements.*";
P_HTM[3362]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ?**And what is the diversity of elements?*";
P_HTM[3363]="*Rūpadhātu … pe … dhammadhātu—**The sight element, the sound element, the smell element, the taste element, the touch element, and the thought element.*";
P_HTM[3364]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ.**This is called the diversity of elements.*";
P_HTM[3365]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saññānānattaṃ, saññānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati … pe … pariyesanānānattaṃ;**And how does diversity of elements give rise to diversity of perceptions …*";
P_HTM[3366]="*no pariyesanānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariḷāhanānattaṃ, no pariḷāhanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati chandanānattaṃ, no chandanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saṅkappanānattaṃ, no saṅkappanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saññānānattaṃ, no saññānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhātunānattaṃ?**diversity of perceptions doesn’t give rise to diversity of elements?*";
P_HTM[3367]="*Rūpadhātuṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati rūpasaññā … pe …**The sight element gives rise to the perception of sights …*";
P_HTM[3368]="*dhammadhātuṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammasaññā, dhammasaññaṃ paṭicca uppajjati … pe … dhammapariyesanā;**The thought element gives rise to the perception of thoughts … the search for thoughts.*";
P_HTM[3369]="*no dhammapariyesanaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammapariḷāho, no dhammapariḷāhaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammacchando, no dhammacchandaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammasaṅkappo, no dhammasaṅkappaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammasaññā, no dhammasaññaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammadhātu.**The search for thoughts doesn’t give rise to the passion for thoughts. The passion for thoughts doesn’t give rise to the desire for thoughts. The desire for thoughts doesn’t give rise to thoughts about thoughts. Thoughts about thoughts don’t give rise to perceptions of thoughts. Perceptions of thoughts don’t give rise to the thought element.*";
P_HTM[3370]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saññānānattaṃ, saññānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati … pe … pariyesanānānattaṃ;**That’s how diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of perceptions …*";
P_HTM[3371]="*no pariyesanānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariḷāhanānattaṃ, no pariḷāhanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati chandanānattaṃ, no chandanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saṅkappanānattaṃ, no saṅkappanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saññānānattaṃ, no saññānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhātunānattan”ti.**diversity of perceptions doesn’t give rise to diversity of elements.”*";
P_HTM[3372]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3373]="*9. Bāhiraphassanānattasuttaṃ**Diversity of Gains*";
P_HTM[3374]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3375]="*“Dhātunānattaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati saññānānattaṃ, saññānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saṅkappanānattaṃ, saṅkappanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ, phassanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati vedanānānattaṃ, vedanānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati chandanānattaṃ, chandanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariḷāhanānattaṃ, pariḷāhanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariyesanānānattaṃ, pariyesanānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati lābhanānattaṃ.**“Mendicants, diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of perceptions. Diversity of perceptions gives rise to diversity of intentions. Diversity of intentions gives rise to diversity of contacts. Diversity of contacts gives rise to diversity of feelings. Diversity of feelings gives rise to diversity of desires. Diversity of desires gives rise to diversity of passions. Diversity of passions gives rise to diversity of searches. Diversity of searches gives rise to diversity of gains.*";
P_HTM[3376]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ?**And what is the diversity of elements?*";
P_HTM[3377]="*Rūpadhātu … pe … dhammadhātu—**The sight element, the sound element, the smell element, the taste element, the touch element, and the thought element.*";
P_HTM[3378]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ.**This is called the diversity of elements.*";
P_HTM[3379]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saññānānattaṃ, saññānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati … pe … lābhanānattaṃ?**And how does diversity of elements give rise to diversity of perceptions … diversity of searches give rise to diversity of gains?*";
P_HTM[3380]="*Rūpadhātuṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati rūpasaññā, rūpasaññaṃ paṭicca uppajjati rūpasaṅkappo, rūpasaṅkappaṃ paṭicca uppajjati rūpasamphasso, rūpasamphassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati rūpasamphassajā vedanā, rūpasamphassajaṃ vedanaṃ paṭicca uppajjati rūpacchando, rūpacchandaṃ paṭicca uppajjati rūpapariḷāho, rūpapariḷāhaṃ paṭicca uppajjati rūpapariyesanā, rūpapariyesanaṃ paṭicca uppajjati rūpalābho … pe …**The sight element gives rise to the perception of sights. The perception of sights gives rise to thoughts about sights. Thoughts about sights give rise to the desire for sights. The desire for sights gives rise to the passion for sights. The passion for sights gives rise to searching for sights. Searching for sights gives rise to gaining sights …*";
P_HTM[3381]="*dhammadhātuṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammasaññā, dhammasaññaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammasaṅkappo, dhammasaṅkappaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammasamphasso, dhammasamphassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammasamphassajā vedanā, dhammasamphassajaṃ vedanaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammacchando, dhammacchandaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammapariḷāho, dhammapariḷāhaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammapariyesanā, dhammapariyesanaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammalābho.**The thought element gives rise to the perception of thoughts. The perception of thoughts gives rise to thoughts about thoughts. Thoughts about thoughts give rise to the desire for thoughts. The desire for thoughts gives rise to the passion for thoughts. The passion for thoughts gives rise to searching for thoughts. Searching for thoughts gives rise to gaining thoughts.*";
P_HTM[3382]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saññānānattaṃ, saññānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati … pe … pariyesanānānattaṃ, pariyesanānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati lābhanānattan”ti.**That’s how diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of perceptions … diversity of searches gives rise to diversity of gains.”*";
P_HTM[3383]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3384]="*10. Dutiyabāhiraphassanānattasuttaṃ**No Diversity of Gains*";
P_HTM[3385]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3386]="*“Dhātunānattaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati saññānānattaṃ,**“Mendicants, diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of perceptions.*";
P_HTM[3387]="*saññānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saṅkappanānattaṃ, phassa …**Diversity of perceptions gives rise to diversity of thoughts. …*";
P_HTM[3388]="*vedanā …**feelings …*";
P_HTM[3389]="*chanda …**desires …*";
P_HTM[3390]="*pariḷāha …**passions …*";
P_HTM[3391]="*pariyesanānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati lābhanānattaṃ;**Diversity of searches gives rise to diversity of gains.*";
P_HTM[3392]="*no lābhanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariyesanānānattaṃ,**Diversity of gains doesn’t give rise to diversity of searches.*";
P_HTM[3393]="*no pariyesanānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariḷāhanānattaṃ, no pariḷāhanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati … pe …**Diversity of searches doesn’t give rise to diversity of passions. …*";
P_HTM[3394]="*chanda …**desires …*";
P_HTM[3395]="*vedanā …**feelings …*";
P_HTM[3396]="*phassa …**contacts …*";
P_HTM[3397]="*saṅkappa …**thoughts …*";
P_HTM[3398]="*saññānānattaṃ, no saññānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhātunānattaṃ.**Diversity of perceptions doesn’t give rise to diversity of elements.*";
P_HTM[3399]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ?**And what is the diversity of elements?*";
P_HTM[3400]="*Rūpadhātu … pe … dhammadhātu—**The sight element, the sound element, the smell element, the taste element, the touch element, and the thought element.*";
P_HTM[3401]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ.**This is called the diversity of elements.*";
P_HTM[3402]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saññānānattaṃ,**And how does diversity of elements give rise to diversity of perceptions …*";
P_HTM[3403]="*Phassa …**contacts …*";
P_HTM[3404]="*vedanā …**feelings …*";
P_HTM[3405]="*chanda …**desires …*";
P_HTM[3406]="*pariḷāha …**passions …*";
P_HTM[3407]="*pariyesanā …**searches …*";
P_HTM[3408]="*lābha …**gains …*";
P_HTM[3409]="*no lābhanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariyesanānānattaṃ,**while diversity of gains doesn’t give rise to diversity of searches …*";
P_HTM[3410]="*no pariyesanānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariḷāha …**passions …*";
P_HTM[3411]="*chanda …**desires …*";
P_HTM[3412]="*vedanā …**feelings …*";
P_HTM[3413]="*phassa …**contacts …*";
P_HTM[3414]="*no saṅkappanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saññānānattaṃ, no saññānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhātunānattaṃ?**thoughts … perceptions … elements?*";
P_HTM[3415]="*Rūpadhātuṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati rūpasaññā … pe …**The sight element gives rise to the perception of sights …*";
P_HTM[3416]="*dhammadhātuṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammasaññā, dhammasaññaṃ paṭicca uppajjati … pe …**The thought element gives rise to the perception of thoughts …*";
P_HTM[3417]="*dhammapariyesanā, dhammapariyesanaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammalābho;**The search for thoughts gives rise to gaining thoughts.*";
P_HTM[3418]="*no dhammalābhaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammapariyesanā, no dhammapariyesanaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammapariḷāho, no dhammapariḷāhaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammacchando, no dhammacchandaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammasamphassajā vedanā, no dhammasamphassajaṃ vedanaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammasamphasso, no dhammasamphassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammasaṅkappo, no dhammasaṅkappaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammasaññā, no dhammasaññaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhammadhātu.**The gaining of thoughts doesn’t give rise to the search for thoughts. The search for thoughts doesn’t give rise to the passion for thoughts. The passion for thoughts doesn’t give rise to the desire for thoughts. The desire for thoughts doesn’t give rise to thoughts about thoughts. Thoughts about thoughts don’t give rise to perceptions of thoughts. Perceptions of thoughts don’t give rise to the thought element.*";
P_HTM[3419]="*Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saññānānattaṃ, saññānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati … pe …**That’s how diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of perceptions …*";
P_HTM[3420]="*saṅkappa …* **";
P_HTM[3421]="*phassa …* **";
P_HTM[3422]="*vedanā …* **";
P_HTM[3423]="*chanda …* **";
P_HTM[3424]="*pariḷāha …* **";
P_HTM[3425]="*pariyesanā …* **";
P_HTM[3426]="*lābha …* **";
P_HTM[3427]="*no lābhanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariyesanānānattaṃ, no pariyesanānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariḷāhanānattaṃ, no pariḷāhanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati chandanānattaṃ, no chandanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati vedanānānattaṃ, no vedanānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ, no phassanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saṅkappanānattaṃ, no saṅkappanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saññānānattaṃ, no saññānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dhātunānattan”ti.**diversity of perceptions doesn’t give rise to diversity of elements.”*";
P_HTM[3428]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3429]="*Nānattavaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[3430]="*Dhātuphassañca no cetaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[3431]="*vedanā apare duve;* **";
P_HTM[3432]="*Etaṃ ajjhattapañcakaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[3433]="*dhātusaññañca no cetaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[3434]="*Phassassa apare duve,* **";
P_HTM[3435]="*etaṃ bāhirapañcakanti.* **";
P_HTM[3436]="*2. Āhāravaggo**The Second Chapter*";
P_HTM[3437]="*1. Sattadhātusuttaṃ**Seven Elements*";
P_HTM[3438]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3439]="*“Sattimā, bhikkhave, dhātuyo.**“Mendicants, there are these seven elements.*";
P_HTM[3440]="*Katamā satta?**What seven?*";
P_HTM[3441]="*Ābhādhātu, subhadhātu, ākāsānañcāyatanadhātu, viññāṇañcāyatanadhātu, ākiñcaññāyatanadhātu, nevasaññānāsaññāyatanadhātu, saññāvedayitanirodhadhātu—**The element of light, the element of beauty, the element of the dimension of infinite space, the element of the dimension of infinite consciousness, the element of the dimension of nothingness, the element of the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, and the element of the cessation of perception and feeling.*";
P_HTM[3442]="*imā kho, bhikkhave, satta dhātuyo”ti.**These are the seven elements.”*";
P_HTM[3443]="*Evaṃ vutte, aññataro bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, one of the mendicants asked the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[3444]="*“yā cāyaṃ, bhante, ābhādhātu yā ca subhadhātu yā ca ākāsānañcāyatanadhātu yā ca viññāṇañcāyatanadhātu yā ca ākiñcaññāyatanadhātu yā ca nevasaññānāsaññāyatanadhātu yā ca saññāvedayitanirodhadhātu—imā nu kho, bhante, dhātuyo kiṃ paṭicca paññāyantī”ti?**“Sir, due to what does each of these elements appear?”*";
P_HTM[3445]="*“Yāyaṃ, bhikkhu, ābhādhātu—ayaṃ dhātu andhakāraṃ paṭicca paññāyati.**“Mendicant, the element of light appears due to the element of darkness.*";
P_HTM[3446]="*Yāyaṃ, bhikkhu, subhadhātu—ayaṃ dhātu asubhaṃ paṭicca paññāyati.**The element of beauty appears due to the element of ugliness.*";
P_HTM[3447]="*Yāyaṃ, bhikkhu, ākāsānañcāyatanadhātu—ayaṃ dhātu rūpaṃ paṭicca paññāyati.**The element of the dimension of infinite space appears due to the element of form.*";
P_HTM[3448]="*Yāyaṃ, bhikkhu, viññāṇañcāyatanadhātu—ayaṃ dhātu ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ paṭicca paññāyati.**The element of the dimension of infinite consciousness appears due to the element of the dimension of infinite space.*";
P_HTM[3449]="*Yāyaṃ, bhikkhu, ākiñcaññāyatanadhātu—ayaṃ dhātu viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ paṭicca paññāyati.**The element of the dimension of nothingness appears due to the element of the dimension of infinite consciousness.*";
P_HTM[3450]="*Yāyaṃ, bhikkhu, nevasaññānāsaññāyatanadhātu—ayaṃ dhātu ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ paṭicca paññāyati.**The element of the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception appears due to the element of the dimension of nothingness.*";
P_HTM[3451]="*Yāyaṃ, bhikkhu, saññāvedayitanirodhadhātu—ayaṃ dhātu nirodhaṃ paṭicca paññāyatī”ti.**The element of the cessation of perception and feeling appears due to the element of cessation.”*";
P_HTM[3452]="*“Yā cāyaṃ, bhante, ābhādhātu yā ca subhadhātu yā ca ākāsānañcāyatanadhātu yā ca viññāṇañcāyatanadhātu yā ca ākiñcaññāyatanadhātu yā ca nevasaññānāsaññāyatanadhātu yā ca saññāvedayitanirodhadhātu—imā nu kho, bhante, dhātuyo kathaṃ samāpatti pattabbā”ti?**“Sir, how is each of these elements to be attained?”*";
P_HTM[3453]="*“Yā cāyaṃ, bhikkhu, ābhādhātu yā ca subhadhātu yā ca ākāsānañcāyatanadhātu yā ca viññāṇañcāyatanadhātu yā ca ākiñcaññāyatanadhātu—imā dhātuyo saññāsamāpatti pattabbā.**“The elements of light, beauty, the dimension of infinite space, the dimension of infinite consciousness, and the dimension of nothingness are attainments with perception.*";
P_HTM[3454]="*Yāyaṃ, bhikkhu, nevasaññānāsaññāyatanadhātu—ayaṃ dhātu saṅkhārāvasesasamāpatti pattabbā.**The element of the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception is an attainment with only a residue of conditioned phenomena.*";
P_HTM[3455]="*Yāyaṃ, bhikkhu, saññāvedayitanirodhadhātu—ayaṃ dhātu nirodhasamāpatti pattabbā”ti.**The element of the cessation of perception and feeling is an attainment of cessation.”*";
P_HTM[3456]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3457]="*2. Sanidānasuttaṃ**With a Cause*";
P_HTM[3458]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3459]="*“Sanidānaṃ, bhikkhave, uppajjati kāmavitakko, no anidānaṃ; sanidānaṃ uppajjati byāpādavitakko, no anidānaṃ; sanidānaṃ uppajjati vihiṃsāvitakko, no anidānaṃ.**“Mendicants, sensual, malicious, and cruel thoughts arise for a reason, not without reason.*";
P_HTM[3460]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, sanidānaṃ uppajjati kāmavitakko, no anidānaṃ; sanidānaṃ uppajjati byāpādavitakko, no anidānaṃ; sanidānaṃ uppajjati vihiṃsāvitakko, no anidānaṃ?**And how do sensual, malicious, and cruel thoughts arise for a reason, not without reason?*";
P_HTM[3461]="*Kāmadhātuṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati kāmasaññā, kāmasaññaṃ paṭicca uppajjati kāmasaṅkappo, kāmasaṅkappaṃ paṭicca uppajjati kāmacchando, kāmacchandaṃ paṭicca uppajjati kāmapariḷāho, kāmapariḷāhaṃ paṭicca uppajjati kāmapariyesanā.**The element of sensuality gives rise to sensual perceptions. Sensual perceptions give rise to sensual thoughts. Sensual thoughts give rise to sensual desires. Sensual desires give rise to sensual passions. Sensual passions give rise to searches for sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[3462]="*Kāmapariyesanaṃ, bhikkhave, pariyesamāno assutavā puthujjano tīhi ṭhānehi micchā paṭipajjati—kāyena, vācāya, manasā.**An uneducated ordinary person on a search for sensual pleasures behaves badly in three ways: by body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[3463]="*Byāpādadhātuṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati byāpādasaññā, byāpādasaññaṃ paṭicca uppajjati byāpādasaṅkappo … pe … byāpādacchando … byāpādapariḷāho … byāpādapariyesanā …**The element of malice gives rise to malicious perceptions. Malicious perceptions give rise to malicious thoughts. … malicious desires … malicious passions … malicious searches …*";
P_HTM[3464]="*byāpādapariyesanaṃ, bhikkhave, pariyesamāno assutavā puthujjano tīhi ṭhānehi micchā paṭipajjati—kāyena, vācāya, manasā.**An uneducated ordinary person on a malicious search behaves badly in three ways: by body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[3465]="*Vihiṃsādhātuṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati vihiṃsāsaññā; vihiṃsāsaññaṃ paṭicca uppajjati vihiṃsāsaṅkappo … pe … vihiṃsāchando … vihiṃsāpariḷāho … vihiṃsāpariyesanā …**The element of cruelty gives rise to cruel perceptions. Cruel perceptions give rise to cruel thoughts. … cruel desires … cruel passions … cruel searches …*";
P_HTM[3466]="*vihiṃsāpariyesanaṃ, bhikkhave, pariyesamāno assutavā puthujjano tīhi ṭhānehi micchā paṭipajjati—kāyena, vācāya, manasā.**An uneducated ordinary person on a cruel search behaves badly in three ways: by body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[3467]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso ādittaṃ tiṇukkaṃ sukkhe tiṇadāye nikkhipeyya; no ce hatthehi ca pādehi ca khippameva nibbāpeyya. Evañhi, bhikkhave, ye tiṇakaṭṭhanissitā pāṇā te anayabyasanaṃ āpajjeyyuṃ.**Suppose a person was to drop a burning torch in a thicket of dry grass. If they don’t quickly extinguish it with their hands and feet, the creatures living in the grass and wood would come to ruin.*";
P_HTM[3468]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, yo hi koci samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā uppannaṃ visamagataṃ saññaṃ na khippameva pajahati vinodeti byantīkaroti anabhāvaṃ gameti, so diṭṭhe ceva dhamme dukkhaṃ viharati savighātaṃ saupāyāsaṃ sapariḷāhaṃ;**In the same way, a corrupt perception might arise in an ascetic or brahmin. If they don’t quickly give it up, get rid of it, eliminate it, and obliterate it, they’ll suffer in the present life, with anguish, distress, and fever.*";
P_HTM[3469]="*kāyassa ca bhedā paraṃ maraṇā duggati pāṭikaṅkhā.**And when the body breaks up, after death, they can expect to be reborn in a bad place.*";
P_HTM[3470]="*Sanidānaṃ, bhikkhave, uppajjati nekkhammavitakko, no anidānaṃ; sanidānaṃ uppajjati abyāpādavitakko, no anidānaṃ; sanidānaṃ uppajjati avihiṃsāvitakko, no anidānaṃ.**Thoughts of renunciation, good will, and harmlessness arise for a reason, not without reason.*";
P_HTM[3471]="*Kathañca, bhikkhave, sanidānaṃ uppajjati nekkhammavitakko, no anidānaṃ; sanidānaṃ uppajjati abyāpādavitakko, no anidānaṃ; sanidānaṃ uppajjati avihiṃsāvitakko, no anidānaṃ?**And how do thoughts of renunciation, good will, and harmlessness arise for a reason, not without reason?*";
P_HTM[3472]="*Nekkhammadhātuṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati nekkhammasaññā,**The element of renunciation gives rise to perceptions of renunciation.*";
P_HTM[3473]="*nekkhammasaññaṃ paṭicca uppajjati nekkhammasaṅkappo,**Perceptions of renunciation give rise to thoughts of renunciation.*";
P_HTM[3474]="*nekkhammasaṅkappaṃ paṭicca uppajjati nekkhammacchando,**Thoughts of renunciation give rise to enthusiasm for renunciation.*";
P_HTM[3475]="*nekkhammacchandaṃ paṭicca uppajjati nekkhammapariḷāho,**Enthusiasm for renunciation gives rise to fervor for renunciation.*";
P_HTM[3476]="*nekkhammapariḷāhaṃ paṭicca uppajjati nekkhammapariyesanā;**Fervor for renunciation gives rise to the search for renunciation.*";
P_HTM[3477]="*nekkhammapariyesanaṃ, bhikkhave, pariyesamāno sutavā ariyasāvako tīhi ṭhānehi sammā paṭipajjati—kāyena, vācāya, manasā.**An educated noble disciple on a search for renunciation behaves well in three ways: by body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[3478]="*Abyāpādadhātuṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati abyāpādasaññā,**The element of good will gives rise to perceptions of good will.*";
P_HTM[3479]="*abyāpādasaññaṃ paṭicca uppajjati abyāpādasaṅkappo … pe …**Perceptions of good will give rise to thoughts of good will. …*";
P_HTM[3480]="*abyāpādacchando …**enthusiasm for good will …*";
P_HTM[3481]="*abyāpādapariḷāho …**fervor for good will …*";
P_HTM[3482]="*abyāpādapariyesanā,**the search for good will.*";
P_HTM[3483]="*abyāpādapariyesanaṃ, bhikkhave, pariyesamāno sutavā ariyasāvako tīhi ṭhānehi sammā paṭipajjati—kāyena, vācāya, manasā.**An educated noble disciple on a search for good will behaves well in three ways: by body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[3484]="*Avihiṃsādhātuṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati avihiṃsāsaññā,**The element of harmlessness gives rise to harmlessness perceptions.*";
P_HTM[3485]="*avihiṃsāsaññaṃ paṭicca uppajjati avihiṃsāsaṅkappo,**Harmlessness perceptions give rise to harmlessness thoughts. …*";
P_HTM[3486]="*avihiṃsāsaṅkappaṃ paṭicca uppajjati avihiṃsāchando,**enthusiasm for harmlessness …*";
P_HTM[3487]="*avihiṃsāchandaṃ paṭicca uppajjati avihiṃsāpariḷāho,**fervor for harmlessness …*";
P_HTM[3488]="*avihiṃsāpariḷāhaṃ paṭicca uppajjati avihiṃsāpariyesanā;**the search for harmlessness.*";
P_HTM[3489]="*avihiṃsāpariyesanaṃ, bhikkhave, pariyesamāno sutavā ariyasāvako tīhi ṭhānehi sammā paṭipajjati—kāyena, vācāya, manasā.**An educated noble disciple on a search for harmlessness behaves well in three ways: by body, speech, and mind.*";
P_HTM[3490]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso ādittaṃ tiṇukkaṃ sukkhe tiṇadāye nikkhipeyya; tamenaṃ hatthehi ca pādehi ca khippameva nibbāpeyya. Evañhi, bhikkhave, ye tiṇakaṭṭhanissitā pāṇā te na anayabyasanaṃ āpajjeyyuṃ.**Suppose a person was to drop a burning torch in a thicket of dry grass. If they were to quickly extinguish it with their hands and feet, the creatures living in the grass and wood wouldn’t come to ruin.*";
P_HTM[3491]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, yo hi koci samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā uppannaṃ visamagataṃ saññaṃ khippameva pajahati vinodeti byantīkaroti anabhāvaṃ gameti, so diṭṭhe ceva dhamme sukhaṃ viharati avighātaṃ anupāyāsaṃ apariḷāhaṃ;**In the same way, a corrupt perception might arise in an ascetic or brahmin. If they quickly give it up, get rid of it, eliminate it, and obliterate it, they’ll be happy in the present life, free of anguish, distress, and fever.*";
P_HTM[3492]="*kāyassa ca bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugati pāṭikaṅkhā”ti.**And when the body breaks up, after death, they can expect to be reborn in a good place.”*";
P_HTM[3493]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3494]="*3. Giñjakāvasathasuttaṃ**In the Brick Hall*";
P_HTM[3495]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā ñātike viharati giñjakāvasathe.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Nādika in the brick house.*";
P_HTM[3496]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[3497]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[3498]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[3499]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[3500]="*“Dhātuṃ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati saññā, uppajjati diṭṭhi, uppajjati vitakko”ti.**“Mendicants, an element gives rise to a perception, a view, and a thought.”*";
P_HTM[3501]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā kaccāno bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Venerable Kaccāna said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[3502]="*“yāyaṃ, bhante, diṭṭhi:**“Sir, regarding*";
P_HTM[3503]="*‘asammāsambuddhesu sammāsambuddhā’ti, ayaṃ nu kho, bhante, diṭṭhi kiṃ paṭicca paññāyatī”ti?**those who are not fully awakened Buddhas, there is a view that they are in fact fully awakened Buddhas. Due to what does this view appear?”*";
P_HTM[3504]="*“Mahati kho esā, kaccāna, dhātu yadidaṃ avijjādhātu.**“It’s a mighty thing, Kaccāna, the element of ignorance.*";
P_HTM[3505]="*Hīnaṃ, kaccāna, dhātuṃ paṭicca uppajjati hīnā saññā, hīnā diṭṭhi, hīno vitakko, hīnā cetanā, hīnā patthanā, hīno paṇidhi, hīno puggalo, hīnā vācā;**An inferior element gives rise to inferior perceptions, inferior views, inferior thoughts, inferior intentions, inferior aims, inferior wishes, an inferior person, and inferior speech.*";
P_HTM[3506]="*hīnaṃ ācikkhati deseti paññapeti paṭṭhapeti vivarati vibhajati uttānīkaroti;**One explains, teaches, asserts, establishes, clarifies, analyzes, and reveals the inferior.*";
P_HTM[3507]="*hīnā tassa upapattīti vadāmi.**I say that their rebirth is inferior.*";
P_HTM[3508]="*Majjhimaṃ, kaccāna, dhātuṃ paṭicca uppajjati majjhimā saññā, majjhimā diṭṭhi, majjhimo vitakko, majjhimā cetanā, majjhimā patthanā, majjhimo paṇidhi, majjhimo puggalo, majjhimā vācā;**A middling element gives rise to middling perceptions, middling views, middling thoughts, middling intentions, middling aims, middling wishes, a middling person, and middling speech.*";
P_HTM[3509]="*majjhimaṃ ācikkhati deseti paññapeti paṭṭhapeti vivarati vibhajati uttānīkaroti;**One explains, teaches, asserts, establishes, clarifies, analyzes, and reveals the middling.*";
P_HTM[3510]="*majjhimā tassa upapattīti vadāmi.**I say that their rebirth is middling.*";
P_HTM[3511]="*Paṇītaṃ, kaccāna, dhātuṃ paṭicca uppajjati paṇītā saññā, paṇītā diṭṭhi, paṇīto vitakko, paṇītā cetanā, paṇītā patthanā, paṇīto paṇidhi, paṇīto puggalo, paṇītā vācā;**A superior element gives rise to superior perceptions, superior views, superior thoughts, superior intentions, superior aims, superior wishes, a superior person, and superior speech.*";
P_HTM[3512]="*paṇītaṃ ācikkhati deseti paññapeti paṭṭhapeti vivarati vibhajati uttānīkaroti;**One explains, teaches, asserts, establishes, clarifies, analyzes, and reveals the superior.*";
P_HTM[3513]="*paṇītā tassa upapattīti vadāmī”ti.**I say that their rebirth is superior.”*";
P_HTM[3514]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3515]="*4. Hīnādhimuttikasuttaṃ**Bad Attitudes*";
P_HTM[3516]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3517]="*“Dhātusova, bhikkhave, sattā saṃsandanti samenti.**“Mendicants, sentient beings come together and converge because of an element.*";
P_HTM[3518]="*Hīnādhimuttikā hīnādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti;**Those who have a bad attitude come together and converge with those who have a bad attitude.*";
P_HTM[3519]="*kalyāṇādhimuttikā kalyāṇādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti.**Those who have a good attitude come together and converge with those who have a good attitude.*";
P_HTM[3520]="*Atītampi kho, bhikkhave, addhānaṃ dhātusova sattā saṃsandiṃsu samiṃsu.**In the past, too, sentient beings came together and converged because of an element. …*";
P_HTM[3521]="*Hīnādhimuttikā hīnādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandiṃsu samiṃsu;* **";
P_HTM[3522]="*kalyāṇādhimuttikā kalyāṇādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandiṃsu samiṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[3523]="*Anāgatampi kho, bhikkhave, addhānaṃ dhātusova sattā saṃsandissanti samessanti.**In the future, too, sentient beings will come together and converge because of an element. …*";
P_HTM[3524]="*Hīnādhimuttikā hīnādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandissanti samessanti;* **";
P_HTM[3525]="*kalyāṇādhimuttikā kalyāṇādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandissanti samessanti.* **";
P_HTM[3526]="*Etarahipi kho, bhikkhave, paccuppannaṃ addhānaṃ dhātusova sattā saṃsandanti samenti.**At present, too, sentient beings come together and converge because of an element.*";
P_HTM[3527]="*Hīnādhimuttikā hīnādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti;**Those who have a bad attitude come together and converge with those who have a bad attitude.*";
P_HTM[3528]="*kalyāṇādhimuttikā kalyāṇādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samentī”ti.**Those who have a good attitude come together and converge with those who have a good attitude.”*";
P_HTM[3529]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3530]="*5. Caṅkamasuttaṃ**Walking Meditation*";
P_HTM[3531]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain.*";
P_HTM[3532]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā sāriputto sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ bhagavato avidūre caṅkamati;**Now at that time Venerable Sāriputta was walking meditation together with several mendicants not far from the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3533]="*āyasmāpi kho mahāmoggallāno sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ bhagavato avidūre caṅkamati;**Venerable Mahāmoggallāna was doing likewise, as were*";
P_HTM[3534]="*āyasmāpi kho mahākassapo sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ bhagavato avidūre caṅkamati;**Venerable Mahākassapa,*";
P_HTM[3535]="*āyasmāpi kho anuruddho sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ bhagavato avidūre caṅkamati;**Venerable Anuruddha,*";
P_HTM[3536]="*āyasmāpi kho puṇṇo mantāniputto sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ bhagavato avidūre caṅkamati;**Venerable Puṇṇa Mantāniputta,*";
P_HTM[3537]="*āyasmāpi kho upāli sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ bhagavato avidūre caṅkamati;**Venerable Upāli,*";
P_HTM[3538]="*āyasmāpi kho ānando sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ bhagavato avidūre caṅkamati;**Venerable Ānanda,*";
P_HTM[3539]="*devadattopi kho sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ bhagavato avidūre caṅkamati.**and Devadatta.*";
P_HTM[3540]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[3541]="*“passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, sāriputtaṃ sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ caṅkamantan”ti?**“Mendicants, do you see Sāriputta walking meditation together with several mendicants?”*";
P_HTM[3542]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3543]="*“Sabbe kho ete, bhikkhave, bhikkhū mahāpaññā.**“All of those mendicants have great wisdom.*";
P_HTM[3544]="*Passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, moggallānaṃ sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ caṅkamantan”ti?**Do you see Moggallāna walking meditation together with several mendicants?”*";
P_HTM[3545]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3546]="*“Sabbe kho ete, bhikkhave, bhikkhū mahiddhikā.**“All of those mendicants have great psychic power.*";
P_HTM[3547]="*Passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, kassapaṃ sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ caṅkamantan”ti?**Do you see Kassapa walking meditation together with several mendicants?”*";
P_HTM[3548]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3549]="*“Sabbe kho ete, bhikkhave, bhikkhū dhutavādā.**“All of those mendicants advocate austerities.*";
P_HTM[3550]="*Passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, anuruddhaṃ sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ caṅkamantan”ti?**Do you see Anuruddha walking meditation together with several mendicants?”*";
P_HTM[3551]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3552]="*“Sabbe kho ete, bhikkhave, bhikkhū dibbacakkhukā.**“All of those mendicants have clairvoyance.*";
P_HTM[3553]="*Passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, puṇṇaṃ mantāniputtaṃ sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ caṅkamantan”ti?**Do you see Puṇṇa Mantāniputta walking meditation together with several mendicants?”*";
P_HTM[3554]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3555]="*“Sabbe kho ete, bhikkhave, bhikkhū dhammakathikā.**“All of those mendicants are Dhamma speakers.*";
P_HTM[3556]="*Passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, upāliṃ sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ caṅkamantan”ti?**Do you see Upāli walking meditation together with several mendicants?”*";
P_HTM[3557]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3558]="*“Sabbe kho ete, bhikkhave, bhikkhū vinayadharā.**“All of those mendicants are experts in monastic training.*";
P_HTM[3559]="*Passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, ānandaṃ sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ caṅkamantan”ti?**Do you see Ānanda walking meditation together with several mendicants?”*";
P_HTM[3560]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3561]="*“Sabbe kho ete, bhikkhave, bhikkhū bahussutā.**“All of those mendicants are very learned.*";
P_HTM[3562]="*Passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, devadattaṃ sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ caṅkamantan”ti?**Do you see Devadatta walking meditation together with several mendicants?”*";
P_HTM[3563]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[3564]="*“Sabbe kho ete, bhikkhave, bhikkhū pāpicchā.**“All of those mendicants have bad desires.*";
P_HTM[3565]="*Dhātusova, bhikkhave, sattā saṃsandanti samenti.**Sentient beings come together and converge because of an element.*";
P_HTM[3566]="*Hīnādhimuttikā hīnādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti;**Those who have a bad attitude come together and converge with those who have a bad attitude.*";
P_HTM[3567]="*kalyāṇādhimuttikā kalyāṇādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti.**Those who have a good attitude come together and converge with those who have a good attitude.*";
P_HTM[3568]="*Atītampi kho, bhikkhave, addhānaṃ dhātusova sattā saṃsandiṃsu samiṃsu.**In the past,*";
P_HTM[3569]="*Hīnādhimuttikā hīnādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandiṃsu samiṃsu;* **";
P_HTM[3570]="*kalyāṇādhimuttikā kalyāṇādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandiṃsu samiṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[3571]="*Anāgatampi kho, bhikkhave, addhānaṃ dhātusova sattā saṃsandissanti samessanti.**in the future,*";
P_HTM[3572]="*Hīnādhimuttikā hīnādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandissanti samessanti;* **";
P_HTM[3573]="*kalyāṇādhimuttikā kalyāṇādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandissanti samessanti.* **";
P_HTM[3574]="*Etarahipi kho, bhikkhave, paccuppannaṃ addhānaṃ dhātusova sattā saṃsandanti samenti.**and also in the present, sentient beings come together and converge because of an element.*";
P_HTM[3575]="*Hīnādhimuttikā hīnādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti;**Those who have a bad attitude come together and converge with those who have a bad attitude.*";
P_HTM[3576]="*kalyāṇādhimuttikā kalyāṇādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samentī”ti.**Those who have a good attitude come together and converge with those who have a good attitude.”*";
P_HTM[3577]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3578]="*6. Sagāthāsuttaṃ**With Verses*";
P_HTM[3579]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3580]="*“Dhātusova, bhikkhave, sattā saṃsandanti samenti.**“Mendicants, sentient beings come together and converge because of an element.*";
P_HTM[3581]="*Hīnādhimuttikā hīnādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti.**Those who have a bad attitude come together and converge with those who have a bad attitude.*";
P_HTM[3582]="*Atītampi kho, bhikkhave, addhānaṃ dhātusova sattā saṃsandiṃsu samiṃsu.**In the past …*";
P_HTM[3583]="*Hīnādhimuttikā hīnādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandiṃsu samiṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[3584]="*Anāgatampi kho, bhikkhave, addhānaṃ dhātusova sattā saṃsandissanti samessanti.**In the future …*";
P_HTM[3585]="*Hīnādhimuttikā hīnādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandissanti samessanti.* **";
P_HTM[3586]="*Etarahipi kho, bhikkhave, paccuppannaṃ addhānaṃ dhātusova sattā saṃsandanti samenti.**At present, too, sentient beings come together and converge because of an element.*";
P_HTM[3587]="*Hīnādhimuttikā hīnādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti.**Those who have a bad attitude come together and converge with those who have a bad attitude.*";
P_HTM[3588]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gūtho gūthena saṃsandati sameti;**It’s like how dung comes together with dung,*";
P_HTM[3589]="*muttaṃ muttena saṃsandati sameti;**urine with urine,*";
P_HTM[3590]="*kheḷo kheḷena saṃsandati sameti;**spit with spit,*";
P_HTM[3591]="*pubbo pubbena saṃsandati sameti;**pus with pus,*";
P_HTM[3592]="*lohitaṃ lohitena saṃsandati sameti;**and blood with blood.*";
P_HTM[3593]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, dhātusova sattā saṃsandanti samenti.**In the same way, sentient beings come together and converge because of an element.*";
P_HTM[3594]="*Hīnādhimuttikā hīnādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti.**Those who have a bad attitude come together and converge with those who have a bad attitude.*";
P_HTM[3595]="*Atītampi kho addhānaṃ … pe …**In the past …*";
P_HTM[3596]="*anāgatampi kho addhānaṃ … pe …**In the future …*";
P_HTM[3597]="*etarahipi kho paccuppannaṃ addhānaṃ dhātusova sattā saṃsandanti samenti.**At present, too, sentient beings come together and converge because of an element.*";
P_HTM[3598]="*Hīnādhimuttikā hīnādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti.**Those who have a bad attitude come together and converge with those who have a bad attitude.*";
P_HTM[3599]="*Dhātusova, bhikkhave, sattā saṃsandanti samenti.**Sentient beings come together and converge because of an element.*";
P_HTM[3600]="*Kalyāṇādhimuttikā kalyāṇādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti.**Those who have a good attitude come together and converge with those who have a good attitude.*";
P_HTM[3601]="*Atītampi kho, bhikkhave, addhānaṃ dhātusova sattā saṃsandiṃsu samiṃsu.**In the past …*";
P_HTM[3602]="*Kalyāṇādhimuttikā kalyāṇādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandiṃsu samiṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[3603]="*Anāgatampi kho, bhikkhave, addhānaṃ … pe …**In the future …*";
P_HTM[3604]="*etarahipi kho, bhikkhave, paccuppannaṃ addhānaṃ dhātusova sattā saṃsandanti samenti.**At present, too, sentient beings come together and converge because of an element.*";
P_HTM[3605]="*Kalyāṇādhimuttikā kalyāṇādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti.**Those who have a good attitude come together and converge with those who have a good attitude.*";
P_HTM[3606]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, khīraṃ khīrena saṃsandati sameti;**It’s like how milk comes together with milk,*";
P_HTM[3607]="*telaṃ telena saṃsandati sameti;**oil with oil,*";
P_HTM[3608]="*sappi sappinā saṃsandati sameti;**ghee with ghee,*";
P_HTM[3609]="*madhu madhunā saṃsandati sameti;**honey with honey,*";
P_HTM[3610]="*phāṇitaṃ phāṇitena saṃsandati sameti;**and molasses with molasses.*";
P_HTM[3611]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, dhātusova sattā saṃsandanti samenti.**In the same way, sentient beings come together and converge because of an element.*";
P_HTM[3612]="*Kalyāṇādhimuttikā kalyāṇādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samenti.**Those who have a good attitude come together and converge with those who have a good attitude.*";
P_HTM[3613]="*Atītampi kho addhānaṃ …**In the past …*";
P_HTM[3614]="*anāgatampi kho addhānaṃ …**In the future …*";
P_HTM[3615]="*etarahipi kho paccuppannaṃ addhānaṃ dhātusova sattā saṃsandanti samenti.**At present, too, sentient beings come together and converge because of an element.*";
P_HTM[3616]="*Kalyāṇādhimuttikā kalyāṇādhimuttikehi saddhiṃ saṃsandanti samentī”ti.**Those who have a good attitude come together and converge with those who have a good attitude.”*";
P_HTM[3617]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[3618]="*Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:**Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:*";
P_HTM[3619]="*“Saṃsaggā vanatho jāto,**“Socializing promotes entanglement;*";
P_HTM[3620]="*asaṃsaggena chijjati;**they’re cut off by being aloof.*";
P_HTM[3621]="*Parittaṃ dārumāruyha,**If you’re lost in the middle of a great sea,*";
P_HTM[3622]="*yathā sīde mahaṇṇave.**and you clamber up on a little log, you’ll sink.*";
P_HTM[3623]="*Evaṃ kusītamāgamma,**So too, a person who lives well*";
P_HTM[3624]="*sādhujīvipi sīdati;**sinks by relying on a lazy person.*";
P_HTM[3625]="*Tasmā taṃ parivajjeyya,**Hence you should avoid such*";
P_HTM[3626]="*kusītaṃ hīnavīriyaṃ.**a lazy person who lacks energy.*";
P_HTM[3627]="*Pavivittehi ariyehi,**Dwell with the noble ones*";
P_HTM[3628]="*pahitattehi jhāyīhi;**who are secluded and determined*";
P_HTM[3629]="*Niccaṃ āraddhavīriyehi,**and always energetic;*";
P_HTM[3630]="*paṇḍitehi sahāvase”ti.**the astute who practice absorption.”*";
P_HTM[3631]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
