P_HTM[3916]="*(Sabbattha atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ kātabbaṃ.)**(All these should be treated in terms of the past, future, and present.)*";
P_HTM[3917]="*Asamāhitaṃ dussīlaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[3918]="*pañca sikkhāpadāni ca;* **";
P_HTM[3919]="*Satta kammapathā vuttā,* **";
P_HTM[3920]="*dasakammapathena ca;* **";
P_HTM[3921]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ aṭṭhaṅgiko vutto,* **";
P_HTM[3922]="*dasaṅgena ca sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3923]="*Kammapathavaggo tatiyo.* **";
P_HTM[3924]="*4. Kaḷārakhattiyavaggo**The Fourth Chapter*";
P_HTM[3925]="*1. Catudhātusuttaṃ**Four Elements*";
P_HTM[3926]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme …**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. …*";
P_HTM[3927]="*“catasso imā, bhikkhave, dhātuyo.**“Mendicants, there are these four elements.*";
P_HTM[3928]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[3929]="*Pathavīdhātu, āpodhātu, tejodhātu, vāyodhātu—**The elements of earth, water, fire, and air.*";
P_HTM[3930]="*imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso dhātuyo”ti.**These are the four elements.”*";
P_HTM[3931]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3932]="*2. Pubbesambodhasuttaṃ**Before Awakening*";
P_HTM[3933]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3934]="*“Pubbeva me, bhikkhave, sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato etadahosi:**“Mendicants, before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on awakening—I thought:*";
P_HTM[3935]="*‘ko nu kho pathavīdhātuyā assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇaṃ;**‘What’s the gratification, the drawback, and the escape when it comes to the earth element …*";
P_HTM[3936]="*ko āpodhātuyā assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇaṃ;**the water element …*";
P_HTM[3937]="*ko tejodhātuyā assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇaṃ;**the fire element …*";
P_HTM[3938]="*ko vāyodhātuyā assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇan’ti?**and the air element?’*";
P_HTM[3939]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me:*";
P_HTM[3940]="*‘yaṃ kho pathavīdhātuṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, ayaṃ pathavīdhātuyā assādo;**‘The pleasure and happiness that arise from the earth element: this is its gratification.*";
P_HTM[3941]="*yaṃ pathavīdhātu aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā, ayaṃ pathavīdhātuyā ādīnavo;**That the earth element is impermanent, suffering, and perishable: this is its drawback.*";
P_HTM[3942]="*yo pathavīdhātuyā chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ, idaṃ pathavīdhātuyā nissaraṇaṃ.**Removing and giving up desire and greed for the earth element: this is its escape.*";
P_HTM[3943]="*Yaṃ āpodhātuṃ paṭicca … pe …**The pleasure and happiness that arise from the water element …*";
P_HTM[3944]="*yaṃ tejodhātuṃ paṭicca … pe …**The pleasure and happiness that arise from the fire element …*";
P_HTM[3945]="*yaṃ vāyodhātuṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, ayaṃ vāyodhātuyā assādo;**The pleasure and happiness that arise from the air element: this is its gratification.*";
P_HTM[3946]="*yaṃ vāyodhātu aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā, ayaṃ vāyodhātuyā ādīnavo;**That the air element is impermanent, suffering, and perishable: this is its drawback.*";
P_HTM[3947]="*yo vāyodhātuyā chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ, idaṃ vāyodhātuyā nissaraṇaṃ’.**Removing and giving up desire and greed for the air element: this is its escape.*";
P_HTM[3948]="*Yāvakīvañcāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imāsaṃ catunnaṃ dhātūnaṃ evaṃ assādañca assādato ādīnavañca ādīnavato nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ na abbhaññāsiṃ, neva tāvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddhoti paccaññāsiṃ.**As long as I didn’t truly understand these four elements’ gratification, drawback, and escape in this way for what they are, I didn’t announce my supreme perfect awakening in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[3949]="*Yato ca khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imāsaṃ catunnaṃ dhātūnaṃ evaṃ assādañca assādato ādīnavañca ādīnavato nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, athāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddhoti paccaññāsiṃ.**But when I did truly understand these four elements’ gratification, drawback, and escape in this way for what they are, I announced my supreme perfect awakening in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[3950]="*Ñāṇañca pana me dassanaṃ udapādi:**Knowledge and vision arose in me:*";
P_HTM[3951]="*‘akuppā me vimutti, ayamantimā jāti, natthi dāni punabbhavo’”ti.**‘My freedom is unshakable; this is my last rebirth; now there are no more future lives.’”*";
P_HTM[3952]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3953]="*3. Acariṃsuttaṃ**In Search of Gratification*";
P_HTM[3954]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3955]="*“Pathavīdhātuyāhaṃ, bhikkhave, assādapariyesanaṃ acariṃ, yo pathavīdhātuyā assādo tadajjhagamaṃ, yāvatā pathavīdhātuyā assādo paññāya me so sudiṭṭho.**“Mendicants, I went in search of the earth element’s gratification, and I found it. I’ve seen clearly with wisdom the full extent of gratification in the earth element.*";
P_HTM[3956]="*Pathavīdhātuyāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ādīnavapariyesanaṃ acariṃ, yo pathavīdhātuyā ādīnavo tadajjhagamaṃ, yāvatā pathavīdhātuyā ādīnavo paññāya me so sudiṭṭho.**I went in search of the earth element’s drawback, and I found it. I’ve seen clearly with wisdom the full extent of the drawback in the earth element.*";
P_HTM[3957]="*Pathavīdhātuyāhaṃ, bhikkhave, nissaraṇapariyesanaṃ acariṃ, yaṃ pathavīdhātuyā nissaraṇaṃ tadajjhagamaṃ, yāvatā pathavīdhātuyā nissaraṇaṃ paññāya me taṃ sudiṭṭhaṃ.**I went in search of escape from the earth element, and I found it. I’ve seen clearly with wisdom the full extent of escape from the earth element.*";
P_HTM[3958]="*Āpodhātuyāhaṃ, bhikkhave … pe …**I went in search of the water element’s gratification …*";
P_HTM[3959]="*tejodhātuyāhaṃ, bhikkhave …**I went in search of the fire element’s gratification …*";
P_HTM[3960]="*vāyodhātuyāhaṃ, bhikkhave, assādapariyesanaṃ acariṃ, yo vāyodhātuyā assādo tadajjhagamaṃ, yāvatā vāyodhātuyā assādo paññāya me so sudiṭṭho.**I went in search of the air element’s gratification …*";
P_HTM[3961]="*Vāyodhātuyāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ādīnavapariyesanaṃ acariṃ, yo vāyodhātuyā ādīnavo tadajjhagamaṃ, yāvatā vāyodhātuyā ādīnavo paññāya me so sudiṭṭho.* **";
P_HTM[3962]="*Vāyodhātuyāhaṃ, bhikkhave, nissaraṇapariyesanaṃ acariṃ, yaṃ vāyodhātuyā nissaraṇaṃ tadajjhagamaṃ, yāvatā vāyodhātuyā nissaraṇaṃ paññāya me taṃ sudiṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3963]="*Yāvakīvañcāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imāsaṃ catunnaṃ dhātūnaṃ assādañca assādato ādīnavañca ādīnavato nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ na abbhaññāsiṃ, neva tāvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddhoti paccaññāsiṃ.**As long as I didn’t truly understand these four elements’ gratification, drawback, and escape for what they are, I didn’t announce my supreme perfect awakening in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[3964]="*Yato ca khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imāsaṃ catunnaṃ dhātūnaṃ assādañca assādato ādīnavañca ādīnavato nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, athāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddhoti paccaññāsiṃ.**But when I did truly understand the four elements’ gratification, drawback, and escape for what they are, I announced my supreme perfect awakening in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[3965]="*Ñāṇañca pana me dassanaṃ udapādi:**Knowledge and vision arose in me:*";
P_HTM[3966]="*‘akuppā me vimutti, ayamantimā jāti, natthi dāni punabbhavo’”ti.**‘My freedom is unshakable; this is my last rebirth; now there are no more future lives.’”*";
P_HTM[3967]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3968]="*4. Nocedaṃsuttaṃ**If There Was No*";
P_HTM[3969]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3970]="*“No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, pathavīdhātuyā assādo abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā pathavīdhātuyā sārajjeyyuṃ.**“Mendicants, if there were no gratification in the earth element, sentient beings wouldn’t love it.*";
P_HTM[3971]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi pathavīdhātuyā assādo, tasmā sattā pathavīdhātuyā sārajjanti.**But because there is gratification in the earth element, sentient beings do love it.*";
P_HTM[3972]="*No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, pathavīdhātuyā ādīnavo abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā pathavīdhātuyā nibbindeyyuṃ.**If the earth element had no drawback, sentient beings wouldn’t grow disillusioned with it.*";
P_HTM[3973]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi pathavīdhātuyā ādīnavo, tasmā sattā pathavīdhātuyā nibbindanti.**But because the earth element has a drawback, sentient beings do grow disillusioned with it.*";
P_HTM[3974]="*No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, pathavīdhātuyā nissaraṇaṃ abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā pathavīdhātuyā nissareyyuṃ.**If there were no escape from the earth element, sentient beings wouldn’t escape from it.*";
P_HTM[3975]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi pathavīdhātuyā nissaraṇaṃ, tasmā sattā pathavīdhātuyā nissaranti.**But because there is an escape from the earth element, sentient beings do escape from it.*";
P_HTM[3976]="*No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, āpodhātuyā assādo abhavissa … pe …**If there were no gratification in the water element …*";
P_HTM[3977]="*no cedaṃ, bhikkhave, tejodhātuyā … pe …**If there were no gratification in the fire element …*";
P_HTM[3978]="*no cedaṃ, bhikkhave, vāyodhātuyā assādo abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā vāyodhātuyā sārajjeyyuṃ.**If there were no gratification in the air element …*";
P_HTM[3979]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi vāyodhātuyā assādo, tasmā sattā vāyodhātuyā sārajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[3980]="*No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, vāyodhātuyā ādīnavo abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā vāyodhātuyā nibbindeyyuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3981]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi vāyodhātuyā ādīnavo, tasmā sattā vāyodhātuyā nibbindanti.* **";
P_HTM[3982]="*No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, vāyodhātuyā nissaraṇaṃ abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā vāyodhātuyā nissareyyuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3983]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi vāyodhātuyā nissaraṇaṃ, tasmā sattā vāyodhātuyā nissaranti.* **";
P_HTM[3984]="*Yāvakīvañcime, bhikkhave, sattā imāsaṃ catunnaṃ dhātūnaṃ assādañca assādato ādīnavañca ādīnavato nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ na abbhaññaṃsu, neva tāvime, bhikkhave, sattā sadevakā lokā samārakā sabrahmakā sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya nissaṭā visaṃyuttā vippamuttā vimariyādikatena cetasā vihariṃsu.**As long as sentient beings don’t truly understand these four elements’ gratification, drawback, and escape for what they are, they haven’t escaped from this world—with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans—and they don’t live detached, liberated, with a mind free of limits.*";
P_HTM[3985]="*Yato ca kho, bhikkhave, sattā imāsaṃ catunnaṃ dhātūnaṃ assādañca assādato ādīnavañca ādīnavato nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññaṃsu, atha, bhikkhave, sattā sadevakā lokā samārakā sabrahmakā sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya nissaṭā visaṃyuttā vippamuttā vimariyādikatena cetasā viharantī”ti.**But when sentient beings truly understand these four elements’ gratification, drawback, and escape for what they are, they’ve escaped from this world—with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans—and they live detached, liberated, with a mind free of limits.”*";
P_HTM[3986]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3987]="*5. Ekantadukkhasuttaṃ**Exclusively Painful*";
P_HTM[3988]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3989]="*“Pathavīdhātu ce hidaṃ, bhikkhave, ekantadukkhā abhavissa dukkhānupatitā dukkhāvakkantā anavakkantā sukhena, nayidaṃ sattā pathavīdhātuyā sārajjeyyuṃ.**“Mendicants, if the earth element were exclusively painful—soaked and steeped in pain and not steeped in pleasure—sentient beings wouldn’t love it.*";
P_HTM[3990]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, pathavīdhātu sukhā sukhānupatitā sukhāvakkantā anavakkantā dukkhena, tasmā sattā pathavīdhātuyā sārajjanti.**But because the earth element is pleasurable—soaked and steeped in pleasure and not steeped in pain—sentient beings do love it.*";
P_HTM[3991]="*Āpodhātu ce hidaṃ, bhikkhave … pe …**If the water element …*";
P_HTM[3992]="*tejodhātu ce hidaṃ, bhikkhave …**If the fire element …*";
P_HTM[3993]="*vāyodhātu ce hidaṃ, bhikkhave, ekantadukkhā abhavissa dukkhānupatitā dukkhāvakkantā anavakkantā sukhena, nayidaṃ sattā vāyodhātuyā sārajjeyyuṃ.**If the air element …*";
P_HTM[3994]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, vāyodhātu sukhā sukhānupatitā sukhāvakkantā anavakkantā dukkhena, tasmā sattā vāyodhātuyā sārajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[3995]="*Pathavīdhātu ce hidaṃ, bhikkhave, ekantasukhā abhavissa sukhānupatitā sukhāvakkantā anavakkantā dukkhena, nayidaṃ sattā pathavīdhātuyā nibbindeyyuṃ.**If the earth element were exclusively pleasurable—soaked and steeped in pleasure and not steeped in pain—sentient beings wouldn’t grow disillusioned with it.*";
P_HTM[3996]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, pathavīdhātu dukkhā dukkhānupatitā dukkhāvakkantā anavakkantā sukhena, tasmā sattā pathavīdhātuyā nibbindanti.**But because the earth element is painful—soaked and steeped in pain and not steeped in pleasure—sentient beings do grow disillusioned with it.*";
P_HTM[3997]="*Āpodhātu ce hidaṃ, bhikkhave … pe …**If the water element …*";
P_HTM[3998]="*tejodhātu ce hidaṃ, bhikkhave …**If the fire element …*";
P_HTM[3999]="*vāyodhātu ce hidaṃ, bhikkhave, ekantasukhā abhavissa sukhānupatitā sukhāvakkantā anavakkantā dukkhena, nayidaṃ sattā vāyodhātuyā nibbindeyyuṃ.**If the air element were exclusively pleasurable—soaked and steeped in pleasure and not steeped in pain—sentient beings wouldn’t grow disillusioned with it.*";
P_HTM[4000]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, vāyodhātu dukkhā dukkhānupatitā dukkhāvakkantā anavakkantā sukhena, tasmā sattā vāyodhātuyā nibbindantī”ti.**But because the air element is painful—soaked and steeped in pain and not steeped in pleasure—sentient beings do grow disillusioned with it.”*";
P_HTM[4001]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4002]="*6. Abhinandasuttaṃ**Taking Pleasure*";
P_HTM[4003]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4004]="*“Yo, bhikkhave, pathavīdhātuṃ abhinandati, dukkhaṃ so abhinandati.**“Mendicants, if you take pleasure in the earth element, you take pleasure in suffering.*";
P_HTM[4005]="*Yo dukkhaṃ abhinandati, aparimutto so dukkhasmāti vadāmi.**If you take pleasure in suffering, I say you’re not exempt from suffering.*";
P_HTM[4006]="*Yo āpodhātuṃ abhinandati … pe …**If you take pleasure in the water element …*";
P_HTM[4007]="*yo tejodhātuṃ …**If you take pleasure in the fire element …*";
P_HTM[4008]="*yo vāyodhātuṃ abhinandati, dukkhaṃ so abhinandati.**If you take pleasure in the air element, you take pleasure in suffering.*";
P_HTM[4009]="*Yo dukkhaṃ abhinandati, aparimutto so dukkhasmāti vadāmi.**If you take pleasure in suffering, I say you’re not exempt from suffering.*";
P_HTM[4010]="*Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, pathavīdhātuṃ nābhinandati, dukkhaṃ so nābhinandati.**If you don’t take pleasure in the earth element, you don’t take pleasure in suffering.*";
P_HTM[4011]="*Yo dukkhaṃ nābhinandati, parimutto so dukkhasmāti vadāmi.**If you don’t take pleasure in suffering, I say you’re exempt from suffering.*";
P_HTM[4012]="*Yo āpodhātuṃ … pe …**If you don’t take pleasure in the water element …*";
P_HTM[4013]="*yo tejodhātuṃ …**If you don’t take pleasure in the fire element …*";
P_HTM[4014]="*yo vāyodhātuṃ nābhinandati, dukkhaṃ so nābhinandati.**If you don’t take pleasure in the air element, you don’t take pleasure in suffering.*";
P_HTM[4015]="*Yo dukkhaṃ nābhinandati, parimutto so dukkhasmāti vadāmī”ti.**If you don’t take pleasure in suffering, I say you’re exempt from suffering.”*";
P_HTM[4016]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4017]="*7. Uppādasuttaṃ**Arising*";
P_HTM[4018]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4019]="*“Yo, bhikkhave, pathavīdhātuyā uppādo ṭhiti abhinibbatti pātubhāvo, dukkhasseso uppādo rogānaṃ ṭhiti jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo.**“Mendicants, the arising, continuation, rebirth, and manifestation of the earth element is the arising of suffering, the continuation of diseases, and the manifestation of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[4020]="*Yo āpodhātuyā … pe …**The arising, continuation, rebirth, and manifestation of the water element …*";
P_HTM[4021]="*yo tejodhātuyā …**The arising, continuation, rebirth, and manifestation of the fire element …*";
P_HTM[4022]="*yo vāyodhātuyā uppādo ṭhiti abhinibbatti pātubhāvo, dukkhasseso uppādo rogānaṃ ṭhiti jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo.**The arising, continuation, rebirth, and manifestation of the air element is the arising of suffering, the continuation of diseases, and the manifestation of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[4023]="*Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, pathavīdhātuyā nirodho vūpasamo atthaṅgamo, dukkhasseso nirodho rogānaṃ vūpasamo jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo.**The cessation, settling, and ending of the earth element is the cessation of suffering, the settling of diseases, and the ending of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[4024]="*Yo āpodhātuyā … pe …**The cessation, settling, and ending of the water element …*";
P_HTM[4025]="*yo tejodhātuyā …**The cessation, settling, and ending of the fire element …*";
P_HTM[4026]="*yo vāyodhātuyā nirodho vūpasamo atthaṅgamo, dukkhasseso nirodho rogānaṃ vūpasamo jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo”ti.**The cessation, settling, and ending of the air element is the cessation of suffering, the settling of diseases, and the ending of old age and death.”*";
P_HTM[4027]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4028]="*8. Samaṇabrāhmaṇasuttaṃ**Ascetics and Brahmins*";
P_HTM[4029]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4030]="*“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, dhātuyo.**“Mendicants, there are these four elements.*";
P_HTM[4031]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[4032]="*Pathavīdhātu, āpodhātu, tejodhātu, vāyodhātu.**The elements of earth, water, fire, and air.*";
P_HTM[4033]="*Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā imāsaṃ catunnaṃ dhātūnaṃ assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ nappajānanti,**There are ascetics and brahmins who don’t truly understand these four elements’ gratification, drawback, and escape for what they are.*";
P_HTM[4034]="*na me te, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā samaṇesu vā samaṇasammatā brāhmaṇesu vā brāhmaṇasammatā; na ca pana te āyasmanto sāmaññatthaṃ vā brahmaññatthaṃ vā diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharanti.**I don’t regard them as true ascetics and brahmins. Those venerables don’t realize the goal of life as an ascetic or brahmin, and don’t live having realized it with their own insight.*";
P_HTM[4035]="*Ye ca kho keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā imāsaṃ catunnaṃ dhātūnaṃ assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ pajānanti,**There are ascetics and brahmins who do truly understand these four elements’ gratification, drawback, and escape for what they are.*";
P_HTM[4036]="*te ca kho me, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā samaṇesu ceva samaṇasammatā brāhmaṇesu ca brāhmaṇasammatā; te ca panāyasmanto sāmaññatthañca brahmaññatthañca diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharantī”ti.**I regard them as true ascetics and brahmins. Those venerables realize the goal of life as an ascetic or brahmin, and live having realized it with their own insight.”*";
P_HTM[4037]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4038]="*9. Dutiyasamaṇabrāhmaṇasuttaṃ**Ascetics and Brahmins (2nd)*";
P_HTM[4039]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4040]="*“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, dhātuyo.**“Mendicants, there are these four elements.*";
P_HTM[4041]="*Katamā catasso?**What four?*";
P_HTM[4042]="*Pathavīdhātu, āpodhātu, tejodhātu, vāyodhātu.**The elements of earth, water, fire, and air.*";
P_HTM[4043]="*Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā imāsaṃ catunnaṃ dhātūnaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ nappajānanti … pe …**There are ascetics and brahmins who don’t truly understand these four elements’ origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape …*";
P_HTM[4044]="*(vitthāretabbaṃ) pajānanti … pe …**There are ascetics and brahmins who do truly understand these four elements’ origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape …”*";
P_HTM[4045]="*sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharantī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4046]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4047]="*10. Tatiyasamaṇabrāhmaṇasuttaṃ**Ascetics and Brahmins (3rd)*";
P_HTM[4048]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4049]="*“Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā pathavīdhātuṃ nappajānanti, pathavīdhātusamudayaṃ nappajānanti, pathavīdhātunirodhaṃ nappajānanti, pathavīdhātunirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ nappajānanti … pe …**“Mendicants, there are ascetics and brahmins who don’t understand the earth element, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation.*";
P_HTM[4050]="*āpodhātuṃ nappajānanti …**They don’t understand the water element …*";
P_HTM[4051]="*tejodhātuṃ nappajānanti …**fire element …*";
P_HTM[4052]="*vāyodhātuṃ nappajānanti, vāyodhātusamudayaṃ nappajānanti, vāyodhātunirodhaṃ nappajānanti, vāyodhātunirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ nappajānanti, na me te, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā samaṇesu vā samaṇasammatā brāhmaṇesu vā brāhmaṇasammatā;**air element …*";
P_HTM[4053]="*na ca pana te āyasmanto sāmaññatthaṃ vā brahmaññatthaṃ vā diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharanti.**Those venerables don’t realize the goal of life as an ascetic or brahmin, and don’t live having realized it with their own insight.*";
P_HTM[4054]="*Ye ca kho keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā pathavīdhātuṃ pajānanti, pathavīdhātusamudayaṃ pajānanti, pathavīdhātunirodhaṃ pajānanti, pathavīdhātunirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ pajānanti …**There are ascetics and brahmins who do understand the earth element, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation.*";
P_HTM[4055]="*ye ca kho keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā … pe … āpodhātuṃ pajānanti …**They do understand the water element …*";
P_HTM[4056]="*tejodhātuṃ pajānanti …**the fire element …*";
P_HTM[4057]="*vāyodhātuṃ pajānanti, vāyodhātusamudayaṃ pajānanti, vāyodhātunirodhaṃ pajānanti, vāyodhātunirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ pajānanti, te ca kho me, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā samaṇesu ceva samaṇasammatā brāhmaṇesu ca brāhmaṇasammatā;**the air element …*";
P_HTM[4058]="*te ca panāyasmanto sāmaññatthañca brahmaññatthañca diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharantī”ti.**Those venerables realize the goal of life as an ascetic or brahmin, and live having realized it with their own insight.”*";
P_HTM[4059]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4060]="*Catuttho vaggo.* **";
P_HTM[4061]="*Catasso pubbe acariṃ,* **";
P_HTM[4062]="*nocedañca dukkhena ca;* **";
P_HTM[4063]="*Abhinandañca uppādo,* **";
P_HTM[4064]="*tayo samaṇabrāhmaṇāti.* **";
P_HTM[4065]="*Dhātusaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ.**The Linked Discourses on the elements are complete.*";
P_HTM[4066]="*15. Anamataggasaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[4067]="*1. Buddhavaggo**The First Chapter*";
P_HTM[4068]="*1. Tiṇakaṭṭhasuttaṃ**Grass and Sticks*";
P_HTM[4069]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[4070]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[4071]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[4072]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[4073]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[4074]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[4075]="*“Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro.**“Mendicants, transmigration has no known beginning.*";
P_HTM[4076]="*Pubbā koṭi na paññāyati avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ.**No first point is found of sentient beings roaming and transmigrating, hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving.*";
P_HTM[4077]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso yaṃ imasmiṃ jambudīpe tiṇakaṭṭhasākhāpalāsaṃ taṃ chetvā ekajjhaṃ saṃharitvā caturaṅgulaṃ caturaṅgulaṃ ghaṭikaṃ katvā nikkhipeyya:**Suppose a person was to strip all the grass, sticks, branches, and leaves in India, gather them together into one pile, and chop them each into four inch pieces. They’d lay them down, saying:*";
P_HTM[4078]="*‘ayaṃ me mātā, tassā me mātu ayaṃ mātā’ti, apariyādinnāva, bhikkhave, tassa purisassa mātumātaro assu, atha imasmiṃ jambudīpe tiṇakaṭṭhasākhāpalāsaṃ parikkhayaṃ pariyādānaṃ gaccheyya.**‘This is my mother, this is my grandmother.’ The grass, sticks, branches, and leaves of India would run out before that person’s mothers and grandmothers.*";
P_HTM[4079]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[4080]="*Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro.**Transmigration has no known beginning.*";
P_HTM[4081]="*Pubbā koṭi na paññāyati avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ.**No first point is found of sentient beings roaming and transmigrating, hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving.*";
P_HTM[4082]="*Evaṃ dīgharattaṃ vo, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ tibbaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ byasanaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ, kaṭasī vaḍḍhitā.**For such a long time you have undergone suffering, agony, and disaster, swelling the cemeteries.*";
P_HTM[4083]="*Yāvañcidaṃ, bhikkhave, alameva sabbasaṅkhāresu nibbindituṃ alaṃ virajjituṃ alaṃ vimuccitun”ti.**This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.”*";
P_HTM[4084]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4085]="*2. Pathavīsuttaṃ**The Earth*";
P_HTM[4086]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4087]="*“Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro.**“Mendicants, transmigration has no known beginning.*";
P_HTM[4088]="*Pubbā koṭi na paññāyati avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ.**No first point is found of sentient beings roaming and transmigrating, hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving.*";
P_HTM[4089]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso imaṃ mahāpathaviṃ kolaṭṭhimattaṃ kolaṭṭhimattaṃ mattikāguḷikaṃ karitvā nikkhipeyya:**Suppose a person was to make the whole earth into clay balls the size of jujube seeds. They’d lay them down, saying:*";
P_HTM[4090]="*‘ayaṃ me pitā, tassa me pitu ayaṃ pitā’ti, apariyādinnāva bhikkhave, tassa purisassa pitupitaro assu, athāyaṃ mahāpathavī parikkhayaṃ pariyādānaṃ gaccheyya.**‘This is my father, this is my grandfather.’ The whole earth would run out before that person’s fathers and grandfathers.*";
P_HTM[4091]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[4092]="*Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro.**Transmigration has no known beginning.*";
P_HTM[4093]="*Pubbā koṭi na paññāyati avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ.**No first point is found of sentient beings roaming and transmigrating, hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving.*";
P_HTM[4094]="*Evaṃ dīgharattaṃ vo, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ tibbaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ byasanaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ, kaṭasī vaḍḍhitā.**For such a long time you have undergone suffering, agony, and disaster, swelling the cemeteries.*";
P_HTM[4095]="*Yāvañcidaṃ, bhikkhave, alameva sabbasaṅkhāresu nibbindituṃ, alaṃ virajjituṃ, alaṃ vimuccitun”ti.**This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.”*";
P_HTM[4096]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4097]="*3. Assusuttaṃ**Tears*";
P_HTM[4098]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4099]="*“Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro.**“Mendicants, transmigration has no known beginning.*";
P_HTM[4100]="*Pubbā koṭi na paññāyati avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ.**No first point is found of sentient beings roaming and transmigrating, hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving.*";
P_HTM[4101]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ, yaṃ vā vo iminā dīghena addhunā sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ amanāpasampayogā manāpavippayogā kandantānaṃ rodantānaṃ assu passannaṃ paggharitaṃ, yaṃ vā catūsu mahāsamuddesu udakan”ti?**What do you think? Which is more: the flow of tears you’ve shed while roaming and transmigrating for such a very long time—weeping and wailing from being united with the unloved and separated from the loved—or the water in the four oceans?”*";
P_HTM[4102]="*“Yathā kho mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāma, etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ yaṃ no iminā dīghena addhunā sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ amanāpasampayogā manāpavippayogā kandantānaṃ rodantānaṃ assu passannaṃ paggharitaṃ, na tveva catūsu mahāsamuddesu udakan”ti.**“As we understand the Buddha’s teaching, the flow of tears we’ve shed while roaming and transmigrating is more than the water in the four oceans.”*";
P_HTM[4103]="*“Sādhu sādhu, bhikkhave, sādhu kho me tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānātha.**“Good, good, mendicants! It’s good that you understand my teaching like this.*";
P_HTM[4104]="*Etadeva, bhikkhave, bahutaraṃ yaṃ vo iminā dīghena addhunā sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ amanāpasampayogā manāpavippayogā kandantānaṃ rodantānaṃ assu passannaṃ paggharitaṃ, na tveva catūsu mahāsamuddesu udakaṃ.**The flow of tears you’ve shed while roaming and transmigrating is indeed more than the water in the four oceans.*";
P_HTM[4105]="*Dīgharattaṃ vo, bhikkhave, mātumaraṇaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ;**For a long time you’ve undergone the death of a mother …*";
P_HTM[4106]="*tesaṃ vo mātumaraṇaṃ paccanubhontānaṃ amanāpasampayogā manāpavippayogā kandantānaṃ rodantānaṃ assu passannaṃ paggharitaṃ, na tveva catūsu mahāsamuddesu udakaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4107]="*Dīgharattaṃ vo, bhikkhave, pitumaraṇaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ … pe …**father …*";
P_HTM[4108]="*bhātumaraṇaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ …**brother …*";
P_HTM[4109]="*bhaginimaraṇaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ …**sister …*";
P_HTM[4110]="*puttamaraṇaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ …**son …*";
P_HTM[4111]="*dhītumaraṇaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ …**daughter …*";
P_HTM[4112]="*ñātibyasanaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ …**loss of relatives …*";
P_HTM[4113]="*bhogabyasanaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ.**loss of wealth …*";
P_HTM[4114]="*Dīgharattaṃ vo, bhikkhave, rogabyasanaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ, tesaṃ vo rogabyasanaṃ paccanubhontānaṃ amanāpasampayogā manāpavippayogā kandantānaṃ rodantānaṃ assu passannaṃ paggharitaṃ, na tveva catūsu mahāsamuddesu udakaṃ.**or loss through illness. From being united with the unloved and separated from the loved, the flow of tears you’ve shed while roaming and transmigrating is indeed more than the water in the four oceans.*";
P_HTM[4115]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[4116]="*Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro … pe …**Transmigration has no known beginning. …*";
P_HTM[4117]="*yāvañcidaṃ, bhikkhave, alameva sabbasaṅkhāresu nibbindituṃ, alaṃ virajjituṃ, alaṃ vimuccitun”ti.**This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.”*";
P_HTM[4118]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4119]="*4. Khīrasuttaṃ**Mother’s Milk*";
P_HTM[4120]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4121]="*“Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro.**“Mendicants, transmigration has no known beginning.*";
P_HTM[4122]="*Pubbā koṭi na paññāyati avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ.**No first point is found of sentient beings roaming and transmigrating, hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving.*";
P_HTM[4123]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ, yaṃ vā vo iminā dīghena addhunā sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ mātuthaññaṃ pītaṃ, yaṃ vā catūsu mahāsamuddesu udakan”ti?**What do you think? Which is more: the mother’s milk you’ve drunk while roaming and transmigrating for such a very long time, or the water in the four oceans?”*";
P_HTM[4124]="*“Yathā kho mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāma, etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ yaṃ no iminā dīghena addhunā sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ mātuthaññaṃ pītaṃ, na tveva catūsu mahāsamuddesu udakan”ti.**“As we understand the Buddha’s teaching, the mother’s milk we’ve drunk while roaming and transmigrating is more than the water in the four oceans.”*";
P_HTM[4125]="*“Sādhu sādhu, bhikkhave, sādhu kho me tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānātha.**“Good, good, mendicants! It’s good that you understand my teaching like this.*";
P_HTM[4126]="*Etadeva, bhikkhave, bahutaraṃ yaṃ vo iminā dīghena addhunā sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ mātuthaññaṃ pītaṃ, na tveva catūsu mahāsamuddesu udakaṃ.**The mother’s milk you’ve drunk while roaming and transmigrating for such a very long time is more than the water in the four oceans.*";
P_HTM[4127]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[4128]="*Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro … pe …**Transmigration has no known beginning. …*";
P_HTM[4129]="*alaṃ vimuccitun”ti.**This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.”*";
P_HTM[4130]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4131]="*5. Pabbatasuttaṃ**A Mountain*";
P_HTM[4132]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati … pe … ārāme … pe ….**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4133]="*Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and asked him,*";
P_HTM[4134]="*“kīvadīgho nu kho, bhante, kappo”ti?**“Sir, how long is an eon?”*";
P_HTM[4135]="*“Dīgho kho, bhikkhu, kappo.**“Mendicant, an eon is long.*";
P_HTM[4136]="*So na sukaro saṅkhātuṃ ettakāni vassāni iti vā, ettakāni vassasatāni iti vā, ettakāni vassasahassāni iti vā, ettakāni vassasatasahassāni iti vā”ti.**It’s not easy to calculate how many years, how many hundreds or thousands or hundreds of thousands of years it lasts.”*";
P_HTM[4137]="*“Sakkā pana, bhante, upamaṃ kātun”ti?**“But sir, is it possible to give a simile?”*";
P_HTM[4138]="*“Sakkā, bhikkhū”ti bhagavā avoca.**“It’s possible,” said the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4139]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhu, mahāselo pabbato yojanaṃ āyāmena yojanaṃ vitthārena yojanaṃ ubbedhena acchinno asusiro ekagghano.**“Suppose there was a huge stone mountain, a league long, a league wide, and a league high, with no cracks or holes, one solid mass.*";
P_HTM[4140]="*Tamenaṃ puriso vassasatassa vassasatassa accayena kāsikena vatthena sakiṃ sakiṃ parimajjeyya.**And as each century passed someone would stroke it with a fine cloth from Kāsī.*";
P_HTM[4141]="*Khippataraṃ kho so, bhikkhu, mahāselo pabbato iminā upakkamena parikkhayaṃ pariyādānaṃ gaccheyya, na tveva kappo.**By this means the huge stone mountain would be worn away before the eon comes to an end.*";
P_HTM[4142]="*Evaṃ dīgho, bhikkhu, kappo.**That’s how long an eon is.*";
P_HTM[4143]="*Evaṃ dīghānaṃ kho, bhikkhu, kappānaṃ neko kappo saṃsito, nekaṃ kappasataṃ saṃsitaṃ, nekaṃ kappasahassaṃ saṃsitaṃ, nekaṃ kappasatasahassaṃ saṃsitaṃ.**And we’ve transmigrated through many such eons, many hundreds, many thousands, many hundreds of thousands.*";
P_HTM[4144]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[4145]="*Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhu, saṃsāro.**Transmigration has no known beginning. …*";
P_HTM[4146]="*Pubbā koṭi … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4147]="*yāvañcidaṃ, bhikkhu, alameva sabbasaṅkhāresu nibbindituṃ, alaṃ virajjituṃ, alaṃ vimuccitun”ti.**This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.”*";
P_HTM[4148]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4149]="*6. Sāsapasuttaṃ**A Mustard Seed*";
P_HTM[4150]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4151]="*Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha … and asked him,*";
P_HTM[4152]="*“kīvadīgho nu kho, bhante, kappo”ti?**“Sir, how long is an eon?”*";
P_HTM[4153]="*“Dīgho kho, bhikkhu, kappo.**“Mendicant, an eon is long.*";
P_HTM[4154]="*So na sukaro saṅkhātuṃ ettakāni vassāni iti vā … pe … ettakāni vassasatasahassāni iti vā”ti.**It’s not easy to calculate how many years, how many hundreds or thousands or hundreds of thousands of years it lasts.”*";
P_HTM[4155]="*“Sakkā pana, bhante, upamaṃ kātun”ti?**“But sir, is it possible to give a simile?”*";
P_HTM[4156]="*“Sakkā, bhikkhū”ti bhagavā avoca.**“It’s possible,” said the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4157]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhu, āyasaṃ nagaraṃ yojanaṃ āyāmena yojanaṃ vitthārena yojanaṃ ubbedhena, puṇṇaṃ sāsapānaṃ guḷikābaddhaṃ.**“Suppose there was an iron city, a league long, a league wide, and a league high, full of mustard seeds pressed into balls.*";
P_HTM[4158]="*Tato puriso vassasatassa vassasatassa accayena ekamekaṃ sāsapaṃ uddhareyya.**And as each century passed someone would remove a single mustard seed.*";
P_HTM[4159]="*Khippataraṃ kho so, bhikkhu, mahāsāsaparāsi iminā upakkamena parikkhayaṃ pariyādānaṃ gaccheyya, na tveva kappo.**By this means the huge heap of mustard seeds would be used up before the eon comes to an end.*";
P_HTM[4160]="*Evaṃ dīgho kho, bhikkhu, kappo.**That’s how long an eon is.*";
P_HTM[4161]="*Evaṃ dīghānaṃ kho, bhikkhu, kappānaṃ neko kappo saṃsito, nekaṃ kappasataṃ saṃsitaṃ, nekaṃ kappasahassaṃ saṃsitaṃ, nekaṃ kappasatasahassaṃ saṃsitaṃ.**And we’ve transmigrated through many such eons, many hundreds, many thousands, many hundreds of thousands.*";
P_HTM[4162]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[4163]="*Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhu, saṃsāro … pe …**Transmigration has no known beginning. …*";
P_HTM[4164]="*alaṃ vimuccitun”ti.**This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.”*";
P_HTM[4165]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4166]="*7. Sāvakasuttaṃ**Disciples*";
P_HTM[4167]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4168]="*Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then several mendicants went up to the Buddha … and asked him,*";
P_HTM[4169]="*“kīvabahukā nu kho, bhante, kappā abbhatītā atikkantā”ti?**“Sir, how many eons have passed?”*";
P_HTM[4170]="*“Bahukā kho, bhikkhave, kappā abbhatītā atikkantā.**“Mendicants, many eons have passed.*";
P_HTM[4171]="*Te na sukarā saṅkhātuṃ:**It’s not easy to calculate*";
P_HTM[4172]="*‘ettakā kappā iti vā, ettakāni kappasatāni iti vā, ettakāni kappasahassāni iti vā, ettakāni kappasatasahassāni iti vā’”ti.**how many eons have passed, how many hundreds or thousands or hundreds of thousands of eons.”*";
P_HTM[4173]="*“Sakkā pana, bhante, upamaṃ kātun”ti?**“But sir, is it possible to give a simile?”*";
P_HTM[4174]="*“Sakkā, bhikkhave”ti bhagavā avoca.**“It’s possible,” said the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4175]="*“Idhassu, bhikkhave, cattāro sāvakā vassasatāyukā vassasatajīvino.**“Suppose there were four disciples with a lifespan of a hundred years.*";
P_HTM[4176]="*Te divase divase kappasatasahassaṃ kappasatasahassaṃ anussareyyuṃ.**And each day they would each recollect a hundred thousand eons.*";
P_HTM[4177]="*Ananussaritāva, bhikkhave, tehi kappā assu, atha kho te cattāro sāvakā vassasatāyukā vassasatajīvino vassasatassa accayena kālaṃ kareyyuṃ.**Those four disciples would pass away after a hundred years and there would still be eons that they haven’t recollected.*";
P_HTM[4178]="*Evaṃ bahukā kho, bhikkhave, kappā abbhatītā atikkantā.**That’s how many eons have passed.*";
P_HTM[4179]="*Te na sukarā saṅkhātuṃ:**It’s not easy to calculate*";
P_HTM[4180]="*‘ettakā kappā iti vā, ettakāni kappasatāni iti vā, ettakāni kappasahassāni iti vā, ettakāni kappasatasahassāni iti vā’ti.**how many eons have passed, how many hundreds or thousands or hundreds of thousands of eons.*";
P_HTM[4181]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[4182]="*Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro … pe …**Transmigration has no known beginning. …*";
P_HTM[4183]="*alaṃ vimuccitun”ti.**This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.”*";
P_HTM[4184]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4185]="*8. Gaṅgāsuttaṃ**The Ganges*";
P_HTM[4186]="*Rājagahe viharati veḷuvane.**Near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove.*";
P_HTM[4187]="*Atha kho aññataro brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then a certain brahmin went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4188]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and asked the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[4189]="*“kīvabahukā nu kho, bho gotama, kappā abbhatītā atikkantā”ti?**“Sir, how many eons have passed?”*";
P_HTM[4190]="*“Bahukā kho, brāhmaṇa, kappā abbhatītā atikkantā.**“Brahmin, many eons have passed.*";
P_HTM[4191]="*Te na sukarā saṅkhātuṃ:**It’s not easy to calculate*";
P_HTM[4192]="*‘ettakā kappā iti vā, ettakāni kappasatāni iti vā, ettakāni kappasahassāni iti vā, ettakāni kappasatasahassāni iti vā’”ti.**how many eons have passed, how many hundreds or thousands or hundreds of thousands of eons.”*";
P_HTM[4193]="*“Sakkā pana, bho gotama, upamaṃ kātun”ti?**“But sir, can you give a simile?”*";
P_HTM[4194]="*“Sakkā, brāhmaṇā”ti bhagavā avoca.**“I can,” said the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4195]="*“Seyyathāpi, brāhmaṇa, yato cāyaṃ gaṅgā nadī pabhavati yattha ca mahāsamuddaṃ appeti, yā etasmiṃ antare vālikā sā na sukarā saṅkhātuṃ:**“Consider the Ganges river from where it originates to where it enters the ocean. Between these places it’s not easy to calculate*";
P_HTM[4196]="*‘ettakā vālikā iti vā, ettakāni vālikasatāni iti vā, ettakāni vālikasahassāni iti vā, ettakāni vālikasatasahassāni iti vā’ti.**how many grains of sand there are, how many hundreds or thousands or hundreds of thousands of grains of sand.*";
P_HTM[4197]="*Tato bahutarā kho, brāhmaṇa, kappā abbhatītā atikkantā.**The eons that have passed are more than this.*";
P_HTM[4198]="*Te na sukarā saṅkhātuṃ:**It’s not easy to calculate*";
P_HTM[4199]="*‘ettakā kappā iti vā, ettakāni kappasatāni iti vā, ettakāni kappasahassāni iti vā, ettakāni kappasatasahassāni iti vā’ti.**how many eons have passed, how many hundreds or thousands or hundreds of thousands of eons.*";
P_HTM[4200]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[4201]="*Anamataggoyaṃ, brāhmaṇa, saṃsāro.**Transmigration has no known beginning.*";
P_HTM[4202]="*Pubbā koṭi na paññāyati avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ.**No first point is found of sentient beings roaming and transmigrating, hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving.*";
P_HTM[4203]="*Evaṃ dīgharattaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, dukkhaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ tibbaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ byasanaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ, kaṭasī vaḍḍhitā.**For such a long time you have undergone suffering, agony, and disaster, swelling the cemeteries.*";
P_HTM[4204]="*Yāvañcidaṃ, brāhmaṇa, alameva sabbasaṅkhāresu nibbindituṃ, alaṃ virajjituṃ, alaṃ vimuccitun”ti.**This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.”*";
P_HTM[4205]="*Evaṃ vutte, so brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, the brahmin said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[4206]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe …**“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent! …*";
P_HTM[4207]="*upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[4208]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4209]="*9. Daṇḍasuttaṃ**A Stick*";
P_HTM[4210]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4211]="*“Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro.**“Mendicants, transmigration has no known beginning.*";
P_HTM[4212]="*Pubbā koṭi na paññāyati avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ.**No first point is found of sentient beings roaming and transmigrating, hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving.*";
P_HTM[4213]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, daṇḍo uparivehāsaṃ khitto sakimpi mūlena nipatati, sakimpi majjhena nipatati, sakimpi antena nipatati;**Suppose a stick was tossed up in the air. Sometimes it’d fall on its bottom, sometimes the middle, and sometimes the top.*";
P_HTM[4214]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, avijjānīvaraṇā sattā taṇhāsaṃyojanā sandhāvantā saṃsarantā sakimpi asmā lokā paraṃ lokaṃ gacchanti, sakimpi parasmā lokā imaṃ lokaṃ āgacchanti.**It’s the same for sentient beings roaming and transmigrating, hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving. Sometimes they go from this world to the other world, and sometimes they come from the other world to this world.*";
P_HTM[4215]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[4216]="*Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro … pe …**Transmigration has no known beginning. …*";
P_HTM[4217]="*alaṃ vimuccitun”ti.**This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.”*";
P_HTM[4218]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4219]="*10. Puggalasuttaṃ**A Single Person*";
P_HTM[4220]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain.*";
P_HTM[4221]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[4222]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[4223]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[4224]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[4225]="*“Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro … pe …**“Mendicants, transmigration has no known beginning. …*";
P_HTM[4226]="*ekapuggalassa, bhikkhave, kappaṃ sandhāvato saṃsarato siyā evaṃ mahā aṭṭhikaṅkalo aṭṭhipuñjo aṭṭhirāsi yathāyaṃ vepullo pabbato, sace saṃhārako assa, sambhatañca na vinasseyya.**One person roaming and transmigrating for an eon would amass a heap of bones the size of this Mount Vepulla, if they were gathered together and not lost.*";
P_HTM[4227]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[4228]="*Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro … pe …**Transmigration has no known beginning. …*";
P_HTM[4229]="*alaṃ vimuccitun”ti.**This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.”*";
P_HTM[4230]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[4231]="*Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:**Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:*";
P_HTM[4232]="*“Ekassekena kappena,**“If the bones of a single person*";
P_HTM[4233]="*puggalassaṭṭhisañcayo;**for a single eon were gathered up,*";
P_HTM[4234]="*Siyā pabbatasamo rāsi,**they’d make a pile the size of a mountain:*";
P_HTM[4235]="*iti vuttaṃ mahesinā.**so said the great hermit.*";
P_HTM[4236]="*So kho panāyaṃ akkhāto,**And this is declared to be*";
P_HTM[4237]="*vepullo pabbato mahā;**as huge as Mount Vepulla,*";
P_HTM[4238]="*Uttaro gijjhakūṭassa,**higher than the Vulture’s Peak*";
P_HTM[4239]="*magadhānaṃ giribbaje.**in the Magadhan mountain range.*";
P_HTM[4240]="*Yato ca ariyasaccāni,**But then, with right understanding,*";
P_HTM[4241]="*sammappaññāya passati;**a person sees the noble truths—*";
P_HTM[4242]="*Dukkhaṃ dukkhasamuppādaṃ,**suffering, suffering’s origin,*";
P_HTM[4243]="*dukkhassa ca atikkamaṃ;**suffering’s transcendence,*";
P_HTM[4244]="*Ariyaṃ caṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ,**and the noble eightfold path*";
P_HTM[4245]="*dukkhūpasamagāminaṃ.**that leads to the stilling of suffering.*";
P_HTM[4246]="*Sa sattakkhattuṃparamaṃ,**After roaming on seven times at most,*";
P_HTM[4247]="*sandhāvitvāna puggalo;**that person*";
P_HTM[4248]="*Dukkhassantakaro hoti,**makes an end of suffering,*";
P_HTM[4249]="*sabbasaṃyojanakkhayā”ti.**with the ending of all fetters.”*";
P_HTM[4250]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4251]="*Paṭhamo vaggo.* **";
P_HTM[4252]="*Tiṇakaṭṭhañca pathavī,* **";
P_HTM[4253]="*assu khīrañca pabbataṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4254]="*Sāsapā sāvakā gaṅgā,* **";
P_HTM[4255]="*daṇḍo ca puggalena cāti.* **";
P_HTM[4256]="*2. Āhāravaggo**The Second Chapter*";
P_HTM[4257]="*1. Duggatasuttaṃ**In a Sorry State*";
P_HTM[4258]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4259]="*Tatra kho … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4260]="*“Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro.**“Mendicants, transmigration has no known beginning.*";
P_HTM[4261]="*Pubbā koṭi na paññāyati avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ.**No first point is found of sentient beings roaming and transmigrating, hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving.*";
P_HTM[4262]="*Yaṃ, bhikkhave, passeyyātha duggataṃ durūpetaṃ niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:**When you see someone in a sorry state, in distress, you should conclude:*";
P_HTM[4263]="*‘amhehipi evarūpaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ iminā dīghena addhunā’ti.**‘In all this long time, we too have undergone the same thing.’*";
P_HTM[4264]="*Taṃ kissa hetu … pe …**Why is that? Transmigration has no known beginning. …*";
P_HTM[4265]="*yāvañcidaṃ, bhikkhave, alameva sabbasaṅkhāresu nibbindituṃ alaṃ virajjituṃ alaṃ vimuccitun”ti.**This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.”*";
P_HTM[4266]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4267]="*2. Sukhitasuttaṃ**In a Good Way*";
P_HTM[4268]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4269]="*“Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro … pe …**“Mendicants, transmigration has no known beginning. …*";
P_HTM[4270]="*yaṃ, bhikkhave, passeyyātha sukhitaṃ susajjitaṃ, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:**When you see someone in a good way, in a happy state, you should conclude:*";
P_HTM[4271]="*‘amhehipi evarūpaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ iminā dīghena addhunā’ti.**‘In all this long time, we too have undergone the same thing.’*";
P_HTM[4272]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[4273]="*Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro.**Transmigration has no known beginning. …*";
P_HTM[4274]="*Pubbā koṭi na paññāyati … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4275]="*alaṃ vimuccitun”ti.**This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.”*";
P_HTM[4276]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4277]="*3. Tiṃsamattasuttaṃ**Thirty Mendicants*";
P_HTM[4278]="*Rājagahe viharati veḷuvane.**Near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove.*";
P_HTM[4279]="*Atha kho tiṃsamattā pāveyyakā bhikkhū sabbe āraññikā sabbe piṇḍapātikā sabbe paṃsukūlikā sabbe tecīvarikā sabbe sasaṃyojanā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu.**Then thirty mendicants from Pāvā went to the Buddha. All of them lived in the wilderness, ate only alms-food, wore rag robes, and owned just three robes; yet they all still had fetters. They bowed to the Buddha and sat down to one side.*";
P_HTM[4280]="*Atha kho bhagavato etadahosi:**Then it occurred to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[4281]="*“ime kho tiṃsamattā pāveyyakā bhikkhū sabbe āraññikā sabbe piṇḍapātikā sabbe paṃsukūlikā sabbe tecīvarikā sabbe sasaṃyojanā.**“These thirty mendicants from Pāvā live in the wilderness, eat only alms-food, wear rag robes, and own just three robes; yet they all still have fetters.*";
P_HTM[4282]="*Yannūnāhaṃ imesaṃ tathā dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ yathā nesaṃ imasmiṃyeva āsane anupādāya āsavehi cittāni vimucceyyun”ti.**Why don’t I teach them the Dhamma in such a way that their minds are freed from defilements by not grasping while sitting in this very seat?”*";
P_HTM[4283]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[4284]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[4285]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[4286]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[4287]="*“Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro.**“Mendicants, transmigration has no known beginning.*";
P_HTM[4288]="*Pubbā koṭi na paññāyati avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ.**No first point is found of sentient beings roaming and transmigrating, hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving.*";
P_HTM[4289]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ, yaṃ vā vo iminā dīghena addhunā sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ sīsacchinnānaṃ lohitaṃ passannaṃ paggharitaṃ, yaṃ vā catūsu mahāsamuddesu udakan”ti?**What do you think? Which is more: the flow of blood you’ve shed when your head was chopped off while roaming and transmigrating for such a very long time, or the water in the four oceans?”*";
P_HTM[4290]="*“Yathā kho mayaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāma, etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ, yaṃ no iminā dīghena addhunā sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ sīsacchinnānaṃ lohitaṃ passannaṃ paggharitaṃ, na tveva catūsu mahāsamuddesu udakan”ti.**“As we understand the Buddha’s teaching, the flow of blood we’ve shed when our head was chopped off while roaming and transmigrating is more than the water in the four oceans.”*";
P_HTM[4291]="*“Sādhu sādhu, bhikkhave, sādhu kho me tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānātha.**“Good, good, mendicants! It’s good that you understand my teaching like this.*";
P_HTM[4292]="*Etadeva, bhikkhave, bahutaraṃ, yaṃ vo iminā dīghena addhunā sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ sīsacchinnānaṃ lohitaṃ passannaṃ paggharitaṃ, na tveva catūsu mahāsamuddesu udakaṃ.**The flow of blood you’ve shed when your head was chopped off while roaming and transmigrating is indeed more than the water in the four oceans.*";
P_HTM[4293]="*Dīgharattaṃ vo, bhikkhave, gunnaṃ sataṃ gobhūtānaṃ sīsacchinnānaṃ lohitaṃ passannaṃ paggharitaṃ, na tveva catūsu mahāsamuddesu udakaṃ.**For a long time you’ve been cows, and the flow of blood you’ve shed when your head was chopped off as a cow is more than the water in the four oceans.*";
P_HTM[4294]="*Dīgharattaṃ vo, bhikkhave, mahiṃsānaṃ sataṃ mahiṃsabhūtānaṃ sīsacchinnānaṃ lohitaṃ passannaṃ paggharitaṃ … pe …**For a long time you’ve been buffalo …*";
P_HTM[4295]="*dīgharattaṃ vo, bhikkhave, urabbhānaṃ sataṃ urabbhabhūtānaṃ … pe …**rams …*";
P_HTM[4296]="*ajānaṃ sataṃ ajabhūtānaṃ …**goats …*";
P_HTM[4297]="*migānaṃ sataṃ migabhūtānaṃ …**deer …*";
P_HTM[4298]="*kukkuṭānaṃ sataṃ kukkuṭabhūtānaṃ …**chickens …*";
P_HTM[4299]="*sūkarānaṃ sataṃ sūkarabhūtānaṃ …**pigs …*";
P_HTM[4300]="*dīgharattaṃ vo, bhikkhave, corā gāmaghātāti gahetvā sīsacchinnānaṃ lohitaṃ passannaṃ paggharitaṃ.**For a long time you’ve been bandits, arrested for raiding villages,*";
P_HTM[4301]="*Dīgharattaṃ vo, bhikkhave, corā pāripanthikāti gahetvā sīsacchinnānaṃ lohitaṃ passannaṃ paggharitaṃ.**highway robbery,*";
P_HTM[4302]="*Dīgharattaṃ vo, bhikkhave, corā pāradārikāti gahetvā sīsacchinnānaṃ lohitaṃ passannaṃ paggharitaṃ, na tveva catūsu mahāsamuddesu udakaṃ.**or adultery. And the flow of blood you’ve shed when your head was chopped off as a bandit is more than the water in the four oceans.*";
P_HTM[4303]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[4304]="*Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro … pe …**Transmigration has no known beginning. …*";
P_HTM[4305]="*alaṃ vimuccitun”ti.**This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.”*";
P_HTM[4306]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[4307]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[4308]="*Imasmiñca pana veyyākaraṇasmiṃ bhaññamāne tiṃsamattānaṃ pāveyyakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ anupādāya āsavehi cittāni vimucciṃsūti.**And while this discourse was being spoken, the minds of the thirty mendicants from Pāvā were freed from defilements by not grasping.*";
P_HTM[4309]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4310]="*4. Mātusuttaṃ**Mother*";
P_HTM[4311]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4312]="*“Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro … pe …**“Mendicants, transmigration has no known beginning. …*";
P_HTM[4313]="*na so, bhikkhave, satto sulabharūpo yo namātābhūtapubbo iminā dīghena addhunā.**It’s not easy to find a sentient being who in all this long time has not previously been your mother.*";
P_HTM[4314]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[4315]="*Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro … pe …**Transmigration has no known beginning. …*";
P_HTM[4316]="*alaṃ vimuccitun”ti.**This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.”*";
P_HTM[4317]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4318]="*5. Pitusuttaṃ**Father*";
P_HTM[4319]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4320]="*“Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro … pe …**“Mendicants, transmigration has no known beginning. …*";
P_HTM[4321]="*na so, bhikkhave, satto sulabharūpo yo napitābhūtapubbo … pe …**It’s not easy to find a sentient being who in all this long time has not previously been your father. …*";
P_HTM[4322]="*alaṃ vimuccitun”ti.**This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.”*";
P_HTM[4323]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4324]="*6. Bhātusuttaṃ**Brother*";
P_HTM[4325]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati … pe …**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4326]="*“na so, bhikkhave, satto sulabharūpo yo nabhātābhūtapubbo … pe …**“It’s not easy to find a sentient being who in all this long time has not previously been your brother. …*";
P_HTM[4327]="*alaṃ vimuccitun”ti.**This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.”*";
P_HTM[4328]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4329]="*7. Bhaginisuttaṃ**Sister*";
P_HTM[4330]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati … pe …**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4331]="*“na so, bhikkhave, satto sulabharūpo yo nabhaginibhūtapubbo … pe …**“It’s not easy to find a sentient being who in all this long time has not previously been your sister. …*";
P_HTM[4332]="*alaṃ vimuccitun”ti.**This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.”*";
P_HTM[4333]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4334]="*8. Puttasuttaṃ**Son*";
P_HTM[4335]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati … pe …**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4336]="*“na so, bhikkhave, satto sulabharūpo yo naputtabhūtapubbo … pe …**“It’s not easy to find a sentient being who in all this long time has not previously been your son. …*";
P_HTM[4337]="*alaṃ vimuccitun”ti.**This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.”*";
P_HTM[4338]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4339]="*9. Dhītusuttaṃ**Daughter*";
P_HTM[4340]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4341]="*“Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro.**“Mendicants, transmigration has no known beginning.*";
P_HTM[4342]="*Pubbā koṭi na paññāyati avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ.**No first point is found of sentient beings roaming and transmigrating, hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving.*";
P_HTM[4343]="*Na so, bhikkhave, satto sulabharūpo yo na dhītābhūtapubbo iminā dīghena addhunā.**It’s not easy to find a sentient being who in all this long time has not previously been your daughter.*";
P_HTM[4344]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[4345]="*Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro.**Transmigration has no known beginning.*";
P_HTM[4346]="*Pubbā koṭi na paññāyati avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ.**No first point is found of sentient beings roaming and transmigrating, hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving.*";
P_HTM[4347]="*Evaṃ dīgharattaṃ vo, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ tibbaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ byasanaṃ paccanubhūtaṃ, kaṭasī vaḍḍhitā.**For such a long time you have undergone suffering, agony, and disaster, swelling the cemeteries.*";
P_HTM[4348]="*Yāvañcidaṃ, bhikkhave, alameva sabbasaṅkhāresu nibbindituṃ, alaṃ virajjituṃ, alaṃ vimuccitun”ti.**This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.”*";
P_HTM[4349]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4350]="*10. Vepullapabbatasuttaṃ**Mount Vepulla*";
P_HTM[4351]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain.*";
P_HTM[4352]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[4353]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[4354]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[4355]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[4356]="*“Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro.**“Mendicants, transmigration has no known beginning.*";
P_HTM[4357]="*Pubbā koṭi na paññāyati avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ.**No first point is found of sentient beings roaming and transmigrating, hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving.*";
P_HTM[4358]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, imassa vepullassa pabbatassa ‘pācīnavaṃso’tveva samaññā udapādi.**Once upon a time, mendicants, this Mount Vepulla was known as Pācīnavaṃsa.*";
P_HTM[4359]="*Tena kho pana, bhikkhave, samayena manussānaṃ ‘tivarā’tveva samaññā udapādi.**And at that time people were known as Tivaras.*";
P_HTM[4360]="*Tivarānaṃ, bhikkhave, manussānaṃ cattārīsa vassasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi.**The lifespan of the Tivaras was 40,000 years.*";
P_HTM[4361]="*Tivarā, bhikkhave, manussā pācīnavaṃsaṃ pabbataṃ catūhena ārohanti, catūhena orohanti.**It took them four days to climb Mount Vepulla, and four days to descend.*";
P_HTM[4362]="*Tena kho pana, bhikkhave, samayena kakusandho bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho loke uppanno hoti.**At that time Kakusandha, the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha arose in the world.*";
P_HTM[4363]="*Kakusandhassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa vidhurasañjīvaṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ.**Kakusandha had a fine pair of chief disciples named Vidhura and Sañjīva.*";
P_HTM[4364]="*Passatha, bhikkhave, sā cevimassa pabbatassa samaññā antarahitā, te ca manussā kālaṅkatā, so ca bhagavā parinibbuto.**See, mendicants! This mountain’s name has vanished, those people have passed away, and that Buddha has become fully extinguished.*";
P_HTM[4365]="*Evaṃ aniccā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā;**So impermanent are conditions,*";
P_HTM[4366]="*evaṃ addhuvā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā;**so unstable are conditions,*";
P_HTM[4367]="*evaṃ anassāsikā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā.**so unreliable are conditions.*";
P_HTM[4368]="*Yāvañcidaṃ, bhikkhave, alameva sabbasaṅkhāresu nibbindituṃ, alaṃ virajjituṃ, alaṃ vimuccituṃ.**This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.*";
P_HTM[4369]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, imassa vepullassa pabbatassa ‘vaṅkako’tveva samaññā udapādi.**Once upon a time this Mount Vepulla was known as Vaṅkaka.*";
P_HTM[4370]="*Tena kho pana, bhikkhave, samayena manussānaṃ ‘rohitassā’tveva samaññā udapādi.**And at that time people were known as Rohitassas.*";
P_HTM[4371]="*Rohitassānaṃ, bhikkhave, manussānaṃ tiṃsavassasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi.**The lifespan of the Rohitassas was 30,000 years.*";
P_HTM[4372]="*Rohitassā, bhikkhave, manussā vaṅkakaṃ pabbataṃ tīhena ārohanti, tīhena orohanti.**It took them three days to climb Mount Vepulla, and three days to descend.*";
P_HTM[4373]="*Tena kho pana, bhikkhave, samayena koṇāgamano bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho loke uppanno hoti.**At that time Koṇāgamana, the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha arose in the world.*";
P_HTM[4374]="*Koṇāgamanassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa bhiyyosuttaraṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ.**Koṇāgamana had a fine pair of chief disciples named Bhiyyosa and Uttara.*";
P_HTM[4375]="*Passatha, bhikkhave, sā cevimassa pabbatassa samaññā antarahitā, te ca manussā kālaṅkatā, so ca bhagavā parinibbuto.**See, mendicants! This mountain’s name has vanished, those people have passed away, and that Buddha has become fully extinguished.*";
P_HTM[4376]="*Evaṃ aniccā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā … pe …**So impermanent are conditions …*";
P_HTM[4377]="*alaṃ vimuccituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4378]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, imassa vepullassa pabbatassa ‘supasso’tveva samaññā udapādi.**Once upon a time this Mount Vepulla was known as Supassa.*";
P_HTM[4379]="*Tena kho pana, bhikkhave, samayena manussānaṃ ‘suppiyā’tveva samaññā udapādi.**And at that time people were known as Suppiyas.*";
P_HTM[4380]="*Suppiyānaṃ, bhikkhave, manussānaṃ vīsativassasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ ahosi.**The lifespan of the Suppiyas was 20,000 years.*";
P_HTM[4381]="*Suppiyā, bhikkhave, manussā supassaṃ pabbataṃ dvīhena ārohanti, dvīhena orohanti.**It took them two days to climb Mount Vepulla, and two days to descend.*";
P_HTM[4382]="*Tena kho pana, bhikkhave, samayena kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho loke uppanno hoti.**At that time Kassapa, the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha arose in the world.*";
P_HTM[4383]="*Kassapassa, bhikkhave, bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa tissabhāradvājaṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ ahosi aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ.**Kassapa had a fine pair of chief disciples named Tissa and Bhāradvāja.*";
P_HTM[4384]="*Passatha, bhikkhave, sā cevimassa pabbatassa samaññā antarahitā, te ca manussā kālaṅkatā, so ca bhagavā parinibbuto.**See, mendicants! This mountain’s name has vanished, those people have passed away, and that Buddha has become fully extinguished.*";
P_HTM[4385]="*Evaṃ aniccā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā;**So impermanent are conditions …*";
P_HTM[4386]="*evaṃ addhuvā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4387]="*alaṃ vimuccituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4388]="*Etarahi kho pana, bhikkhave, imassa vepullassa pabbatassa ‘vepullo’tveva samaññā udapādi.**These days this Mount Vepulla is known as Vepulla.*";
P_HTM[4389]="*Etarahi kho pana, bhikkhave, imesaṃ manussānaṃ ‘māgadhakā’tveva samaññā udapādi.**And these people are known as Magadhans.*";
P_HTM[4390]="*Māgadhakānaṃ, bhikkhave, manussānaṃ appakaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ parittaṃ lahukaṃ;**The lifespan of the Magadhans is short, brief, and fleeting.*";
P_HTM[4391]="*yo ciraṃ jīvati so vassasataṃ appaṃ vā bhiyyo.**A long life is a hundred years or a little more.*";
P_HTM[4392]="*Māgadhakā, bhikkhave, manussā vepullaṃ pabbataṃ muhuttena ārohanti muhuttena orohanti.**It takes the Magadhans an hour to climb Mount Vepulla, and an hour to descend.*";
P_HTM[4393]="*Etarahi kho panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, arahaṃ sammāsambuddho loke uppanno.**And now I am the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha who has arisen in the world.*";
P_HTM[4394]="*Mayhaṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, sāriputtamoggallānaṃ nāma sāvakayugaṃ aggaṃ bhaddayugaṃ.**I have a fine pair of chief disciples named Sāriputta and Moggallāna.*";
P_HTM[4395]="*Bhavissati, bhikkhave, so samayo yā ayañcevimassa pabbatassa samaññā antaradhāyissati, ime ca manussā kālaṃ karissanti, ahañca parinibbāyissāmi.**There will come a time when this mountain’s name will disappear, those people will die, and I will be fully extinguished.*";
P_HTM[4396]="*Evaṃ aniccā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā;**So impermanent are conditions,*";
P_HTM[4397]="*evaṃ addhuvā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā;**so unstable are conditions,*";
P_HTM[4398]="*evaṃ anassāsikā, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā.**so unreliable are conditions.*";
P_HTM[4399]="*Yāvañcidaṃ, bhikkhave, alameva sabbasaṅkhāresu nibbindituṃ, alaṃ virajjituṃ, alaṃ vimuccitun”ti.**This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.”*";
P_HTM[4400]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[4401]="*Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:**Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:*";
P_HTM[4402]="*“Pācīnavaṃso tivarānaṃ,**“For the Tivaras it was Pācīnavaṃsa,*";
P_HTM[4403]="*rohitassāna vaṅkako;**for the Rohitassa, Vaṅkaka,*";
P_HTM[4404]="*Suppiyānaṃ supassoti,**Supassa for the Suppiyas,*";
P_HTM[4405]="*māgadhānañca vepullo.**and Vepulla for the Magadhans.*";
P_HTM[4406]="*Aniccā vata saṅkhārā,**Oh! Conditions are impermanent,*";
P_HTM[4407]="*uppādavayadhammino;**their nature is to rise and fall;*";
P_HTM[4408]="*Uppajjitvā nirujjhanti,**having arisen, they cease;*";
P_HTM[4409]="*tesaṃ vūpasamo sukho”ti.**their stilling is true bliss.”*";
P_HTM[4410]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4411]="*Dutiyo vaggo.* **";
P_HTM[4412]="*Duggataṃ sukhitañceva,* **";
P_HTM[4413]="*tiṃsa mātāpitena ca;* **";
P_HTM[4414]="*Bhātā bhaginī putto ca,* **";
P_HTM[4415]="*dhītā vepullapabbataṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4416]="*Anamataggasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ.**The Linked Discourses on the unknown beginning are complete.*";
P_HTM[4417]="*16. Kassapasaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[4418]="*1. Buddhavaggo**Kassapa*";
P_HTM[4419]="*1. Santuṭṭhasuttaṃ**Content*";
P_HTM[4420]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4421]="*“Santuṭṭhāyaṃ, bhikkhave, kassapo itarītarena cīvarena, itarītaracīvarasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī;**“Mendicants, Kassapa is content with any kind of robe, and praises such contentment.*";
P_HTM[4422]="*na ca cīvarahetu anesanaṃ appatirūpaṃ āpajjati; aladdhā ca cīvaraṃ na paritassati; laddhā ca cīvaraṃ agadhito amucchito anajjhāpanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati.**He doesn’t try to get hold of a robe in an improper way. He doesn’t get upset if he doesn’t get a robe. And if he does get a robe, he uses it untied, uninfatuated, unattached, seeing the drawback, and understanding the escape.*";
P_HTM[4423]="*Santuṭṭhāyaṃ, bhikkhave, kassapo itarītarena piṇḍapātena, itarītarapiṇḍapātasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī; na ca piṇḍapātahetu anesanaṃ appatirūpaṃ āpajjati; aladdhā ca piṇḍapātaṃ na paritassati; laddhā ca piṇḍapātaṃ agadhito amucchito anajjhāpanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati.**Kassapa is content with any kind of alms-food …*";
P_HTM[4424]="*Santuṭṭhāyaṃ, bhikkhave, kassapo itarītarena senāsanena, itarītarasenāsanasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī; na ca senāsanahetu anesanaṃ appatirūpaṃ āpajjati; aladdhā ca senāsanaṃ na paritassati; laddhā ca senāsanaṃ agadhito amucchito anajjhāpanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati.**Kassapa is content with any kind of lodging …*";
P_HTM[4425]="*Santuṭṭhāyaṃ, bhikkhave, kassapo itarītarena gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena, itarītaragilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī; na ca gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārahetu anesanaṃ appatirūpaṃ āpajjati; aladdhā ca gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ na paritassati; laddhā ca gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ agadhito amucchito anajjhāpanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati.**Kassapa is content with any kind of medicines and supplies for the sick …*";
P_HTM[4426]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ: ‘santuṭṭhā bhavissāma itarītarena cīvarena, itarītaracīvarasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādino; na ca cīvarahetu anesanaṃ appatirūpaṃ āpajjissāma;**So you should train like this: ‘We will be content with any kind of robe, and praise such contentment. We won’t try to get hold of a robe in an improper way.*";
P_HTM[4427]="*aladdhā ca cīvaraṃ na ca paritassissāma; laddhā ca cīvaraṃ agadhitā amucchitā anajjhāpannā ādīnavadassāvino nissaraṇapaññā paribhuñjissāma’.**We won’t get upset if we don’t get a robe. And if we do get a robe, we’ll use it untied, uninfatuated, unattached, seeing the drawback, and understanding the escape.’*";
P_HTM[4428]="*(Evaṃ sabbaṃ kātabbaṃ.)**(All should be treated the same way.)*";
P_HTM[4429]="*‘Santuṭṭhā bhavissāma itarītarena piṇḍapātena … pe …**‘We will be content with any kind of alms-food …’*";
P_HTM[4430]="*santuṭṭhā bhavissāma itarītarena senāsanena … pe …**‘We will be content with any kind of lodging …’*";
P_HTM[4431]="*santuṭṭhā bhavissāma itarītarena gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena, itarītaragilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādino; na ca gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārahetu anesanaṃ appatirūpaṃ āpajjissāma aladdhā ca gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ na paritassissāma; laddhā ca gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ agadhitā amucchitā anajjhāpannā ādīnavadassāvino nissaraṇapaññā paribhuñjissāmā’ti.**‘We will be content with any kind of medicines and supplies for the sick …’*";
P_HTM[4432]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ.**That’s how you should train.*";
P_HTM[4433]="*Kassapena vā hi vo, bhikkhave, ovadissāmi yo vā panassa kassapasadiso, ovaditehi ca pana vo tathattāya paṭipajjitabban”ti.**I will exhort you with the example of Kassapa or someone like him. You should practice accordingly.”*";
P_HTM[4434]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4435]="*2. Anottappīsuttaṃ**Imprudent*";
P_HTM[4436]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[4437]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ca mahākassapo āyasmā ca sāriputto bārāṇasiyaṃ viharanti isipatane migadāye.**At one time Venerable Mahākassapa and Venerable Sāriputta were staying near Benares, in the deer park at Isipatana.*";
P_HTM[4438]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yenāyasmā mahākassapo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā mahākassapena saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Sāriputta came out of retreat, went to Venerable Mahākassapa, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4439]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ mahākassapaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to Mahākassapa:*";
P_HTM[4440]="*“vuccati hidaṃ, āvuso kassapa, anātāpī anottappī abhabbo sambodhāya abhabbo nibbānāya abhabbo anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya;**“Reverend Kassapa, it’s said that without being keen and prudent you can’t achieve awakening, extinguishment, and the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[4441]="*ātāpī ca kho ottappī bhabbo sambodhāya bhabbo nibbānāya bhabbo anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāyā”ti.**But if you’re keen and prudent you can achieve awakening, extinguishment, and the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[4442]="*“Kittāvatā nu kho, āvuso, anātāpī hoti anottappī abhabbo sambodhāya abhabbo nibbānāya abhabbo anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya;**To what extent is this the case?”*";
P_HTM[4443]="*kittāvatā ca panāvuso, ātāpī hoti ottappī bhabbo sambodhāya bhabbo nibbānāya bhabbo anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāyā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[4444]="*“Idhāvuso, bhikkhu ‘anuppannā me pāpakā akusalā dhammā uppajjamānā anatthāya saṃvatteyyun’ti na ātappaṃ karoti, ‘uppannā me pāpakā akusalā dhammā appahīyamānā anatthāya saṃvatteyyun’ti na ātappaṃ karoti, ‘anuppannā me kusalā dhammā nuppajjamānā anatthāya saṃvatteyyun’ti na ātappaṃ karoti, ‘uppannā me kusalā dhammā nirujjhamānā anatthāya saṃvatteyyun’ti na ātappaṃ karoti.**“Reverend, take a mendicant who doesn’t foster keenness by thinking: ‘If unarisen unskillful qualities arise in me, they’ll lead to harm.’ ‘If I don’t give up arisen unskillful qualities, they’ll lead to harm.’ ‘If I don’t give rise to unarisen skillful qualities, they’ll lead to harm.’ ‘If arisen skillful qualities cease in me, they’ll lead to harm.’*";
P_HTM[4445]="*Evaṃ kho, āvuso, anātāpī hoti.**That’s how you’re not keen.*";
P_HTM[4446]="*Kathañcāvuso, anottappī hoti?**And how are you not prudent?*";
P_HTM[4447]="*Idhāvuso, bhikkhu ‘anuppannā me pāpakā akusalā dhammā uppajjamānā anatthāya saṃvatteyyun’ti na ottappati, ‘uppannā me pāpakā akusalā dhammā appahīyamānā anatthāya saṃvatteyyun’ti na ottappati, ‘anuppannā me kusalā dhammā nuppajjamānā anatthāya saṃvatteyyun’ti na ottappati, ‘uppannā me kusalā dhammā nirujjhamānā anatthāya saṃvatteyyun’ti na ottappati.**Take a mendicant who doesn’t foster prudence by thinking: ‘If unarisen unskillful qualities arise in me, they’ll lead to harm.’ ‘If I don’t give up arisen unskillful qualities, they’ll lead to harm.’ ‘If I don’t give rise to unarisen skillful qualities, they’ll lead to harm.’ ‘If arisen skillful qualities cease in me, they’ll lead to harm.’*";
P_HTM[4448]="*Evaṃ kho, āvuso, anottappī hoti.**That’s how you’re not prudent.*";
P_HTM[4449]="*Evaṃ kho, āvuso, anātāpī anottappī abhabbo sambodhāya abhabbo nibbānāya abhabbo anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya.**That’s how without being keen and prudent you can’t achieve awakening, extinguishment, and the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[4450]="*Kathañcāvuso, ātāpī hoti?**And how are you keen?*";
P_HTM[4451]="*Idhāvuso, bhikkhu ‘anuppannā me pāpakā akusalā dhammā uppajjamānā anatthāya saṃvatteyyun’ti ātappaṃ karoti, ‘uppannā me pāpakā akusalā dhammā appahīyamānā anatthāya saṃvatteyyun’ti ātappaṃ karoti, anuppannā me kusalā dhammā … pe … ātappaṃ karoti.**Take a mendicant who fosters keenness by thinking: ‘If unarisen unskillful qualities arise in me, they’ll lead to harm.’ ‘If I don’t give up arisen unskillful qualities, they’ll lead to harm.’ ‘If I don’t give rise to unarisen skillful qualities, they’ll lead to harm.’ ‘If arisen skillful qualities cease in me, they’ll lead to harm.’*";
P_HTM[4452]="*Evaṃ kho, āvuso, ātāpī hoti.**That’s how you’re keen.*";
P_HTM[4453]="*Kathañcāvuso, ottappī hoti?**And how are you prudent?*";
P_HTM[4454]="*Idhāvuso, bhikkhu ‘anuppannā me pāpakā akusalā dhammā uppajjamānā anatthāya saṃvatteyyun’ti ottappati, ‘uppannā me pāpakā akusalā dhammā appahīyamānā anatthāya saṃvatteyyun’ti ottappati, ‘anuppannā me kusalā dhammā anuppajjamānā anatthāya saṃvatteyyun’ti ottappati, ‘uppannā me kusalā dhammā nirujjhamānā anatthāya saṃvatteyyun’ti ottappati.**Take a mendicant who fosters prudence by thinking: ‘If unarisen unskillful qualities arise in me, they’ll lead to harm.’ ‘If I don’t give up arisen unskillful qualities, they’ll lead to harm.’ ‘If I don’t give rise to unarisen skillful qualities, they’ll lead to harm.’ ‘If arisen skillful qualities cease in me, they’ll lead to harm.’*";
P_HTM[4455]="*Evaṃ kho, āvuso, ottappī hoti.**That’s how you’re prudent.*";
P_HTM[4456]="*Evaṃ kho, āvuso, ātāpī ottappī bhabbo sambodhāya bhabbo nibbānāya bhabbo anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāyā”ti.**That’s how if you’re keen and prudent you can achieve awakening, extinguishment, and the supreme sanctuary.”*";
P_HTM[4457]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4458]="*3. Candūpamasuttaṃ**Like the Moon*";
P_HTM[4459]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4460]="*“Candūpamā, bhikkhave, kulāni upasaṅkamatha—**“Mendicants, you should approach families like the moon:*";
P_HTM[4461]="*apakasseva kāyaṃ, apakassa cittaṃ, niccanavakā kulesu appagabbhā.**withdrawn in body and mind, always the newcomer, and never impudent.*";
P_HTM[4462]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso jarudapānaṃ vā olokeyya pabbatavisamaṃ vā nadīviduggaṃ vā—**Suppose a person were to look down at an old well, a rugged cliff, or an inaccessible riverland.*";
P_HTM[4463]="*apakasseva kāyaṃ, apakassa cittaṃ;**They’d withdraw their body and mind.*";
P_HTM[4464]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, candūpamā kulāni upasaṅkamatha—**In the same way, you should approach families like the moon:*";
P_HTM[4465]="*apakasseva kāyaṃ, apakassa cittaṃ, niccanavakā kulesu appagabbhā.**withdrawn in body and mind, always the newcomer, and never impudent.*";
P_HTM[4466]="*Kassapo, bhikkhave, candūpamo kulāni upasaṅkamati—**Kassapa approaches families like the moon:*";
P_HTM[4467]="*apakasseva kāyaṃ, apakassa cittaṃ, niccanavako kulesu appagabbho.**withdrawn in body and mind, always the newcomer, and never impudent.*";
P_HTM[4468]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[4469]="*kathaṃrūpo bhikkhu arahati kulāni upasaṅkamitun”ti?**What kind of mendicant is worthy of approaching families?”*";
P_HTM[4470]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā bhagavaṃnettikā bhagavaṃpaṭisaraṇā. Sādhu vata, bhante, bhagavantaṃyeva paṭibhātu etassa bhāsitassa attho. Bhagavato sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti.**“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. He is our guide and our refuge. Sir, may the Buddha himself please clarify the meaning of this. The mendicants will listen and remember it.”*";
P_HTM[4471]="*Atha kho bhagavā ākāse pāṇiṃ cālesi.**Then the Buddha waved his hand in space.*";
P_HTM[4472]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ayaṃ ākāse pāṇi na sajjati na gayhati na bajjhati;**“Mendicants, this hand is not stuck or held or caught in space.*";
P_HTM[4473]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, yassa kassaci bhikkhuno kulāni upasaṅkamato kulesu cittaṃ na sajjati na gayhati na bajjhati:**In the same way, when approaching families, a mendicant’s mind is not stuck or held or caught, thinking:*";
P_HTM[4474]="*‘labhantu lābhakāmā, puññakāmā karontu puññānī’ti;**‘May those who want material possessions get them, and may those who want merit make merits!’*";
P_HTM[4475]="*yathāsakena lābhena attamano hoti sumano, evaṃ paresaṃ lābhena attamano hoti sumano;**They’re just as pleased and happy when others get something as they are when they get something.*";
P_HTM[4476]="*evarūpo kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu arahati kulāni upasaṅkamituṃ.**This kind of mendicant is worthy of approaching families.*";
P_HTM[4477]="*Kassapassa, bhikkhave, kulāni upasaṅkamato kulesu cittaṃ na sajjati na gayhati na bajjhati:**When Kassapa approaches families, his mind is not stuck or held or caught, thinking:*";
P_HTM[4478]="*‘labhantu lābhakāmā, puññakāmā karontu puññānī’ti;**‘May those who want material possessions get them, and may those who want merit make merits!’*";
P_HTM[4479]="*yathāsakena lābhena attamano hoti sumano;**He’s just as pleased and happy when others get something as he is when he gets something.*";
P_HTM[4480]="*evaṃ paresaṃ lābhena attamano hoti sumano.* **";
P_HTM[4481]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[4482]="*kathaṃrūpassa bhikkhuno aparisuddhā dhammadesanā hoti, kathaṃrūpassa bhikkhuno parisuddhā dhammadesanā hotī”ti?**What kind of mendicant’s teaching is pure, and what kind is impure?”*";
P_HTM[4483]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā bhagavaṃnettikā bhagavaṃpaṭisaraṇā. Sādhu vata, bhante, bhagavantaṃyeva paṭibhātu etassa bhāsitassa attho. Bhagavato sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti.**“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. He is our guide and our refuge. Sir, may the Buddha himself please clarify the meaning of this. The mendicants will listen and remember it.”*";
P_HTM[4484]="*“Tena hi, bhikkhave, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, mendicants, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[4485]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[4486]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[4487]="*“Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃcitto paresaṃ dhammaṃ deseti:**“Whoever teaches Dhamma to others with the thought:*";
P_HTM[4488]="*‘aho vata me dhammaṃ suṇeyyuṃ, sutvā ca pana dhammaṃ pasīdeyyuṃ, pasannā ca me pasannākāraṃ kareyyun’ti;**‘Oh! May they listen to the teaching from me. When they’ve heard it, may they gain confidence in the teaching and demonstrate their confidence to me.’*";
P_HTM[4489]="*evarūpassa kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno aparisuddhā dhammadesanā hoti.**Such a mendicant’s teaching is impure.*";
P_HTM[4490]="*Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃcitto paresaṃ dhammaṃ deseti:**Whoever teaches Dhamma to others with the thought:*";
P_HTM[4491]="*‘svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo sandiṭṭhiko akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhīti.**‘The teaching is well explained by the Buddha—visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves.*";
P_HTM[4492]="*Aho vata me dhammaṃ suṇeyyuṃ, sutvā ca pana dhammaṃ ājāneyyuṃ, ājānitvā ca pana tathattāya paṭipajjeyyun’ti.**Oh! May they listen to the teaching from me. When they’ve heard it, may they understand the teaching and practice accordingly.’*";
P_HTM[4493]="*Iti dhammasudhammataṃ paṭicca paresaṃ dhammaṃ deseti, kāruññaṃ paṭicca anuddayaṃ paṭicca anukampaṃ upādāya paresaṃ dhammaṃ deseti.**So they teach others because of the natural excellence of the teaching, out of compassion, kindness, and sympathy.*";
P_HTM[4494]="*Evarūpassa kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno parisuddhā dhammadesanā hoti.**Such a mendicant’s teaching is pure.*";
P_HTM[4495]="*Kassapo, bhikkhave, evaṃcitto paresaṃ dhammaṃ deseti:**Kassapa teaches Dhamma to others with the thought:*";
P_HTM[4496]="*‘svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo sandiṭṭhiko akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhīti.**‘The teaching is well explained by the Buddha—visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves.*";
P_HTM[4497]="*Aho vata me dhammaṃ suṇeyyuṃ, sutvā ca pana dhammaṃ ājāneyyuṃ, ājānitvā ca pana tathattāya paṭipajjeyyun’ti.**Oh! May they listen to the teaching from me. When they’ve heard it, may they understand the teaching and practice accordingly.’*";
P_HTM[4498]="*Iti dhammasudhammataṃ paṭicca paresaṃ dhammaṃ deseti, kāruññaṃ paṭicca anuddayaṃ paṭicca anukampaṃ upādāya paresaṃ dhammaṃ deseti.**Thus he teaches others because of the natural excellence of the teaching, out of compassion, kindness, and sympathy.*";
P_HTM[4499]="*Kassapena vā hi vo, bhikkhave, ovadissāmi yo vā panassa kassapasadiso, ovaditehi ca pana vo tathattāya paṭipajjitabban”ti.**I will exhort you with the example of Kassapa or someone like him. You should practice accordingly.”*";
P_HTM[4500]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4501]="*4. Kulūpakasuttaṃ**Visiting Families*";
P_HTM[4502]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4503]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**“What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[4504]="*kathaṃrūpo bhikkhu arahati kulūpako hotuṃ, kathaṃrūpo bhikkhu na arahati kulūpako hotun”ti?**What kind of mendicant is worthy of visiting families? And what kind of mendicant is not worthy of visiting families?”*";
P_HTM[4505]="*Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …**“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”*";
P_HTM[4506]="*bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[4507]="*“Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃcitto kulāni upasaṅkamati:**“Whoever visits families with the thought:*";
P_HTM[4508]="*‘dentuyeva me, mā nādaṃsu;**‘May they give to me, may they not fail to give.*";
P_HTM[4509]="*bahukaññeva me dentu, mā thokaṃ;**May they give a lot, not a little.*";
P_HTM[4510]="*paṇītaññeva me dentu, mā lūkhaṃ;**May they give me fine things, not coarse.*";
P_HTM[4511]="*sīghaññeva me dentu, mā dandhaṃ;**May they give quickly, not slowly.*";
P_HTM[4512]="*sakkaccaññeva me dentu, mā asakkaccan’ti.**May they give carefully, not carelessly.’*";
P_HTM[4513]="*Tassa ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno evaṃcittassa kulāni upasaṅkamato na denti, tena bhikkhu sandīyati; so tatonidānaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati.**If a mendicant with such a thought approaches a family and they don’t give, the mendicant feels slighted. And they experience pain and sadness because of that.*";
P_HTM[4514]="*Thokaṃ denti, no bahukaṃ … pe …**If they give only a little …*";
P_HTM[4515]="*lūkhaṃ denti, no paṇītaṃ …**if they give coarse things …*";
P_HTM[4516]="*dandhaṃ denti, no sīghaṃ, tena bhikkhu sandīyati; so tatonidānaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati.**if they give slowly …*";
P_HTM[4517]="*Asakkaccaṃ denti, no sakkaccaṃ; tena bhikkhu sandīyati; so tatonidānaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati.**if they give carelessly, the mendicant feels slighted. And they experience pain and sadness because of that.*";
P_HTM[4518]="*Evarūpo kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na arahati kulūpako hotuṃ.**That kind of mendicant is not worthy of visiting families.*";
P_HTM[4519]="*Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃcitto kulāni upasaṅkamati:**Whoever visits families with the thought:*";
P_HTM[4520]="*‘taṃ kutettha labbhā parakulesu—**‘When among other families, how could I possibly think:*";
P_HTM[4521]="*dentuyeva me, mā nādaṃsu;**“May they give to me, may they not fail to give.*";
P_HTM[4522]="*bahukaññeva me dentu, mā thokaṃ;**May they give a lot, not a little.*";
P_HTM[4523]="*paṇītaññeva me dentu, mā lūkhaṃ;**May they give me fine things, not coarse.*";
P_HTM[4524]="*sīghaññeva me dentu, mā dandhaṃ;**May they give quickly, not slowly.*";
P_HTM[4525]="*sakkaccaññeva me dentu, mā asakkaccan’ti.**May they give carefully, not carelessly.”’*";
P_HTM[4526]="*Tassa ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno evaṃcittassa kulāni upasaṅkamato na denti; tena bhikkhu na sandīyati; so na tatonidānaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati.**If a mendicant with such a thought approaches a family and they don’t give, the mendicant doesn’t feel slighted. And they don’t experience pain and sadness because of that.*";
P_HTM[4527]="*Thokaṃ denti, no bahukaṃ; tena bhikkhu na sandīyati; so na tatonidānaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati.**If they give only a little …*";
P_HTM[4528]="*Lūkhaṃ denti, no paṇītaṃ; tena bhikkhu na sandīyati; so na tatonidānaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati.**if they give coarse things …*";
P_HTM[4529]="*Dandhaṃ denti, no sīghaṃ; tena bhikkhu na sandīyati; so na tatonidānaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati.**if they give slowly …*";
P_HTM[4530]="*Asakkaccaṃ denti, no sakkaccaṃ; tena bhikkhu na sandīyati; so na tatonidānaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati.**if they give carelessly, the mendicant doesn’t feel slighted. And they don’t experience pain and sadness because of that.*";
P_HTM[4531]="*Evarūpo kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu arahati kulūpako hotuṃ.**That kind of mendicant is worthy of visiting families.*";
P_HTM[4532]="*Kassapo, bhikkhave, evaṃcitto kulāni upasaṅkamati:**Kassapa visits families with the thought:*";
P_HTM[4533]="*‘taṃ kutettha labbhā parakulesu—**‘When among other families, how could I possibly think:*";
P_HTM[4534]="*dentuyeva me, mā nādaṃsu;**“May they give to me, may they not fail to give.*";
P_HTM[4535]="*bahukaññeva me dentu, mā thokaṃ;**May they give a lot, not a little.*";
P_HTM[4536]="*paṇītaññeva me dentu, mā lūkhaṃ;**May they give me fine things, not coarse.*";
P_HTM[4537]="*sīghaññeva me dentu, mā dandhaṃ;**May they give quickly, not slowly.*";
P_HTM[4538]="*sakkaccaññeva me dentu, mā asakkaccan’ti.**May they give carefully, not carelessly.”’*";
P_HTM[4539]="*Tassa ce, bhikkhave, kassapassa evaṃcittassa kulāni upasaṅkamato na denti; tena kassapo na sandīyati; so na tatonidānaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati.**With such a thought, if he approaches a family and they don’t give, he doesn’t feel slighted. And he doesn’t experience pain and sadness because of that.*";
P_HTM[4540]="*Thokaṃ denti, no bahukaṃ; tena kassapo na sandīyati; so na tatonidānaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati.**If they give only a little …*";
P_HTM[4541]="*Lūkhaṃ denti, no paṇītaṃ; tena kassapo na sandīyati; so na tatonidānaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati.**if they give coarse things …*";
P_HTM[4542]="*Dandhaṃ denti, no sīghaṃ; tena kassapo na sandīyati; so na tatonidānaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati.**if they give slowly …*";
P_HTM[4543]="*Asakkaccaṃ denti, no sakkaccaṃ; tena kassapo na sandīyati; so na tatonidānaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedayati.**if they give carelessly, he doesn’t feel slighted. And he doesn’t experience pain and sadness because of that.*";
P_HTM[4544]="*Kassapena vā hi vo, bhikkhave, ovadissāmi yo vā panassa kassapasadiso. Ovaditehi ca pana vo tathattāya paṭipajjitabban”ti.**I will exhort you with the example of Kassapa or someone like him. You should practice accordingly.”*";
P_HTM[4545]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4546]="*5. Jiṇṇasuttaṃ**Old Age*";
P_HTM[4547]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ …**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[4548]="*rājagahe veḷuvane.**Near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove.*";
P_HTM[4549]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ mahākassapaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then Venerable Mahākassapa went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[4550]="*“jiṇṇosi dāni tvaṃ, kassapa, garukāni ca te imāni sāṇāni paṃsukūlāni nibbasanāni.**“You’re old now, Kassapa. Those worn-out hempen rag robes must be a burden for you.*";
P_HTM[4551]="*Tasmātiha tvaṃ, kassapa, gahapatāni ceva cīvarāni dhārehi, nimantanāni ca bhuñjāhi, mama ca santike viharāhī”ti.**So Kassapa, you should wear clothes given by householders, accept invitations for the meal, and stay in my presence.”*";
P_HTM[4552]="*“Ahaṃ kho, bhante, dīgharattaṃ āraññiko ceva āraññikattassa ca vaṇṇavādī, piṇḍapātiko ceva piṇḍapātikattassa ca vaṇṇavādī, paṃsukūliko ceva paṃsukūlikattassa ca vaṇṇavādī, tecīvariko ceva tecīvarikattassa ca vaṇṇavādī, appiccho ceva appicchatāya ca vaṇṇavādī, santuṭṭho ceva santuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī, pavivitto ceva pavivekassa ca vaṇṇavādī, asaṃsaṭṭho ceva asaṃsaggassa ca vaṇṇavādī, āraddhavīriyo ceva vīriyārambhassa ca vaṇṇavādī”ti.**“For a long time, sir, I’ve lived in the wilderness, eaten only alms-food, worn rag robes, and owned just three robes; and I’ve praised these things. I’ve been one of few wishes, content, secluded, aloof, and energetic; and I’ve praised these things.”*";
P_HTM[4553]="*“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, kassapa, atthavasaṃ sampassamāno dīgharattaṃ āraññiko ceva āraññikattassa ca vaṇṇavādī, piṇḍapātiko ceva … pe …**“But seeing what benefit, Kassapa, have you long practiced these things?”*";
P_HTM[4554]="*paṃsukūliko ceva …* **";
P_HTM[4555]="*tecīvariko ceva …* **";
P_HTM[4556]="*appiccho ceva …* **";
P_HTM[4557]="*santuṭṭho ceva …* **";
P_HTM[4558]="*pavivitto ceva …* **";
P_HTM[4559]="*asaṃsaṭṭho ceva …* **";
P_HTM[4560]="*āraddhavīriyo ceva vīriyārambhassa ca vaṇṇavādī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[4561]="*“Dve khvāhaṃ, bhante, atthavase sampassamāno dīgharattaṃ āraññiko ceva āraññikattassa ca vaṇṇavādī, piṇḍapātiko ceva … pe …**“Sir, seeing two benefits I have long practiced these things.*";
P_HTM[4562]="*paṃsukūliko ceva …* **";
P_HTM[4563]="*tecīvariko ceva …* **";
P_HTM[4564]="*appiccho ceva …* **";
P_HTM[4565]="*santuṭṭho ceva …* **";
P_HTM[4566]="*pavivitto ceva …* **";
P_HTM[4567]="*asaṃsaṭṭho ceva …* **";
P_HTM[4568]="*āraddhavīriyo ceva vīriyārambhassa ca vaṇṇavādī.* **";
P_HTM[4569]="*Attano ca diṭṭhadhammasukhavihāraṃ sampassamāno, pacchimañca janataṃ anukampamāno:**I see a happy life for myself in the present. And I have compassion for future generations, thinking:*";
P_HTM[4570]="*‘appeva nāma pacchimā janatā diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjeyyuṃ.**‘Hopefully those who come after might follow my example.’*";
P_HTM[4571]="*Ye kira te ahesuṃ buddhānubuddhasāvakā te dīgharattaṃ āraññikā ceva ahesuṃ āraññikattassa ca vaṇṇavādino … pe …**For they may think: ‘It seems that the awakened disciples of the Buddha for a long time lived in the wilderness, ate only alms-food, wore rag robes, and owned just three robes; and they praised these things. They were of few wishes, content, secluded, aloof, and energetic; and they praised these things.’*";
P_HTM[4572]="*piṇḍapātikā ceva ahesuṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4573]="*paṃsukūlikā ceva ahesuṃ …* **";
P_HTM[4574]="*tecīvarikā ceva ahesuṃ …* **";
P_HTM[4575]="*appicchā ceva ahesuṃ …* **";
P_HTM[4576]="*santuṭṭhā ceva ahesuṃ …* **";
P_HTM[4577]="*pavivittā ceva ahesuṃ …* **";
P_HTM[4578]="*asaṃsaṭṭhā ceva ahesuṃ …* **";
P_HTM[4579]="*āraddhavīriyā ceva ahesuṃ vīriyārambhassa ca vaṇṇavādino’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4580]="*Te tathattāya paṭipajjissanti, tesaṃ taṃ bhavissati dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya.**They’ll practice accordingly, which will be for their lasting welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[4581]="*Ime khvāhaṃ, bhante, dve atthavase sampassamāno dīgharattaṃ āraññiko ceva āraññikattassa ca vaṇṇavādī, piṇḍapātiko ceva … pe …**Seeing these two benefits I have long practiced these things.”*";
P_HTM[4582]="*paṃsukūliko ceva …* **";
P_HTM[4583]="*tecīvariko ceva …* **";
P_HTM[4584]="*appiccho ceva …* **";
P_HTM[4585]="*santuṭṭho ceva …* **";
P_HTM[4586]="*pavivitto ceva …* **";
P_HTM[4587]="*asaṃsaṭṭho ceva …* **";
P_HTM[4588]="*āraddhavīriyo ceva vīriyārambhassa ca vaṇṇavādī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4589]="*“Sādhu sādhu, kassapa.**“Good, good, Kassapa!*";
P_HTM[4590]="*Bahujanahitāya kira tvaṃ, kassapa, paṭipanno bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ.**You’re acting for the welfare and happiness of the people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[4591]="*Tasmātiha tvaṃ, kassapa, sāṇāni ceva paṃsukūlāni dhārehi nibbasanāni, piṇḍāya ca carāhi, araññe ca viharāhī”ti.**So Kassapa, wear worn-out hempen rag robes, walk for alms, and stay in the wilderness.”*";
P_HTM[4592]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4593]="*6. Ovādasuttaṃ**Advice*";
P_HTM[4594]="*Rājagahe veḷuvane.**Near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove.*";
P_HTM[4595]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ mahākassapaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then Venerable Mahākassapa went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[4596]="*“ovada, kassapa, bhikkhū;**“Kassapa, advise the mendicants!*";
P_HTM[4597]="*karohi, kassapa, bhikkhūnaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ.**Give them a Dhamma talk!*";
P_HTM[4598]="*Ahaṃ vā, kassapa, bhikkhū ovadeyyaṃ tvaṃ vā;**Either you or I should advise the mendicants*";
P_HTM[4599]="*ahaṃ vā bhikkhūnaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ kareyyaṃ tvaṃ vā”ti.**and give them a Dhamma talk.”*";
P_HTM[4600]="*“Dubbacā kho, bhante, etarahi bhikkhū, dovacassakaraṇehi dhammehi samannāgatā, akkhamā, appadakkhiṇaggāhino anusāsaniṃ.**“Sir, the mendicants these days are hard to admonish, having qualities that make them hard to admonish. They’re impatient, and don’t take instruction respectfully.*";
P_HTM[4601]="*Idhāhaṃ, bhante, addasaṃ bhaṇḍañca nāma bhikkhuṃ ānandassa saddhivihāriṃ abhijikañca nāma bhikkhuṃ anuruddhassa saddhivihāriṃ aññamaññaṃ sutena accāvadante:**Take the monk called Bhaṇḍa, Ānanda’s pupil. He’s been competing in studies with the monk called Abhiñjika, Anuruddha’s pupil. They say:*";
P_HTM[4602]="*‘ehi, bhikkhu, ko bahutaraṃ bhāsissati, ko sundarataraṃ bhāsissati, ko cirataraṃ bhāsissatī’”ti.**‘Come on, monk, who can recite more? Who can recite better? Who can recite longer?’”*";
P_HTM[4603]="*Atha kho bhagavā aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ āmantesi:**So the Buddha said to a certain monk,*";
P_HTM[4604]="*“ehi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, mama vacanena bhaṇḍañca bhikkhuṃ ānandassa saddhivihāriṃ abhijikañca bhikkhuṃ anuruddhassa saddhivihāriṃ āmantehi:**“Please, monk, in my name tell the monk called Bhaṇḍa, Ānanda’s pupil, and the monk called Abhiñjika, Anuruddha’s pupil that*";
P_HTM[4605]="*‘satthā āyasmante āmantetī’”ti.**the teacher summons them.”*";
P_HTM[4606]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu bhagavato paṭissutvā yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū etadavoca:**“Yes, sir,” that monk replied. He went to those monks and said,*";
P_HTM[4607]="*“satthā āyasmante āmantetī”ti.**“Venerables, the teacher summons you.”*";
P_HTM[4608]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū tassa bhikkhuno paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho te bhikkhū bhagavā etadavoca:**“Yes, reverend,” those monks replied. They went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to them:*";
P_HTM[4609]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, aññamaññaṃ sutena accāvadatha:**“Is it really true, monks, that you’ve been competing in studies, saying:*";
P_HTM[4610]="*‘ehi, bhikkhu, ko bahutaraṃ bhāsissati, ko sundarataraṃ bhāsissati, ko cirataraṃ bhāsissatī’”ti?**‘Come on, monk, who can recite more? Who can recite better? Who can recite longer?’”*";
P_HTM[4611]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4612]="*“Kiṃ nu kho me tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānātha:**“Have you ever known me to teach the Dhamma like this:*";
P_HTM[4613]="*‘etha tumhe, bhikkhave, aññamaññaṃ sutena accāvadatha—**‘Please mendicants, compete in studies to*";
P_HTM[4614]="*ehi, bhikkhu, ko bahutaraṃ bhāsissati, ko sundarataraṃ bhāsissati, ko cirataraṃ bhāsissatī’”ti?**see who can recite more and better and longer’?”*";
P_HTM[4615]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4616]="*“No ce kira me tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānātha, atha kiñcarahi tumhe, moghapurisā, kiṃ jānantā kiṃ passantā evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye pabbajitā samānā aññamaññaṃ sutena accāvadatha:**“If you’ve never known me to teach the Dhamma like this, then what exactly do you know and see, you foolish men, that after going forth in such a well explained teaching and training you’d compete in studies to*";
P_HTM[4617]="*‘ehi, bhikkhu, ko bahutaraṃ bhāsissati, ko sundarataraṃ bhāsissati, ko cirataraṃ bhāsissatī’”ti.**see who can recite more and better and longer?”*";
P_HTM[4618]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato pādesu sirasā nipatitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then those monks bowed with their heads at the Buddha’s feet and said,*";
P_HTM[4619]="*“accayo no, bhante, accagamā, yathābāle yathāmūḷhe yathāakusale, ye mayaṃ evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye pabbajitā samānā aññamaññaṃ sutena accāvadimha:**“We have made a mistake, sir. It was foolish, stupid, and unskillful of us in that after going forth in such a well explained teaching and training we competed in studies to*";
P_HTM[4620]="*‘ehi, bhikkhu, ko bahutaraṃ bhāsissati, ko sundarataraṃ bhāsissati, ko cirataraṃ bhāsissatī’ti.**see who can recite more and better and longer.*";
P_HTM[4621]="*Tesaṃ no, bhante, bhagavā accayaṃ accayato paṭiggaṇhātu āyatiṃ saṃvarāyā”ti.**Please, sir, accept our mistake for what it is, so we will restrain ourselves in future.”*";
P_HTM[4622]="*“Taggha tumhe, bhikkhave, accayo accagamā yathābāle yathāmūḷhe yathāakusale, ye tumhe evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye pabbajitā samānā aññamaññaṃ sutena accāvadittha:**“Indeed, monks, you made a mistake. It was foolish, stupid, and unskillful of you to act in that way.*";
P_HTM[4623]="*‘ehi, bhikkhu, ko bahutaraṃ bhāsissati, ko sundarataraṃ bhāsissati, ko cirataraṃ bhāsissatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4624]="*Yato ca kho tumhe, bhikkhave, accayaṃ accayato disvā yathādhammaṃ paṭikarotha, taṃ vo mayaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma.**But since you have recognized your mistake for what it is, and have dealt with it properly, I accept it.*";
P_HTM[4625]="*Vuddhi hesā, bhikkhave, ariyassa vinaye yo accayaṃ accayato disvā yathādhammaṃ paṭikaroti āyatiñca saṃvaraṃ āpajjatī”ti.**For it is growth in the training of the noble one to recognize a mistake for what it is, deal with it properly, and commit to restraint in the future.”*";
P_HTM[4626]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4627]="*7. Dutiyaovādasuttaṃ**Advice (2nd)*";
P_HTM[4628]="*Rājagahe viharati veḷuvane.**Near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove.*";
P_HTM[4629]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe …**Then Venerable Mahākassapa went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side.*";
P_HTM[4630]="*ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ mahākassapaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[4631]="*“ovada, kassapa, bhikkhū;**“Kassapa, advise the mendicants!*";
P_HTM[4632]="*karohi, kassapa, bhikkhūnaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ.**Give them a Dhamma talk!*";
P_HTM[4633]="*Ahaṃ vā, kassapa, bhikkhū ovadeyyaṃ tvaṃ vā;**Either you or I should advise the mendicants*";
P_HTM[4634]="*ahaṃ vā bhikkhūnaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ kareyyaṃ tvaṃ vā”ti.**and give them a Dhamma talk.”*";
P_HTM[4635]="*“Dubbacā kho, bhante, etarahi bhikkhū, dovacassakaraṇehi dhammehi samannāgatā akkhamā appadakkhiṇaggāhino anusāsaniṃ.**“Sir, the mendicants these days are hard to admonish, having qualities that make them hard to admonish. They’re impatient, and don’t take instruction respectfully.*";
P_HTM[4636]="*Yassa kassaci, bhante, saddhā natthi kusalesu dhammesu, hirī natthi kusalesu dhammesu, ottappaṃ natthi kusalesu dhammesu, vīriyaṃ natthi kusalesu dhammesu, paññā natthi kusalesu dhammesu, tassa yā ratti vā divaso vā āgacchati, hāniyeva pāṭikaṅkhā kusalesu dhammesu, no vuddhi.**Sir, whoever has no faith, conscience, prudence, energy, or wisdom when it comes to skillful qualities can expect decline, not growth, in skillful qualities, whether by day or by night.*";
P_HTM[4637]="*Seyyathāpi, bhante, kāḷapakkhe candassa yā ratti vā divaso vā āgacchati, hāyateva vaṇṇena, hāyati maṇḍalena, hāyati ābhāya, hāyati ārohapariṇāhena.**It’s like the moon in the waning fortnight. Whether by day or by night, its beauty, roundness, light, and diameter and circumference only decline.*";
P_HTM[4638]="*Evameva kho, bhante, yassa kassaci saddhā natthi kusalesu dhammesu … pe …**In the same way, whoever has no faith, conscience, prudence, energy, and wisdom when it comes to skillful qualities can expect decline, not growth, in skillful qualities, whether by day or by night.*";
P_HTM[4639]="*hirī natthi …* **";
P_HTM[4640]="*ottappaṃ natthi …* **";
P_HTM[4641]="*vīriyaṃ natthi …* **";
P_HTM[4642]="*paññā natthi … kusalesu dhammesu tassa yā ratti vā divaso vā āgacchati, hāniyeva pāṭikaṅkhā kusalesu dhammesu, no vuddhi.* **";
P_HTM[4643]="*‘Assaddho purisapuggalo’ti, bhante, parihānametaṃ;**A faithless individual is in decline.*";
P_HTM[4644]="*‘ahiriko purisapuggalo’ti, bhante, parihānametaṃ;**An individual with no conscience is in decline.*";
P_HTM[4645]="*‘anottappī purisapuggalo’ti, bhante, parihānametaṃ;**An imprudent individual is in decline.*";
P_HTM[4646]="*‘kusīto purisapuggalo’ti, bhante, parihānametaṃ;**A lazy individual is in decline.*";
P_HTM[4647]="*‘duppañño purisapuggalo’ti, bhante, parihānametaṃ;**A witless individual is in decline.*";
P_HTM[4648]="*‘kodhano purisapuggalo’ti, bhante, parihānametaṃ;**An irritable individual is in decline.*";
P_HTM[4649]="*‘upanāhī purisapuggalo’ti, bhante, parihānametaṃ;**A hostile individual is in decline.*";
P_HTM[4650]="*‘na santi bhikkhū ovādakā’ti, bhante, parihānametaṃ.**When there are no mendicant advisers there is decline.*";
P_HTM[4651]="*Yassa kassaci, bhante, saddhā atthi kusalesu dhammesu, hirī atthi kusalesu dhammesu, ottappaṃ atthi kusalesu dhammesu, vīriyaṃ atthi kusalesu dhammesu, paññā atthi kusalesu dhammesu, tassa yā ratti vā divaso vā āgacchati, vuddhiyeva pāṭikaṅkhā kusalesu dhammesu, no parihāni.**Sir, whoever has faith, conscience, prudence, energy, and wisdom when it comes to skillful qualities can expect growth, not decline, in skillful qualities, whether by day or by night.*";
P_HTM[4652]="*Seyyathāpi, bhante, juṇhapakkhe candassa yā ratti vā divaso vā āgacchati, vaḍḍhateva vaṇṇena, vaḍḍhati maṇḍalena, vaḍḍhati ābhāya, vaḍḍhati ārohapariṇāhena.**It’s like the moon in the waxing fortnight. Whether by day or by night, its beauty, roundness, light, and diameter and circumference only grow.*";
P_HTM[4653]="*Evameva kho, bhante, yassa kassaci saddhā atthi kusalesu dhammesu …**In the same way, whoever has faith, conscience, prudence, energy, and wisdom when it comes to skillful qualities can expect growth, not decline, in skillful qualities, whether by day or by night.*";
P_HTM[4654]="*hirī atthi … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4655]="*ottappaṃ atthi …* **";
P_HTM[4656]="*vīriyaṃ atthi …* **";
P_HTM[4657]="*paññā atthi kusalesu dhammesu tassa yā ratti vā divaso vā āgacchati, vuddhiyeva pāṭikaṅkhā kusalesu dhammesu, no parihāni.* **";
P_HTM[4658]="*‘Saddho purisapuggalo’ti, bhante, aparihānametaṃ;**A faithful individual doesn’t decline.*";
P_HTM[4659]="*‘hirimā purisapuggalo’ti, bhante, aparihānametaṃ;**An individual with a conscience doesn’t decline.*";
P_HTM[4660]="*‘ottappī purisapuggalo’ti, bhante, aparihānametaṃ;**A prudent individual doesn’t decline.*";
P_HTM[4661]="*‘āraddhavīriyo purisapuggalo’ti, bhante, aparihānametaṃ;**An energetic individual doesn’t decline.*";
P_HTM[4662]="*‘paññavā purisapuggalo’ti, bhante, aparihānametaṃ;**A wise individual doesn’t decline.*";
P_HTM[4663]="*‘akkodhano purisapuggalo’ti, bhante, aparihānametaṃ;**A loving individual doesn’t decline.*";
P_HTM[4664]="*‘anupanāhī purisapuggalo’ti, bhante, aparihānametaṃ;**A kind individual doesn’t decline.*";
P_HTM[4665]="*‘santi bhikkhū ovādakā’ti, bhante, aparihānametan”ti.**When there are mendicant advisers there is no decline.”*";
P_HTM[4666]="*“Sādhu sādhu, kassapa.**“Good, good, Kassapa!*";
P_HTM[4667]="*Yassa kassaci, kassapa, saddhā natthi kusalesu dhammesu … pe …**Whoever has no faith, conscience, prudence, energy, or wisdom when it comes to skillful qualities can expect decline, not growth …*";
P_HTM[4668]="*hirī natthi …* **";
P_HTM[4669]="*ottappaṃ natthi …* **";
P_HTM[4670]="*vīriyaṃ natthi …* **";
P_HTM[4671]="*paññā natthi kusalesu dhammesu tassa yā ratti vā divaso vā āgacchati, hāniyeva pāṭikaṅkhā kusalesu dhammesu, no vuddhi.* **";
P_HTM[4672]="*Seyyathāpi, kassapa, kāḷapakkhe candassa yā ratti vā divaso vā āgacchati, hāyateva vaṇṇena … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4673]="*hāyati ārohapariṇāhena.* **";
P_HTM[4674]="*Evameva kho, kassapa, yassa kassaci saddhā natthi kusalesu dhammesu … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4675]="*hirī natthi …* **";
P_HTM[4676]="*ottappaṃ natthi …* **";
P_HTM[4677]="*vīriyaṃ natthi …* **";
P_HTM[4678]="*paññā natthi kusalesu dhammesu tassa yā ratti vā divaso vā āgacchati, hāniyeva pāṭikaṅkhā kusalesu dhammesu, no vuddhi.* **";
P_HTM[4679]="*‘Assaddho purisapuggalo’ti, kassapa, parihānametaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4680]="*ahiriko … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4681]="*anottappī …* **";
P_HTM[4682]="*kusīto …* **";
P_HTM[4683]="*duppañño …* **";
P_HTM[4684]="*kodhano …* **";
P_HTM[4685]="*‘upanāhī purisapuggalo’ti, kassapa, parihānametaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4686]="*‘na santi bhikkhū ovādakā’ti, kassapa, parihānametaṃ.**When there are no mendicant advisers there is decline.*";
P_HTM[4687]="*Yassa kassaci, kassapa, saddhā atthi kusalesu dhammesu … pe …**Whoever has faith, conscience, prudence, energy, and wisdom when it comes to skillful qualities can expect growth, not decline …*";
P_HTM[4688]="*hirī atthi …* **";
P_HTM[4689]="*ottappaṃ atthi …* **";
P_HTM[4690]="*vīriyaṃ atthi …* **";
P_HTM[4691]="*paññā atthi kusalesu dhammesu tassa yā ratti vā divaso vā āgacchati, vuddhiyeva pāṭikaṅkhā kusalesu dhammesu, no parihāni.* **";
P_HTM[4692]="*Seyyathāpi, kassapa, juṇhapakkhe candassa yā ratti vā divaso vā āgacchati, vaḍḍhateva vaṇṇena, vaḍḍhati maṇḍalena, vaḍḍhati ābhāya, vaḍḍhati ārohapariṇāhena.* **";
P_HTM[4693]="*Evameva kho, kassapa, yassa kassaci saddhā atthi kusalesu dhammesu hirī atthi …* **";
P_HTM[4694]="*ottappaṃ atthi …* **";
P_HTM[4695]="*vīriyaṃ atthi …* **";
P_HTM[4696]="*paññā atthi kusalesu dhammesu tassa yā ratti vā divaso vā āgacchati, vuddhiyeva pāṭikaṅkhā kusalesu dhammesu, no parihāni.* **";
P_HTM[4697]="*‘Saddho purisapuggalo’ti, kassapa, aparihānametaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4698]="*hirimā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4699]="*ottappī …* **";
P_HTM[4700]="*āraddhavīriyo …* **";
P_HTM[4701]="*paññavā …* **";
P_HTM[4702]="*akkodhano …* **";
P_HTM[4703]="*‘anupanāhī purisapuggalo’ti, kassapa, aparihānametaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4704]="*‘santi bhikkhū ovādakā’ti, kassapa, aparihānametan”ti.**When there are mendicant advisers there is no decline.”*";
P_HTM[4705]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4706]="*8. Tatiyaovādasuttaṃ**Advice (3rd)*";
P_HTM[4707]="*Rājagahe kalandakanivāpe.**Near Rājagaha, in the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[4708]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ mahākassapaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then Venerable Mahākassapa went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[4709]="*“ovada, kassapa, bhikkhū;**“Kassapa, advise the mendicants!*";
P_HTM[4710]="*karohi, kassapa, bhikkhūnaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ.**Give them a Dhamma talk!*";
P_HTM[4711]="*Ahaṃ vā, kassapa, bhikkhūnaṃ ovadeyyaṃ tvaṃ vā;**Either you or I should advise the mendicants*";
P_HTM[4712]="*ahaṃ vā bhikkhūnaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ kareyyaṃ tvaṃ vā”ti.**and give them a Dhamma talk.”*";
P_HTM[4713]="*“Dubbacā kho, bhante, etarahi bhikkhū, dovacassakaraṇehi dhammehi samannāgatā, akkhamā, appadakkhiṇaggāhino anusāsanin”ti.**“Sir, the mendicants these days are hard to admonish, having qualities that make them hard to admonish. They’re impatient, and don’t take instruction respectfully.”*";
P_HTM[4714]="*“Tathā hi pana, kassapa, pubbe therā bhikkhū āraññikā ceva ahesuṃ āraññikattassa ca vaṇṇavādino, piṇḍapātikā ceva ahesuṃ piṇḍapātikattassa ca vaṇṇavādino, paṃsukūlikā ceva ahesuṃ paṃsukūlikattassa ca vaṇṇavādino, tecīvarikā ceva ahesuṃ tecīvarikattassa ca vaṇṇavādino, appicchā ceva ahesuṃ appicchatāya ca vaṇṇavādino, santuṭṭhā ceva ahesuṃ santuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādino, pavivittā ceva ahesuṃ pavivekassa ca vaṇṇavādino, asaṃsaṭṭhā ceva ahesuṃ asaṃsaggassa ca vaṇṇavādino, āraddhavīriyā ceva ahesuṃ vīriyārambhassa ca vaṇṇavādino.**“Kassapa, that’s because formerly the senior mendicants lived in the wilderness, ate only alms-food, wore rag robes, and owned just three robes; and they praised these things. They were of few wishes, content, secluded, aloof, and energetic; and they praised these things.*";
P_HTM[4715]="*Tatra yo hoti bhikkhu āraññiko ceva āraññikattassa ca vaṇṇavādī, piṇḍapātiko ceva piṇḍapātikattassa ca vaṇṇavādī, paṃsukūliko ceva paṃsukūlikattassa ca vaṇṇavādī, tecīvariko ceva tecīvarikattassa ca vaṇṇavādī, appiccho ceva appicchatāya ca vaṇṇavādī, santuṭṭho ceva santuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī, pavivitto ceva pavivekassa ca vaṇṇavādī, asaṃsaṭṭho ceva asaṃsaggassa ca vaṇṇavādī, āraddhavīriyo ceva vīriyārambhassa ca vaṇṇavādī, taṃ therā bhikkhū āsanena nimantenti:**The senior mendicants invite such a mendicant to a seat, saying:*";
P_HTM[4716]="*‘ehi, bhikkhu, ko nāmāyaṃ bhikkhu, bhaddako vatāyaṃ bhikkhu, sikkhākāmo vatāyaṃ bhikkhu; ehi, bhikkhu, idaṃ āsanaṃ nisīdāhī’ti.**‘Welcome, mendicant! What is this mendicant’s name? This mendicant is good-natured; he really wants to train. Please, mendicant, take a seat.’*";
P_HTM[4717]="*Tatra, kassapa, navānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ hoti:**Then the junior mendicants think:*";
P_HTM[4718]="*‘yo kira so hoti bhikkhu āraññiko ceva āraññikattassa ca vaṇṇavādī, piṇḍapātiko ceva … pe … paṃsukūliko ceva … tecīvariko ceva … appiccho ceva … santuṭṭho ceva … pavivitto ceva … asaṃsaṭṭho ceva … āraddhavīriyo ceva vīriyārambhassa ca vaṇṇavādī, taṃ therā bhikkhū āsanena nimantenti—**‘It seems that when a mendicant lives in the wilderness … and is energetic, and praises these things, senior mendicants invite them to a seat …’*";
P_HTM[4719]="*ehi, bhikkhu, ko nāmāyaṃ bhikkhu, bhaddako vatāyaṃ bhikkhu, sikkhākāmo vatāyaṃ bhikkhu; ehi, bhikkhu, idaṃ āsanaṃ nisīdāhī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4720]="*Te tathattāya paṭipajjanti;**They practice accordingly.*";
P_HTM[4721]="*tesaṃ taṃ hoti dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya.**That is for their lasting welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[4722]="*Etarahi pana, kassapa, therā bhikkhū na ceva āraññikā na ca āraññikattassa vaṇṇavādino, na ceva piṇḍapātikā na ca piṇḍapātikattassa vaṇṇavādino, na ceva paṃsukūlikā na ca paṃsukūlikattassa vaṇṇavādino, na ceva tecīvarikā na ca tecīvarikattassa vaṇṇavādino, na ceva appicchā na ca appicchatāya vaṇṇavādino, na ceva santuṭṭhā na ca santuṭṭhiyā vaṇṇavādino, na ceva pavivittā na ca pavivekassa vaṇṇavādino, na ceva asaṃsaṭṭhā na ca asaṃsaggassa vaṇṇavādino, na ceva āraddhavīriyā na ca vīriyārambhassa vaṇṇavādino.**But these days, Kassapa, the senior mendicants don’t live in the wilderness … and aren’t energetic; and they don’t praise these things.*";
P_HTM[4723]="*Tatra yo hoti bhikkhu ñāto yasassī lābhī cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ taṃ therā bhikkhū āsanena nimantenti:**When a mendicant is well-known and famous, a recipient of robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick, senior mendicants invite them to a seat:*";
P_HTM[4724]="*‘ehi, bhikkhu, ko nāmāyaṃ bhikkhu, bhaddako vatāyaṃ bhikkhu, sabrahmacārikāmo vatāyaṃ bhikkhu; ehi, bhikkhu, idaṃ āsanaṃ nisīdāhī’ti.**‘Welcome, mendicant! What is this mendicant’s name? This mendicant is good-natured; he really likes his fellow monks. Please, mendicant, take a seat.’*";
P_HTM[4725]="*Tatra, kassapa, navānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ hoti:**Then the junior mendicants think:*";
P_HTM[4726]="*‘yo kira so hoti bhikkhu ñāto yasassī lābhī cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ taṃ therā bhikkhū āsanena nimantenti—**‘It seems that when a mendicant is well-known and famous, a recipient of robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick, senior mendicants invite them to a seat …’*";
P_HTM[4727]="*ehi, bhikkhu, ko nāmāyaṃ bhikkhu, bhaddako vatāyaṃ bhikkhu, sabrahmacārikāmo vatāyaṃ bhikkhu; ehi, bhikkhu, idaṃ āsanaṃ nisīdāhī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4728]="*Te tathattāya paṭipajjanti.**They practice accordingly.*";
P_HTM[4729]="*Tesaṃ taṃ hoti dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya.**That is for their lasting harm and suffering.*";
P_HTM[4730]="*Yañhi taṃ, kassapa, sammā vadamāno vadeyya:**And if it could ever be rightly said that*";
P_HTM[4731]="*‘upaddutā brahmacārī brahmacārūpaddavena abhipatthanā brahmacārī brahmacāriabhipatthanenā’ti, etarahi taṃ, kassapa, sammā vadamāno vadeyya: ‘upaddutā brahmacārī brahmacārūpaddavena abhipatthanā brahmacārī brahmacāriabhipatthanenā’”ti.**spiritual practitioners are imperiled by the peril of a spiritual practitioner, and vanquished by the vanquishing of a spiritual practitioner, it is these days that this could be rightly said.”*";
P_HTM[4732]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4733]="*9. Jhānābhiññasuttaṃ**Absorptions and Insights*";
P_HTM[4734]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4735]="*“Ahaṃ, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhāmi vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharāmi.**“Mendicants, whenever I want, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, I enter and remain in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[4736]="*Kassapopi, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhati vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**And so does Kassapa.*";
P_HTM[4737]="*Ahaṃ, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhāmi vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharāmi.**Whenever I want, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, I enter and remain in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[4738]="*Kassapopi, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhati vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**And so does Kassapa.*";
P_HTM[4739]="*Ahaṃ, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhāmi pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharāmi sato ca sampajāno sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedemi, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharāmi.**Whenever I want, with the fading away of rapture, I enter and remain in the third absorption, where I meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’*";
P_HTM[4740]="*Kassapopi, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhati pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati sato ca sampajāno, sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**And so does Kassapa.*";
P_HTM[4741]="*Ahaṃ, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhāmi sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharāmi.**Whenever I want, with the giving up of pleasure and pain, and the ending of former happiness and sadness, I enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness.*";
P_HTM[4742]="*Kassapopi, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhati sukhassa ca pahānā … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**And so does Kassapa.*";
P_HTM[4743]="*Ahaṃ, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhāmi sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ananto ākāsoti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharāmi.**Whenever I want, going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, I enter and remain in the dimension of infinite space.*";
P_HTM[4744]="*Kassapopi, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhati sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā … pe … ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**And so does Kassapa.*";
P_HTM[4745]="*Ahaṃ, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhāmi sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma anantaṃ viññāṇanti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharāmi.**Whenever I want, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, I enter and remain in the dimension of infinite consciousness.*";
P_HTM[4746]="*Kassapopi, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhati sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma anantaṃ viññāṇanti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**And so does Kassapa.*";
P_HTM[4747]="*Ahaṃ, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhāmi sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharāmi.**Whenever I want, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, I enter and remain in the dimension of nothingness.*";
P_HTM[4748]="*Kassapopi, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhati … pe … ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**And so does Kassapa.*";
P_HTM[4749]="*Ahaṃ, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhāmi sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharāmi.**Whenever I want, going totally beyond the dimension of nothingness, I enter and remain in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.*";
P_HTM[4750]="*Kassapopi, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhati … pe … nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati.**And so does Kassapa.*";
P_HTM[4751]="*Ahaṃ, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhāmi sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ upasampajja viharāmi.**Whenever I want, going totally beyond the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, I enter and remain in the cessation of perception and feeling.*";
P_HTM[4752]="*Kassapopi, bhikkhave … pe … saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ upasampajja viharati.**And so does Kassapa.*";
P_HTM[4753]="*Ahaṃ, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhāmi anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhomi—ekopi hutvā bahudhā homi, bahudhāpi hutvā eko homi; āvibhāvaṃ, tirobhāvaṃ, tirokuṭṭaṃ, tiropākāraṃ, tiropabbataṃ, asajjamāno gacchāmi, seyyathāpi ākāse; pathaviyāpi ummujjanimujjaṃ karomi, seyyathāpi udake; udakepi abhijjamāne gacchāmi, seyyathāpi pathaviyaṃ; ākāsepi pallaṅkena kamāmi, seyyathāpi pakkhī sakuṇo; imepi candimasūriye evaṃmahiddhike evaṃmahānubhāve pāṇinā parimasāmi parimajjāmi; yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vattemi.**Whenever I want, I wield the many kinds of psychic power: multiplying myself and becoming one again; going unimpeded through a wall, a rampart, or a mountain as if through space; diving in and out of the earth as if it were water; walking on water as if it were earth; flying cross-legged through the sky like a bird; touching and stroking with the hand the sun and moon, so mighty and powerful. I control the body as far as the Brahmā realm.*";
P_HTM[4754]="*Kassapopi, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhati anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhoti … pe … yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vatteti.**And so does Kassapa.*";
P_HTM[4755]="*Ahaṃ, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhāmi dibbāya sotadhātuyā visuddhāya atikkantamānusikāya ubho sadde suṇāmi, dibbe ca mānuse ca, ye dūre santike ca.**Whenever I want, with clairaudience that is purified and superhuman, I hear both kinds of sounds, human and divine, whether near or far.*";
P_HTM[4756]="*Kassapopi, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhati dibbāya sotadhātuyā … pe … dūre santike ca.**And so does Kassapa.*";
P_HTM[4757]="*Ahaṃ, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhāmi parasattānaṃ parapuggalānaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi—sarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ sarāgaṃ cittanti pajānāmi, vītarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ vītarāgaṃ cittanti pajānāmi, sadosaṃ vā cittaṃ … pe … vītadosaṃ vā cittaṃ … samohaṃ vā cittaṃ … vītamohaṃ vā cittaṃ … saṅkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ … vikkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ … mahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ … amahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ … sauttaraṃ vā cittaṃ … anuttaraṃ vā cittaṃ … samāhitaṃ vā cittaṃ … asamāhitaṃ vā cittaṃ … vimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ … avimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ avimuttaṃ cittanti pajānāmi.**Whenever I want, I understand the minds of other beings and individuals, having comprehended them with my mind. I understand mind with greed as ‘mind with greed’, and mind without greed as ‘mind without greed’; mind with hate … mind without hate … mind with delusion … mind without delusion … constricted mind … scattered mind … expansive mind … unexpansive mind … mind that is not supreme … mind that is supreme … mind immersed in samādhi … mind not immersed in samādhi … freed mind … unfreed mind …*";
P_HTM[4758]="*Kassapopi, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhati parasattānaṃ parapuggalānaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāti—sarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ sarāgaṃ cittanti pajānāti … pe … avimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ avimuttaṃ cittanti pajānāti.**And so does Kassapa.*";
P_HTM[4759]="*Ahaṃ, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhāmi anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo tissopi jātiyo catassopi jātiyo pañcapi jātiyo dasapi jātiyo vīsampi jātiyo tiṃsampi jātiyo cattālīsampi jātiyo paññāsampi jātiyo jātisatampi jātisahassampi jātisatasahassampi, anekepi saṃvaṭṭakappe anekepi vivaṭṭakappe anekepi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭakappe: ‘amutrāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto amutra udapādiṃ; tatrāpāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto idhūpapanno’ti. Iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi.**Whenever I want, I recollect my many kinds of past lives. That is: one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the world expanding, many eons of the world contracting and expanding. I remember: ‘There, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn somewhere else. There, too, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn here.’ And so I recollect my many kinds of past lives, with features and details.*";
P_HTM[4760]="*Kassapopi, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhati anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati.**And so does Kassapa.*";
P_HTM[4761]="*Ahaṃ, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhāmi dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passāmi cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe, sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāmi: ‘ime vata, bhonto, sattā kāyaduccaritena samannāgatā vacīduccaritena samannāgatā manoduccaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ upavādakā micchādiṭṭhikā micchādiṭṭhikammasamādānā; te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannā, ime vā pana, bhonto, sattā kāyasucaritena samannāgatā vacīsucaritena samannāgatā manosucaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ anupavādakā sammādiṭṭhikā sammādiṭṭhikammasamādānā; te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapannā’ti. Iti dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passāmi cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe, sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāmi.**Whenever I want, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, I see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. I understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds. ‘These dear beings did bad things by way of body, speech, and mind. They spoke ill of the noble ones; they had wrong view; and they chose to act out of that wrong view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. These dear beings, however, did good things by way of body, speech, and mind. They never spoke ill of the noble ones; they had right view; and they chose to act out of that right view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.’ And so, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, I see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. I understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.*";
P_HTM[4762]="*Kassapopi, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhati dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne … pe … yathākammūpage satte pajānāti.**And so does Kassapa.*";
P_HTM[4763]="*Ahaṃ, bhikkhave, āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmi.**I have realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And I live having realized it with my own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[4764]="*Kassapopi, bhikkhave, āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharatī”ti.**And so does Kassapa.”*";
P_HTM[4765]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4766]="*10. Upassayasuttaṃ**The Nuns’ Quarters*";
P_HTM[4767]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[4768]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā mahākassapo sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time Venerable Mahākassapa was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[4769]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yenāyasmā mahākassapo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahākassapaṃ etadavoca:**Then Venerable Ānanda robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to Mahākassapa and said,*";
P_HTM[4770]="*“āyāma, bhante kassapa, yena aññataro bhikkhunupassayo tenupasaṅkamissāmā”ti.**“Kassapa, come, sir. Let’s go to one of the nuns’ quarters.”*";
P_HTM[4771]="*“Gaccha tvaṃ, āvuso ānanda, bahukicco tvaṃ bahukaraṇīyo”ti.**“You go, Reverend Ānanda. You have many duties and responsibilities.”*";
P_HTM[4772]="*Dutiyampi kho āyasmā ānando āyasmantaṃ mahākassapaṃ etadavoca:**And a second time …*";
P_HTM[4773]="*“āyāma, bhante kassapa, yena aññataro bhikkhunupassayo tenupasaṅkamissāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4774]="*“Gaccha tvaṃ, āvuso ānanda, bahukicco tvaṃ bahukaraṇīyo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4775]="*Tatiyampi kho āyasmā ānando āyasmantaṃ mahākassapaṃ etadavoca:**And a third time, Ānanda said,*";
P_HTM[4776]="*“āyāma, bhante kassapa, yena aññataro bhikkhunupassayo tenupasaṅkamissāmā”ti.**“Kassapa, come, sir. Let’s go to one of the nuns’ quarters.”*";
P_HTM[4777]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya āyasmatā ānandena pacchāsamaṇena yena aññataro bhikkhunupassayo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**Then Venerable Mahākassapa robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went with Venerable Ānanda as his second monk to one of the nuns’ quarters, where he sat on the seat spread out.*";
P_HTM[4778]="*Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhuniyo yenāyasmā mahākassapo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahākassapaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu.**And then several nuns went up to Mahākassapa, bowed, and sat down to one side.*";
P_HTM[4779]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho tā bhikkhuniyo āyasmā mahākassapo dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi.**Mahākassapa educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired those nuns with a Dhamma talk,*";
P_HTM[4780]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo tā bhikkhuniyo dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi.**after which he got up from his seat and left.*";
P_HTM[4781]="*Atha kho thullatissā bhikkhunī anattamanā anattamanavācaṃ nicchāresi:**But the nun Thullatissā was upset and blurted out,*";
P_HTM[4782]="*“kiṃ pana ayyo mahākassapo, ayyassa ānandassa vedehamunino sammukhā dhammaṃ bhāsitabbaṃ maññati?**“What is Master Mahākassapa thinking, that he’d teach Dhamma in front of Master Ānanda, the Videhan sage?*";
P_HTM[4783]="*Seyyathāpi nāma sūcivāṇijako sūcikārassa santike sūciṃ vikketabbaṃ maññeyya;**He’s like a needle seller who thinks they can sell a needle to a needle maker!”*";
P_HTM[4784]="*evameva ayyo mahākassapo ayyassa ānandassa vedehamunino sammukhā dhammaṃ bhāsitabbaṃ maññatī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4785]="*Assosi kho āyasmā mahākassapo thullatissāya bhikkhuniyā imaṃ vācaṃ bhāsamānāya.**Mahākassapa heard Thullatissā say these words,*";
P_HTM[4786]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:**and he said to Ānanda,*";
P_HTM[4787]="*“kiṃ nu kho, āvuso ānanda, ahaṃ sūcivāṇijako, tvaṃ sūcikāro;**“Is that right, Reverend Ānanda? Am I the needle seller and you the needle maker?*";
P_HTM[4788]="*udāhu ahaṃ sūcikāro, tvaṃ sūcivāṇijako”ti?**Or am I the needle maker and you the needle seller?”*";
P_HTM[4789]="*“Khama, bhante kassapa, bālo mātugāmo”ti.**“Forgive her, sir. The woman’s a fool.”*";
P_HTM[4790]="*“Āgamehi tvaṃ, āvuso ānanda, mā te saṅgho uttari upaparikkhi.**“Hold on, Reverend Ānanda! Don’t make the Saṅgha investigate you further!*";
P_HTM[4791]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, āvuso ānanda,**What do you think, Reverend Ānanda?*";
P_HTM[4792]="*api nu tvaṃ bhagavato sammukhā bhikkhusaṅghe upanīto:**Was it you who the Buddha brought up before the Saṅgha of mendicants, saying:*";
P_HTM[4793]="*‘ahaṃ, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhāmi vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharāmi.**‘Mendicants, whenever I want, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, I enter and remain in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[4794]="*Ānandopi, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhati vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharatī’”ti?**And so does Ānanda’?”*";
P_HTM[4795]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4796]="*“Ahaṃ kho, āvuso, bhagavato sammukhā bhikkhusaṅghe upanīto:**“I was the one the Buddha brought up before the Saṅgha of mendicants, saying:*";
P_HTM[4797]="*‘ahaṃ, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhāmi vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharāmi.**‘Mendicants, whenever I want, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, I enter and remain in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[4798]="*Kassapopi, bhikkhave, yāvade ākaṅkhati vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharatī’ti … pe ….**And so does Kassapa. …’*";
P_HTM[4799]="*(Navannaṃ anupubbavihārasamāpattīnaṃ pañcannañca abhiññānaṃ evaṃ vitthāro veditabbo.)**(The nine progressive meditations and the five insights should be treated in full.)*";
P_HTM[4800]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, āvuso ānanda,**What do you think, Reverend Ānanda?*";
P_HTM[4801]="*api nu tvaṃ bhagavato sammukhā bhikkhusaṅghe upanīto:**Was it you who the Buddha brought up before the Saṅgha of mendicants, saying:*";
P_HTM[4802]="*‘ahaṃ, bhikkhave, āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmi.**‘I have realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And I live having realized it with my own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[4803]="*Ānandopi, bhikkhave, āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharatī’”ti?**And so does Ānanda’?”*";
P_HTM[4804]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[4805]="*“Ahaṃ kho, āvuso, bhagavato sammukhā bhikkhusaṅghe upanīto:**“I was the one the Buddha brought up before the Saṅgha of mendicants, saying:*";
P_HTM[4806]="*‘ahaṃ, bhikkhave, āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmi.**‘I have realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And I live having realized it with my own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[4807]="*Kassapopi, bhikkhave, āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharatī’ti.**And so does Kassapa.’*";
P_HTM[4808]="*Sattaratanaṃ vā, āvuso, nāgaṃ aḍḍhaṭṭhamaratanaṃ vā tālapattikāya chādetabbaṃ maññeyya, yo me cha abhiññā chādetabbaṃ maññeyyā”ti.**Reverend, you might as well think to hide a bull elephant that’s three or three and a half meters tall behind a palm leaf as to hide my six insights.”*";
P_HTM[4809]="*Cavittha ca pana thullatissā bhikkhunī brahmacariyamhāti.**But the nun Thullatissā fell from the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[4810]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4811]="*11. Cīvarasuttaṃ**Robes*";
P_HTM[4812]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā mahākassapo rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time Venerable Mahākassapa was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[4813]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā ānando dakkhiṇagirismiṃ cārikaṃ carati mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ.**Now at that time Venerable Ānanda was wandering in the Southern Hills together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants.*";
P_HTM[4814]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato ānandassa tiṃsamattā saddhivihārino bhikkhū sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattā bhavanti yebhuyyena kumārabhūtā.**And at that time thirty of Ānanda’s mendicant pupils rejected the training and returned to a lesser life. Most of them were youths.*";
P_HTM[4815]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando dakkhiṇagirismiṃ yathābhirantaṃ cārikaṃ caritvā yena rājagahaṃ veḷuvanaṃ kalandakanivāpo yenāyasmā mahākassapo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahākassapaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āyasmā mahākassapo etadavoca:**When Venerable Ānanda had wandered in the Southern Hills as long as he wished, he set out for Rājagaha, to the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. He went up to Venerable Mahākassapa, bowed, and sat down to one side. Mahākassapa said to him:*";
P_HTM[4816]="*“kati nu kho, āvuso ānanda, atthavase paṭicca bhagavatā kulesu tikabhojanaṃ paññattan”ti?**“Reverend Ānanda, for how many reasons did the Buddha lay down a rule against eating in groups of more than three among families?”*";
P_HTM[4817]="*“Tayo kho, bhante kassapa, atthavase paṭicca bhagavatā kulesu tikabhojanaṃ paññattaṃ—**“Sir, the Buddha laid down that rule for three reasons.*";
P_HTM[4818]="*dummaṅkūnaṃ puggalānaṃ niggahāya pesalānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ phāsuvihārāya, mā pāpicchā pakkhaṃ nissāya saṃghaṃ bhindeyyuṃ, kulānuddayatāya ca.**For keeping difficult persons in check and for the comfort of good-hearted mendicants. To prevent those of wicked desires from taking sides and dividing the Saṅgha. And out of consideration for families.*";
P_HTM[4819]="*Ime kho, bhante kassapa, tayo atthavase paṭicca bhagavatā kulesu tikabhojanaṃ paññattan”ti.**These are the three reasons why the Buddha laid down that rule.”*";
P_HTM[4820]="*“Atha kiñcarahi tvaṃ, āvuso ānanda, imehi navehi bhikkhūhi indriyesu aguttadvārehi bhojane amattaññūhi jāgariyaṃ ananuyuttehi saddhiṃ cārikaṃ carasi?**“So what exactly are you doing, wandering together with these junior mendicants? They don’t guard their sense doors, they eat too much, and they’re not committed to wakefulness.*";
P_HTM[4821]="*Sassaghātaṃ maññe carasi, kulūpaghātaṃ maññe carasi.**It’s like you’re wandering about wrecking crops and ruining families!*";
P_HTM[4822]="*Olujjati kho te, āvuso ānanda, parisā;**Your following is falling apart, Reverend Ānanda,*";
P_HTM[4823]="*palujjanti kho te, āvuso, navappāyā.**and those just getting started are slipping away.*";
P_HTM[4824]="*Na vāyaṃ kumārako mattamaññāsī”ti.**Yet this boy knows no bounds!”*";
P_HTM[4825]="*“Api me, bhante kassapa, sirasmiṃ palitāni jātāni.**“Though there are grey hairs on my head,*";
P_HTM[4826]="*Atha ca pana mayaṃ ajjāpi āyasmato mahākassapassa kumārakavādā na muccāmā”ti.**I still can’t escape being called a boy by Venerable Mahākassapa.”*";
P_HTM[4827]="*“Tathā hi pana tvaṃ, āvuso ānanda, imehi navehi bhikkhūhi indriyesu aguttadvārehi bhojane amattaññūhi jāgariyaṃ ananuyuttehi saddhiṃ cārikaṃ carasi, sassaghātaṃ maññe carasi, kulūpaghātaṃ maññe carasi.**“It’s because you wander with these junior mendicants. …*";
P_HTM[4828]="*Olujjati kho te, āvuso ānanda, parisā;**Your following is falling apart, Reverend Ānanda,*";
P_HTM[4829]="*palujjanti kho te, āvuso, navappāyā.**and those just getting started are slipping away.*";
P_HTM[4830]="*Na vāyaṃ kumārako mattamaññāsī”ti.**Yet this boy knows no bounds!”*";
P_HTM[4831]="*Assosi kho thullanandā bhikkhunī:**The nun Thullanandā heard a rumor that*";
P_HTM[4832]="*“ayyena kira mahākassapena ayyo ānando vedehamuni kumārakavādena apasādito”ti.**Master Mahākassapa had rebuked Master Ānanda the Videhan sage by calling him a boy.*";
P_HTM[4833]="*Atha kho thullanandā bhikkhunī anattamanā anattamanavācaṃ nicchāresi:**She was upset and blurted out,*";
P_HTM[4834]="*“kiṃ pana ayyo mahākassapo aññatitthiyapubbo samāno ayyaṃ ānandaṃ vedehamuniṃ kumārakavādena apasādetabbaṃ maññatī”ti.**“How can Master Mahākassapa, who formerly followed another path, presume to rebuke Master Ānanda the Videhan sage by calling him a boy?”*";
P_HTM[4835]="*Assosi kho āyasmā mahākassapo thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā imaṃ vācaṃ bhāsamānāya.**Mahākassapa heard Thullanandā say these words,*";
P_HTM[4836]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:**and he said to Ānanda,*";
P_HTM[4837]="*“tagghāvuso ānanda, thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā sahasā appaṭisaṅkhā vācā bhāsitā.**“Indeed, Reverend Ānanda, the nun Thullanandā spoke rashly and without reflection.*";
P_HTM[4838]="*Yatvāhaṃ, āvuso, kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito, nābhijānāmi aññaṃ satthāraṃ uddisitā, aññatra tena bhagavatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena.**Since I shaved off my hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and went forth from the lay life to homelessness, I don’t recall acknowledging any other teacher apart from the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4839]="*Pubbe me, āvuso, agārikabhūtassa sato etadahosi:**Formerly when I was still a layman, I thought:*";
P_HTM[4840]="*‘sambādho gharāvāso rajāpatho, abbhokāso pabbajjā.**‘Living in a house is cramped and dirty, but the life of one gone forth is wide open.*";
P_HTM[4841]="*Nayidaṃ sukaraṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvasatā ekantaparipuṇṇaṃ ekantaparisuddhaṃ saṅkhalikhitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ.**It’s not easy for someone living at home to lead the spiritual life utterly full and pure, like a polished shell.*";
P_HTM[4842]="*Yannūnāhaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyan’ti.**Why don’t I shave off my hair and beard, dress in ocher robes, and go forth from the lay life to homelessness?’*";
P_HTM[4843]="*So khvāhaṃ, āvuso, aparena samayena paṭapilotikānaṃ saṅghāṭiṃ kāretvā ye loke arahanto te uddissa kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajiṃ.**After some time I made an outer robe of patches and, in the name of the perfected ones in the world, I shaved off my hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and went forth from the lay life to homelessness.*";
P_HTM[4844]="*So evaṃ pabbajito samāno addhānamaggappaṭipanno addasaṃ bhagavantaṃ antarā ca rājagahaṃ antarā ca nāḷandaṃ bahuputte cetiye nisinnaṃ.**When I had gone forth, I traveled along the road between Rājagaha and Nālanda, where I saw the Buddha sitting at the Bahuputta Shrine.*";
P_HTM[4845]="*Disvāna me etadahosi:**Seeing him, I thought:*";
P_HTM[4846]="*‘satthārañca vatāhaṃ passeyyaṃ, bhagavantameva passeyyaṃ;**‘If I’m ever to see a Teacher, it would be this Blessed One!*";
P_HTM[4847]="*sugatañca vatāhaṃ passeyyaṃ, bhagavantameva passeyyaṃ;**If I’m ever to see a Holy One, it would be this Blessed One!*";
P_HTM[4848]="*sammāsambuddhañca vatāhaṃ passeyyaṃ;**If I’m ever to see a fully awakened Buddha, it would be this Blessed One!’*";
P_HTM[4849]="*bhagavantameva passeyyan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4850]="*So khvāhaṃ, āvuso, tattheva bhagavato pādesu sirasā nipatitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavocaṃ:**Then I bowed with my head at the Buddha’s feet and said:*";
P_HTM[4851]="*‘satthā me, bhante, bhagavā, sāvakohamasmi;**‘Sir, the Buddha is my Teacher, I am his disciple!*";
P_HTM[4852]="*satthā me, bhante, bhagavā, sāvakohamasmī’ti.**The Buddha is my Teacher, I am his disciple!’*";
P_HTM[4853]="*Evaṃ vutte, maṃ, āvuso, bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said to me,*";
P_HTM[4854]="*‘yo kho, kassapa, evaṃ sabbacetasā samannāgataṃ sāvakaṃ ajānaññeva vadeyya jānāmīti, apassaññeva vadeyya passāmīti, muddhāpi tassa vipateyya.**‘Kassapa, if anyone was to say to such a wholehearted disciple that they know when they don’t know, or that they see when they don’t see, their head would explode.*";
P_HTM[4855]="*Ahaṃ kho pana, kassapa, jānaññeva vadāmi jānāmīti, passaññeva vadāmi passāmīti.**But Kassapa, when I say that I know and see I really do know and see.*";
P_HTM[4856]="*Tasmātiha te, kassapa, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[4857]="*“tibbaṃ me hirottappaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ bhavissati theresu navesu majjhimesū”ti.**“I will set up a keen sense of conscience and prudence for seniors, juniors, and those in the middle.”*";
P_HTM[4858]="*Evañhi te, kassapa, sikkhitabbaṃ.**That’s how you should train.*";
P_HTM[4859]="*Tasmātiha te, kassapa, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**And you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[4860]="*“yaṃ kiñci dhammaṃ suṇissāmi kusalūpasaṃhitaṃ sabbaṃ taṃ aṭṭhiṃ katvā manasi karitvā sabbacetasā samannāharitvā ohitasoto dhammaṃ suṇissāmī”ti.**“Whenever I hear a teaching connected with what’s skillful, I will pay heed, pay attention, engage wholeheartedly, and lend an ear to that teaching.”*";
P_HTM[4861]="*Evañhi te, kassapa, sikkhitabbaṃ.**That’s how you should train.*";
P_HTM[4862]="*Tasmātiha te, kassapa, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**And you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[4863]="*“sātasahagatā ca me kāyagatāsati na vijahissatī”ti.**“I will never neglect mindfulness of the body that is full of pleasure.”*";
P_HTM[4864]="*Evañhi te, kassapa, sikkhitabbanti’.**That’s how you should train.’*";
P_HTM[4865]="*Atha kho maṃ, āvuso, bhagavā iminā ovādena ovaditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi.**And when the Buddha had given me this advice he got up from his seat and left.*";
P_HTM[4866]="*Sattāhameva khvāhaṃ, āvuso, saraṇo raṭṭhapiṇḍaṃ bhuñjiṃ aṭṭhamiyā aññā udapādi.**For seven days I ate the nation’s almsfood as a debtor. On the eighth day I was enlightened.*";
P_HTM[4867]="*Atha kho, āvuso, bhagavā maggā okkamma yena aññataraṃ rukkhamūlaṃ tenupasaṅkami.**And then the Buddha left the road and went to the root of a tree.*";
P_HTM[4868]="*Atha khvāhaṃ, āvuso, paṭapilotikānaṃ saṅghāṭiṃ catugguṇaṃ paññapetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavocaṃ:**So I spread out my outer robe of patches folded in four and said to him,*";
P_HTM[4869]="*‘idha, bhante, bhagavā nisīdatu, yaṃ mamassa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā’ti.**‘Sir, sit here. That would be for my lasting welfare and happiness.’*";
P_HTM[4870]="*Nisīdi kho, āvuso, bhagavā paññatte āsane.**The Buddha sat on the seat spread out*";
P_HTM[4871]="*Nisajja kho maṃ, āvuso, bhagavā etadavoca:**and said to me,*";
P_HTM[4872]="*‘mudukā kho tyāyaṃ, kassapa, paṭapilotikānaṃ saṅghāṭī’ti.**‘Kassapa, this outer robe of patches is soft.’*";
P_HTM[4873]="*‘Paṭiggaṇhātu me, bhante, bhagavā paṭapilotikānaṃ saṅghāṭiṃ anukampaṃ upādāyā’ti.**‘Sir, please accept my outer robe of patches out of compassion.’*";
P_HTM[4874]="*‘Dhāressasi pana me tvaṃ, kassapa, sāṇāni paṃsukūlāni nibbasanānī’ti.**‘In that case, Kassapa, will you wear my worn-out hempen rag robe?’*";
P_HTM[4875]="*‘Dhāressāmahaṃ, bhante, bhagavato sāṇāni paṃsukūlāni nibbasanānī’ti.**‘I will wear it, sir.’*";
P_HTM[4876]="*So khvāhaṃ, āvuso, paṭapilotikānaṃ saṅghāṭiṃ bhagavato pādāsiṃ.**And so I presented my outer robe of patches to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[4877]="*Ahaṃ pana bhagavato sāṇāni paṃsukūlāni nibbasanāni paṭipajjiṃ.**and the Buddha presented me with his worn-out hempen rag robe.*";
P_HTM[4878]="*Yañhi taṃ, āvuso, sammā vadamāno vadeyya:**For if anyone should be rightly called*";
P_HTM[4879]="*‘bhagavato putto oraso mukhato jāto dhammajo dhammanimmito dhammadāyādo, paṭiggahitāni sāṇāni paṃsukūlāni nibbasanānī’ti, mamaṃ taṃ sammā vadamāno vadeyya:**the Buddha’s true-born child, born from his mouth, born of the teaching, created by the teaching, heir to the teaching, and receiver of his worn-out hempen rag robes, it’s me.*";
P_HTM[4880]="*‘bhagavato putto oraso mukhato jāto dhammajo dhammanimmito dhammadāyādo, paṭiggahitāni sāṇāni paṃsukūlāni nibbasanānī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[4881]="*Ahaṃ kho, āvuso, yāvade ākaṅkhāmi vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharāmi.**Whenever I want, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, I enter and remain in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected. …*";
P_HTM[4882]="*Ahaṃ kho, āvuso, yāvade ākaṅkhāmi … pe …* **";
P_HTM[4883]="*(navannaṃ anupubbavihārasamāpattīnaṃ pañcannañca abhiññānaṃ evaṃ vitthāro veditabbo.)**(The nine progressive meditations and the five insights should be treated in full.)*";
P_HTM[4884]="*Ahaṃ kho, āvuso, āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmi;**I have realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And I live having realized it with my own insight due to the ending of defilements.*";
P_HTM[4885]="*sattaratanaṃ vā, āvuso, nāgaṃ aḍḍhaṭṭhamaratanaṃ vā tālapattikāya chādetabbaṃ maññeyya, yo me cha abhiññā chādetabbaṃ maññeyyā”ti.**Reverend, you might as well think to hide a bull elephant that’s three or three and a half meters tall behind a palm leaf as to hide my six insights.”*";
P_HTM[4886]="*Cavittha ca pana thullanandā bhikkhunī brahmacariyamhāti.**But the nun Thullanandā fell from the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[4887]="*Ekādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4888]="*12. Paraṃmaraṇasuttaṃ**The Realized One After Death*";
P_HTM[4889]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ca mahākassapo āyasmā ca sāriputto bārāṇasiyaṃ viharanti isipatane migadāye.**At one time Venerable Mahākassapa and Venerable Sāriputta were staying near Benares, in the deer park at Isipatana.*";
P_HTM[4890]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yenāyasmā mahākassapo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā mahākassapena saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Sāriputta came out of retreat, went to Venerable Mahākassapa, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[4891]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ mahākassapaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to Mahākassapa:*";
P_HTM[4892]="*“kiṃ nu kho, āvuso kassapa, hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti?**“Reverend Kassapa, does a Realized One exist after death?”*";
P_HTM[4893]="*“Abyākataṃ kho etaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā:**“Reverend, this has not been declared by the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[4894]="*‘hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4895]="*“Kiṃ panāvuso, na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti?**“Well then, does a Realized One not exist after death?”*";
P_HTM[4896]="*“Evampi kho, āvuso, abyākataṃ bhagavatā:**“This too has not been declared by the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[4897]="*‘na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4898]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti?**“Well then, does a Realized One both exist and not exist after death?”*";
P_HTM[4899]="*“Abyākataṃ kho etaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā:**“This too has not been declared by the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[4900]="*‘hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4901]="*“Kiṃ panāvuso, neva hoti, na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti?**“Well then, does a Realized One neither exist nor not exist after death?”*";
P_HTM[4902]="*“Evampi kho, āvuso, abyākataṃ bhagavatā:**“This too has not been declared by the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[4903]="*‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4904]="*“Kasmā cetaṃ, āvuso, abyākataṃ bhagavatā”ti?**“And why has this not been declared by the Buddha?”*";
P_HTM[4905]="*“Na hetaṃ, āvuso, atthasaṃhitaṃ nādibrahmacariyakaṃ na nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati.**“Because it’s not beneficial or relevant to the fundamentals of the spiritual life. It doesn’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[4906]="*Tasmā taṃ abyākataṃ bhagavatā”ti.**That’s why it has not been declared by the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[4907]="*“Atha kiñcarahāvuso, byākataṃ bhagavatā”ti?**“So what now has been declared by the Buddha?”*";
P_HTM[4908]="*“Idaṃ ‘dukkhan’ti kho, āvuso, byākataṃ bhagavatā;**“‘This is suffering’ has been declared by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4909]="*ayaṃ ‘dukkhasamudayo’ti byākataṃ bhagavatā;**‘This is the origin of suffering’ …*";
P_HTM[4910]="*ayaṃ ‘dukkhanirodho’ti byākataṃ bhagavatā;**‘This is the cessation of suffering’ …*";
P_HTM[4911]="*ayaṃ ‘dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti byākataṃ bhagavatā”ti.**‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’ has been declared by the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[4912]="*“Kasmā cetaṃ, āvuso, byākataṃ bhagavatā”ti?**“And why has this been declared by the Buddha?”*";
P_HTM[4913]="*“Etañhi, āvuso, atthasaṃhitaṃ etaṃ ādibrahmacariyakaṃ etaṃ nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati.**“Because it’s beneficial and relevant to the fundamentals of the spiritual life. It leads to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment.*";
P_HTM[4914]="*Tasmā taṃ byākataṃ bhagavatā”ti.**That’s why it has been declared by the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[4915]="*Dvādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4916]="*13. Saddhammappatirūpakasuttaṃ**The Counterfeit of the True Teaching*";
P_HTM[4917]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[4918]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[4919]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā mahākassapo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Venerable Mahākassapa went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[4920]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu ko paccayo, yena pubbe appatarāni ceva sikkhāpadāni ahesuṃ bahutarā ca bhikkhū aññāya saṇṭhahiṃsu?**“What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why there used to be fewer training rules but more enlightened mendicants?*";
P_HTM[4921]="*Ko pana, bhante, hetu ko paccayo, yenetarahi bahutarāni ceva sikkhāpadāni appatarā ca bhikkhū aññāya saṇṭhahantī”ti?**And what is the cause, what is the reason why these days there are more training rules and fewer enlightened mendicants?”*";
P_HTM[4922]="*“Evañcetaṃ, kassapa, hoti sattesu hāyamānesu saddhamme antaradhāyamāne, bahutarāni ceva sikkhāpadāni honti appatarā ca bhikkhū aññāya saṇṭhahanti.**“That’s how it is, Kassapa. When sentient beings are in decline and the true teaching is disappearing there are more training rules and fewer enlightened mendicants.*";
P_HTM[4923]="*Na tāva, kassapa, saddhammassa antaradhānaṃ hoti yāva na saddhammappatirūpakaṃ loke uppajjati.**The true teaching doesn’t disappear as long the counterfeit of the true teaching hasn’t appeared in the world.*";
P_HTM[4924]="*Yato ca kho, kassapa, saddhammappatirūpakaṃ loke uppajjati, atha saddhammassa antaradhānaṃ hoti.**But when the counterfeit of the true teaching appears in the world then the true teaching disappears.*";
P_HTM[4925]="*Seyyathāpi, kassapa, na tāva jātarūpassa antaradhānaṃ hoti yāva na jātarūpappatirūpakaṃ loke uppajjati.**It’s like true gold, which doesn’t disappear as long as counterfeit gold hasn’t appeared in the world.*";
P_HTM[4926]="*Yato ca kho, kassapa, jātarūpappatirūpakaṃ loke uppajjati, atha kho jātarūpassa antaradhānaṃ hoti.**But when counterfeit gold appears in the world then real gold disappears.*";
P_HTM[4927]="*Evameva kho, kassapa, na tāva saddhammassa antaradhānaṃ hoti yāva na saddhammappatirūpakaṃ loke uppajjati.**In the same way, the true teaching doesn’t disappear as long the counterfeit of the true teaching hasn’t appeared in the world.*";
P_HTM[4928]="*Yato ca kho, kassapa, saddhammappatirūpakaṃ loke uppajjati, atha saddhammassa antaradhānaṃ hoti.**But when the counterfeit of the true teaching appears in the world then the true teaching disappears.*";
P_HTM[4929]="*Na kho, kassapa, pathavīdhātu saddhammaṃ antaradhāpeti, na āpodhātu saddhammaṃ antaradhāpeti, na tejodhātu saddhammaṃ antaradhāpeti, na vāyodhātu saddhammaṃ antaradhāpeti;**It’s not the elements of earth, water, fire, or air that make the true teaching disappear.*";
P_HTM[4930]="*atha kho idheva te uppajjanti moghapurisā ye imaṃ saddhammaṃ antaradhāpenti.**Rather, it’s the foolish people who appear right here that make the true teaching disappear.*";
P_HTM[4931]="*Seyyathāpi, kassapa, nāvā ādikeneva opilavati;**The true teaching doesn’t disappear like a ship that sinks all at once.*";
P_HTM[4932]="*na kho, kassapa, evaṃ saddhammassa antaradhānaṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[4933]="*Pañca khome, kassapa, okkamaniyā dhammā saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattanti.**There are five detrimental things that lead to the decline and disappearance of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[4934]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4935]="*Idha, kassapa, bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo upāsakā upāsikāyo satthari agāravā viharanti appatissā, dhamme agāravā viharanti appatissā, saṅghe agāravā viharanti appatissā, sikkhāya agāravā viharanti appatissā, samādhismiṃ agāravā viharanti appatissā—**It’s when the monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen lack respect and reverence for the Teacher, the teaching, the Saṅgha, the training, and immersion.*";
P_HTM[4936]="*ime kho, kassapa, pañca okkamaniyā dhammā saddhammassa sammosāya antaradhānāya saṃvattanti.**These five detrimental things lead to the decline and disappearance of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[4937]="*Pañca khome, kassapa, dhammā saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattanti.**There are five things that lead to the continuation, persistence, and enduring of the true teaching.*";
P_HTM[4938]="*Katame pañca?**What five?*";
P_HTM[4939]="*Idha, kassapa, bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo upāsakā upāsikāyo satthari sagāravā viharanti sappatissā, dhamme sagāravā viharanti sappatissā, saṅghe sagāravā viharanti sappatissā, sikkhāya sagāravā viharanti sappatissā, samādhismiṃ sagāravā viharanti sappatissā—**It’s when the monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen maintain respect and reverence for the Teacher, the teaching, the Saṅgha, the training, and immersion.*";
P_HTM[4940]="*ime kho, kassapa, pañca dhammā saddhammassa ṭhitiyā asammosāya anantaradhānāya saṃvattantī”ti.**These five things lead to the continuation, persistence, and enduring of the true teaching.”*";
P_HTM[4941]="*Terasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4942]="*Kassapavaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[4943]="*Santuṭṭhañca anottappī,* **";
P_HTM[4944]="*candūpamaṃ kulūpakaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4945]="*Jiṇṇaṃ tayo ca ovādā,* **";
P_HTM[4946]="*jhānābhiññā upassayaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[4947]="*Cīvaraṃ paraṃmaraṇaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[4948]="*saddhammappatirūpakanti.* **";
P_HTM[4949]="*Kassapasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ.**The Linked Discourses with Kassapa are complete.*";
P_HTM[4950]="*17. Lābhasakkārasaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[4951]="*1. Buddhavaggo**The First Chapter*";
P_HTM[4952]="*1. Dāruṇasuttaṃ**Brutal*";
P_HTM[4953]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[4954]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[4955]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[4956]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[4957]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[4958]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[4959]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko kaṭuko pharuso antarāyiko anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya.**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal, bitter, and harsh. They’re an obstacle to reaching the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[4960]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[4961]="*‘uppannaṃ lābhasakkārasilokaṃ pajahissāma, na ca no uppanno lābhasakkārasiloko cittaṃ pariyādāya ṭhassatī’ti.**‘We will give up arisen possessions, honor, and popularity, and we won’t let them occupy our minds.’*";
P_HTM[4962]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[4963]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4964]="*2. Baḷisasuttaṃ**A Hook*";
P_HTM[4965]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4966]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko kaṭuko pharuso antarāyiko anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya.**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal, bitter, and harsh. They’re an obstacle to reaching the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[4967]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, bāḷisiko āmisagataṃ baḷisaṃ gambhīre udakarahade pakkhipeyya.**Suppose a fisherman was to cast a baited hook into a deep lake.*";
P_HTM[4968]="*Tamenaṃ aññataro āmisacakkhu maccho gileyya.**Seeing the bait, a fish would swallow it.*";
P_HTM[4969]="*Evañhi so, bhikkhave, maccho gilabaḷiso bāḷisikassa anayaṃ āpanno byasanaṃ āpanno yathākāmakaraṇīyo bāḷisikassa.**And so the fish that swallowed the hook would meet with tragedy and disaster, and the fisherman can do what he wants with it.*";
P_HTM[4970]="*Bāḷisikoti kho, bhikkhave, mārassetaṃ pāpimato adhivacanaṃ.**‘Fisherman’ is a term for Māra the Wicked.*";
P_HTM[4971]="*Baḷisanti kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasilokassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘Hook’ is a term for possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[4972]="*Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, bhikkhu uppannaṃ lābhasakkārasilokaṃ assādeti nikāmeti, ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu gilabaḷiso mārassa anayaṃ āpanno byasanaṃ āpanno yathākāmakaraṇīyo pāpimato.**Whoever enjoys and likes arisen possessions, honor, and popularity is called a mendicant who has swallowed Māra’s hook. They’ve met with tragedy and disaster, and the Wicked One can do what he wants with them.*";
P_HTM[4973]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko kaṭuko pharuso antarāyiko anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya.**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity—bitter and harsh, an obstacle to reaching the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[4974]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[4975]="*‘uppannaṃ lābhasakkārasilokaṃ pajahissāma, na ca no uppanno lābhasakkārasiloko cittaṃ pariyādāya ṭhassatī’ti.**‘We will give up arisen possessions, honor, and popularity, and we won’t let them occupy our minds.’*";
P_HTM[4976]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[4977]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[4978]="*3. Kummasuttaṃ**A Turtle*";
P_HTM[4979]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4980]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe … adhigamāya.**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal …*";
P_HTM[4981]="*Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, aññatarasmiṃ udakarahade mahākummakulaṃ ciranivāsi ahosi.**Once upon a time in a certain lake there was a large family of turtles that had lived there for a long time.*";
P_HTM[4982]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, aññataro kummo aññataraṃ kummaṃ etadavoca:**Then one of the turtles said to another,*";
P_HTM[4983]="*‘mā kho tvaṃ, tāta kumma, etaṃ padesaṃ agamāsī’ti.**‘My dear turtle, don’t you go to that place.’*";
P_HTM[4984]="*Agamāsi kho, bhikkhave, so kummo taṃ padesaṃ.**But that turtle did go to that place,*";
P_HTM[4985]="*Tamenaṃ luddo papatāya vijjhi.**and a hunter pierced her with a harpoon.*";
P_HTM[4986]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, so kummo yena so kummo tenupasaṅkami.**Then that turtle went back to the other turtle.*";
P_HTM[4987]="*Addasā kho, bhikkhave, so kummo taṃ kummaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**When the other turtle saw her coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[4988]="*Disvāna taṃ kummaṃ etadavoca:**he said,*";
P_HTM[4989]="*‘kacci tvaṃ, tāta kumma, na taṃ padesaṃ agamāsī’ti?**‘My dear turtle, I hope you didn’t go to that place!’*";
P_HTM[4990]="*‘Agamāsiṃ khvāhaṃ, tāta kumma, taṃ padesan’ti.**‘I did.’*";
P_HTM[4991]="*‘Kacci panāsi, tāta kumma, akkhato anupahato’ti?**‘But my dear turtle, I hope you’re not hurt or injured!’*";
P_HTM[4992]="*‘Akkhato khomhi, tāta kumma, anupahato, atthi ca me idaṃ suttakaṃ piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhan’ti.**‘I’m not hurt or injured. But this cord keeps dragging behind me.’*";
P_HTM[4993]="*‘Tagghasi, tāta kumma, khato, taggha upahato.**‘Indeed, my dear turtle, you’re hurt and injured!*";
P_HTM[4994]="*Etena hi te, tāta kumma, suttakena pitaro ca pitāmahā ca anayaṃ āpannā byasanaṃ āpannā.**Your father and grandfather met with tragedy and disaster because of such a cord.*";
P_HTM[4995]="*Gaccha dāni tvaṃ, tāta kumma, na dāni tvaṃ amhākan’ti.**Go now, you are no longer one of us.’*";
P_HTM[4996]="*Luddoti kho, bhikkhave, mārassetaṃ pāpimato adhivacanaṃ.**‘Hunter’ is a term for Māra the Wicked.*";
P_HTM[4997]="*Papatāti kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasilokassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘Harpoon’ is a term for possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[4998]="*Suttakanti kho, bhikkhave, nandīrāgassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘Cord’ is a term for desire with relishing.*";
P_HTM[4999]="*Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, bhikkhu uppannaṃ lābhasakkārasilokaṃ assādeti nikāmeti—**Whoever enjoys and likes arisen possessions, honor, and popularity is called a mendicant who has been pierced with a harpoon. They’ve met with tragedy and disaster, and the Wicked One can treat them however he wants.*";
P_HTM[5000]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu giddho papatāya anayaṃ āpanno byasanaṃ āpanno yathākāmakaraṇīyo pāpimato.* **";
P_HTM[5001]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5002]="*evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5003]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5004]="*4. Dīghalomikasuttaṃ**A Fleecy Sheep*";
P_HTM[5005]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5006]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe … adhigamāya.**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal …*";
P_HTM[5007]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, dīghalomikā eḷakā kaṇṭakagahanaṃ paviseyya.**Suppose a fleecy sheep was to enter a briar patch.*";
P_HTM[5008]="*Sā tatra tatra sajjeyya, tatra tatra gayheyya, tatra tatra bajjheyya, tatra tatra anayabyasanaṃ āpajjeyya.**She’d get caught, snagged, and trapped at every turn, coming to ruin.*";
P_HTM[5009]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhikkhu lābhasakkārasilokena abhibhūto pariyādiṇṇacitto pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisati.**In the same way, take a certain mendicant whose mind is overcome and overwhelmed by possessions, honor, and popularity. They robe up in the morning and, taking their bowl and robe, enter the village or town for alms.*";
P_HTM[5010]="*So tatra tatra sajjati, tatra tatra gayhati, tatra tatra bajjhati, tatra tatra anayabyasanaṃ āpajjati.**They get caught, snagged, and trapped at every turn, coming to ruin.*";
P_HTM[5011]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5012]="*evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5013]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5014]="*5. Mīḷhakasuttaṃ**A Dung Beetle*";
P_HTM[5015]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5016]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe … adhigamāya.**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal …*";
P_HTM[5017]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, mīḷhakā gūthādī gūthapūrā puṇṇā gūthassa. Purato cassa mahāgūthapuñjo.**Suppose there was a dung-eating beetle full of dung, stuffed with dung, and before her was a huge pile of dung.*";
P_HTM[5018]="*Sā tena aññā mīḷhakā atimaññeyya:**She’d look down on other beetles, thinking:*";
P_HTM[5019]="*‘ahamhi gūthādī gūthapūrā puṇṇā gūthassa, purato ca myāyaṃ mahāgūthapuñjo’ti.**‘For I am a dung-eating beetle full of dung, stuffed with dung, and before me is a huge pile of dung.’*";
P_HTM[5020]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhikkhu lābhasakkārasilokena abhibhūto pariyādiṇṇacitto pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisati.**In the same way, take a certain mendicant whose mind is overcome and overwhelmed by possessions, honor, and popularity. They robe up in the morning and, taking their bowl and robe, enter the village or town for alms.*";
P_HTM[5021]="*So tattha bhuttāvī ca hoti yāvadattho, nimantito ca svātanāya, piṇḍapāto cassa pūro.**There they eat as much as they like, get invited back tomorrow, and have plenty of alms-food.*";
P_HTM[5022]="*So ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhugaṇassa majjhe vikatthati:**When they get back to the monastery, they boast in the middle of a group of mendicants:*";
P_HTM[5023]="*‘bhuttāvī camhi yāvadattho, nimantito camhi svātanāya, piṇḍapāto ca myāyaṃ pūro, lābhī camhi cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ, ime panaññe bhikkhū appapuññā appesakkhā na lābhino cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānan’ti.**‘I ate as much as I liked, got invited back tomorrow, and had plenty of alms-food. I get robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick. But these other mendicants have little merit or significance, so they don’t get these things.’*";
P_HTM[5024]="*So tena lābhasakkārasilokena abhibhūto pariyādiṇṇacitto aññe pesale bhikkhū atimaññati.**With a mind overcome and overwhelmed by possessions, honor, and popularity, they look down on other good-hearted mendicants.*";
P_HTM[5025]="*Tañhi tassa, bhikkhave, moghapurisassa hoti dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya.**This will be for their lasting harm and suffering.*";
P_HTM[5026]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5027]="*evañhi vo bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5028]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5029]="*6. Asanisuttaṃ**A Bolt of Lightning*";
P_HTM[5030]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5031]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe … adhigamāya.**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal …*";
P_HTM[5032]="*Kaṃ, bhikkhave, asanivicakkaṃ āgacchatu, sekhaṃ appattamānasaṃ lābhasakkārasiloko anupāpuṇātu.**Who should be struck by lightning? A trainee who comes into possessions, honor, and popularity before they achieve their heart’s desire.*";
P_HTM[5033]="*Asanivicakkanti kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasilokassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘Lightning strike’ is a term for possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[5034]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5035]="*evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5036]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5037]="*7. Diddhasuttaṃ**A Poisoned Arrow*";
P_HTM[5038]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5039]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe … adhigamāya.**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal …*";
P_HTM[5040]="*Kaṃ, bhikkhave, diddhagatena visallena sallena vijjhatu, sekhaṃ appattamānasaṃ lābhasakkārasiloko anupāpuṇātu.**Who should be pierced by a poisoned arrow? A trainee who comes into possessions, honor, and popularity before they achieve their heart’s desire.*";
P_HTM[5041]="*Sallanti kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasilokassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ.**‘Arrow’ is a term for possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[5042]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5043]="*evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5044]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5045]="*8. Siṅgālasuttaṃ**A Jackal*";
P_HTM[5046]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5047]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe … adhigamāya.**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal …*";
P_HTM[5048]="*Assuttha no tumhe, bhikkhave, rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ jarasiṅgālassa vassamānassā”ti?**Mendicants, did you hear an old jackal howling at the crack of dawn?”*";
P_HTM[5049]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5050]="*“Eso kho, bhikkhave, jarasiṅgālo ukkaṇḍakena nāma rogajātena phuṭṭho neva bilagato ramati, na rukkhamūlagato ramati, na ajjhokāsagato ramati;**“That old jackal has the disease called mange. He’s not happy in his den, or at the root of a tree, or out in the open.*";
P_HTM[5051]="*yena yena gacchati, yattha yattha tiṭṭhati, yattha yattha nisīdati, yattha yattha nipajjati; tattha tattha anayabyasanaṃ āpajjati.**Wherever he goes, stands, sits, or lies down he meets with tragedy and disaster.*";
P_HTM[5052]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhikkhu lābhasakkārasilokena abhibhūto pariyādiṇṇacitto neva suññāgāragato ramati, na rukkhamūlagato ramati, na ajjhokāsagato ramati;**In the same way, take a certain mendicant whose mind is overcome and overwhelmed by possessions, honor, and popularity. They’re not happy in an empty hut, at the root of a tree, or out in the open.*";
P_HTM[5053]="*yena yena gacchati, yattha yattha tiṭṭhati, yattha yattha nisīdati, yattha yattha nipajjati; tattha tattha anayabyasanaṃ āpajjati.**Wherever they go, stand, sit, or lie down they meet with tragedy and disaster.*";
P_HTM[5054]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5055]="*evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5056]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5057]="*9. Verambhasuttaṃ**Gale*";
P_HTM[5058]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5059]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe … adhigamāya.**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal …*";
P_HTM[5060]="*Upari, bhikkhave, ākāse verambhā nāma vātā vāyanti.**High in the sky there are gale-force winds blowing.*";
P_HTM[5061]="*Tattha yo pakkhī gacchati tamenaṃ verambhā vātā khipanti.**Any bird that flies there is flung about by those gale-force winds.*";
P_HTM[5062]="*Tassa verambhavātakkhittassa aññeneva pādā gacchanti, aññena pakkhā gacchanti, aññena sīsaṃ gacchati, aññena kāyo gacchati.**Their feet go one way, their wings another, their head another, and their body another.*";
P_HTM[5063]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhikkhu lābhasakkārasilokena abhibhūto pariyādiṇṇacitto pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisati arakkhiteneva kāyena arakkhitāya vācāya arakkhitena cittena, anupaṭṭhitāya satiyā, asaṃvutehi indriyehi.**In the same way, take a certain monk whose mind is overcome and overwhelmed by possessions, honor, and popularity. He robes up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, enters the village or town for alms without guarding body, speech, and mind, without establishing mindfulness, and without restraining the sense faculties.*";
P_HTM[5064]="*So tattha passati mātugāmaṃ dunnivatthaṃ vā duppārutaṃ vā.**There he sees a female scantily clad, with revealing clothes.*";
P_HTM[5065]="*Tassa mātugāmaṃ disvā dunnivatthaṃ vā duppārutaṃ vā rāgo cittaṃ anuddhaṃseti.**Lust infects his mind.*";
P_HTM[5066]="*So rāgānuddhaṃsitena cittena sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattati.**He rejects the training and returns to a lesser life.*";
P_HTM[5067]="*Tassa aññe cīvaraṃ haranti, aññe pattaṃ haranti, aññe nisīdanaṃ haranti, aññe sūcigharaṃ haranti, verambhavātakkhittasseva sakuṇassa.**Some take his robe, others his bowl, others his sitting cloth, others his needle case, just like the bird flung about by the gale-force winds.*";
P_HTM[5068]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5069]="*evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5070]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5071]="*10. Sagāthakasuttaṃ**With Verses*";
P_HTM[5072]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5073]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe … adhigamāya.**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal …*";
P_HTM[5074]="*Idhāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ passāmi sakkārena abhibhūtaṃ pariyādiṇṇacittaṃ, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannaṃ.**Take a case where I see a certain person whose mind is overcome and overwhelmed by honor. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[5075]="*Idha panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ passāmi asakkārena abhibhūtaṃ pariyādiṇṇacittaṃ, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannaṃ.**Take another case where I see a certain person whose mind is overcome and overwhelmed by lack of honor. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[5076]="*Idha panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ passāmi sakkārena ca asakkārena ca tadubhayena abhibhūtaṃ pariyādiṇṇacittaṃ, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannaṃ.**And take another case where I see a certain person whose mind is overcome and overwhelmed by both honor and lack of honor. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.*";
P_HTM[5077]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5078]="*evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5079]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[5080]="*Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:**Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:*";
P_HTM[5081]="*“Yassa sakkariyamānassa,**“Whether they’re honored*";
P_HTM[5082]="*asakkārena cūbhayaṃ;**or not honored, or both,*";
P_HTM[5083]="*Samādhi na vikampati,**their immersion doesn’t waver*";
P_HTM[5084]="*appamāṇavihārino.**as they live diligently.*";
P_HTM[5085]="*Taṃ jhāyinaṃ sātatikaṃ,**They persistently practice absorption*";
P_HTM[5086]="*sukhumaṃ diṭṭhivipassakaṃ;**with subtle view and discernment.*";
P_HTM[5087]="*Upādānakkhayārāmaṃ,**Rejoicing in the ending of grasping,*";
P_HTM[5088]="*āhu sappuriso itī”ti.**they’re said to be a good person.”*";
P_HTM[5089]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5090]="*Paṭhamo vaggo.* **";
P_HTM[5091]="*Dāruṇo baḷisaṃ kummaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[5092]="*dīghalomi ca mīḷhakaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[5093]="*Asani diddhaṃ siṅgālaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[5094]="*verambhena sagāthakanti.* **";
P_HTM[5095]="*2. Āhāravaggo**The Second Chapter*";
P_HTM[5096]="*1. Suvaṇṇapātisuttaṃ**A Golden Bowl*";
P_HTM[5097]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5098]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe … adhigamāya.**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal …*";
P_HTM[5099]="*Idhāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:**When I’ve comprehended the mind of a certain person, I understand:*";
P_HTM[5100]="*‘na cāyamāyasmā suvaṇṇapātiyāpi rūpiyacuṇṇaparipūrāya hetu sampajānamusā bhāseyyā’ti.**‘This venerable would not tell a deliberate lie even for the sake of a golden bowl filled with silver powder.’*";
P_HTM[5101]="*Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena lābhasakkārasilokena abhibhūtaṃ pariyādiṇṇacittaṃ sampajānamusā bhāsantaṃ.**But some time later I see them tell a deliberate lie because their mind is overcome and overwhelmed by possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[5102]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5103]="*evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5104]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5105]="*2. Rūpiyapātisuttaṃ**A Silver Bowl*";
P_HTM[5106]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5107]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal …*";
P_HTM[5108]="*idhāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:**When I’ve comprehended the mind of a certain person, I understand:*";
P_HTM[5109]="*‘na cāyamāyasmā rūpiyapātiyāpi suvaṇṇacuṇṇaparipūrāya hetu sampajānamusā bhāseyyā’ti.**‘This venerable would not tell a deliberate lie even for the sake of a silver bowl filled with gold powder.’*";
P_HTM[5110]="*Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena lābhasakkārasilokena abhibhūtaṃ pariyādiṇṇacittaṃ sampajānamusā bhāsantaṃ.**But some time later I see them tell a deliberate lie because their mind is overcome and overwhelmed by possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[5111]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5112]="*evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5113]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5114]="*3-10. Suvaṇṇanikkhasuttādiaṭṭhakaṃ**13–20. Suvaṇṇanikkhasuttādiaṭṭhaka*";
P_HTM[5115]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5116]="*“Idhāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:**“Mendicants, when I’ve comprehended the mind of a certain person, I understand:*";
P_HTM[5117]="*‘na cāyamāyasmā suvaṇṇanikkhassāpi hetu … pe …**‘This venerable would not tell a deliberate lie even for the sake of a gold coin.’ …*";
P_HTM[5118]="*suvaṇṇanikkhasatassāpi hetu …**‘… for the sake of a hundred gold coins.’ …*";
P_HTM[5119]="*siṅgīnikkhassāpi hetu …**‘… for the sake of a gold doubloon.’ …*";
P_HTM[5120]="*siṅgīnikkhasatassāpi hetu …**‘… for the sake of a hundred gold doubloons.’ …*";
P_HTM[5121]="*pathaviyāpi jātarūpaparipūrāya hetu …**‘… for the sake of the whole earth full of gold.’ …*";
P_HTM[5122]="*āmisakiñcikkhahetupi …**‘… for any kind of material reward.’ …*";
P_HTM[5123]="*jīvitahetupi …**‘… for the sake of life.’ …*";
P_HTM[5124]="*janapadakalyāṇiyāpi hetu sampajānamusā bhāseyyā’ti.**‘… for the sake of the finest lady in the land.’*";
P_HTM[5125]="*Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena lābhasakkārasilokena abhibhūtaṃ pariyādiṇṇacittaṃ sampajānamusā bhāsantaṃ.**But some time later I see them tell a deliberate lie because their mind is overcome and overwhelmed by possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[5126]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5127]="*evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5128]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5129]="*Dutiyo vaggo.* **";
P_HTM[5130]="*Dve pāti dve suvaṇṇā ca,* **";
P_HTM[5131]="*Siṅgīhi apare duve;* **";
P_HTM[5132]="*Pathavī kiñcikkhajīvitaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[5133]="*Janapadakalyāṇiyā dasāti.* **";
P_HTM[5134]="*3. Dasabalavaggo**The Third Chapter*";
P_HTM[5135]="*1. Mātugāmasuttaṃ**A Female*";
P_HTM[5136]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5137]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal …*";
P_HTM[5138]="*na tassa, bhikkhave, mātugāmo eko ekassa cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhati yassa lābhasakkārasiloko cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhati.**Even if you’re alone with a female she might not occupy your mind, but possessions, honor and popularity would still occupy your mind.*";
P_HTM[5139]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5140]="*evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5141]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5142]="*2. Kalyāṇīsuttaṃ**The Finest Lady in the Land*";
P_HTM[5143]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5144]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal …*";
P_HTM[5145]="*na tassa, bhikkhave, janapadakalyāṇī ekā ekassa cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhati yassa lābhasakkārasiloko cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhati.**Even if you’re alone with the finest lady in the land she might not occupy your mind, but possessions, honor and popularity would still occupy your mind.*";
P_HTM[5146]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5147]="*evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5148]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5149]="*3. Ekaputtakasuttaṃ**An Only Son*";
P_HTM[5150]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5151]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal …*";
P_HTM[5152]="*saddhā, bhikkhave, upāsikā ekaputtakaṃ piyaṃ manāpaṃ evaṃ sammā āyācamānā āyāceyya:**A faithful laywoman with a dear and beloved only son would rightly appeal to him,*";
P_HTM[5153]="*‘tādiso, tāta, bhavāhi yādiso citto ca gahapati hatthako ca āḷavako’ti.**‘My darling, please be like the householder Citta and Hatthaka of Aḷavī.’*";
P_HTM[5154]="*Esā, bhikkhave, tulā etaṃ pamāṇaṃ mama sāvakānaṃ upāsakānaṃ, yadidaṃ citto ca gahapati hatthako ca āḷavako.**These are a standard and a measure for my male lay disciples, that is, the householder Citta and Hatthaka of Aḷavī.*";
P_HTM[5155]="*Sace kho tvaṃ, tāta, agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajasi;**‘But my darling, if you go forth from the lay life to homelessness,*";
P_HTM[5156]="*tādiso, tāta, bhavāhi yādisā sāriputtamoggallānāti.**please be like Sāriputta and Moggallāna.’*";
P_HTM[5157]="*Esā, bhikkhave, tulā etaṃ pamāṇaṃ mama sāvakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, yadidaṃ sāriputtamoggalānā.**These are a standard and a measure for my monk disciples, that is, Sāriputta and Moggallāna.*";
P_HTM[5158]="*Mā ca kho tvaṃ, tāta, sekhaṃ appattamānasaṃ lābhasakkārasiloko anupāpuṇātūti.**‘And my darling, may you not come into possessions, honor, and popularity while you’re still a trainee and haven’t achieved your heart’s desire.’*";
P_HTM[5159]="*Tañce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ sekhaṃ appattamānasaṃ lābhasakkārasiloko anupāpuṇāti, so tassa hoti antarāyāya.**If a trainee who hasn’t achieved their heart’s desire comes into possessions, honor, and popularity it’s an obstacle for them.*";
P_HTM[5160]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5161]="*evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5162]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5163]="*4. Ekadhītusuttaṃ**An Only Daughter*";
P_HTM[5164]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5165]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal …*";
P_HTM[5166]="*saddhā bhikkhave upāsikā ekaṃ dhītaraṃ piyaṃ manāpaṃ evaṃ sammā āyācamānā āyāceyya:**A faithful laywoman with a dear and beloved only daughter would rightly appeal to her,*";
P_HTM[5167]="*‘tādisā, ayye, bhavāhi yādisā khujjuttarā ca upāsikā veḷukaṇḍakiyā ca nandamātā’ti.**‘My darling, please be like the laywomen Khujjuttarā and Veḷukaṇṭakī, Nanda’s mother.’*";
P_HTM[5168]="*Esā, bhikkhave, tulā etaṃ pamāṇaṃ mama sāvikānaṃ upāsikānaṃ, yadidaṃ khujjuttarā ca upāsikā veḷukaṇḍakiyā ca nandamātā.**These are a standard and a measure for my female lay disciples, that is, the laywomen Khujjuttarā and Veḷukaṇṭakī, Nanda’s mother.*";
P_HTM[5169]="*Sace kho tvaṃ, ayye, agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajasi;**‘But my darling, if you go forth from the lay life to homelessness, please be like the nuns Khemā and Uppalavaṇṇā.’*";
P_HTM[5170]="*tādisā, ayye, bhavāhi yādisā khemā ca bhikkhunī uppalavaṇṇā cāti.* **";
P_HTM[5171]="*Esā, bhikkhave, tulā etaṃ pamāṇaṃ mama sāvikānaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ, yadidaṃ khemā ca bhikkhunī uppalavaṇṇā ca.**These are a standard and a measure for my nun disciples, that is, the nuns Khemā and Uppalavaṇṇā.*";
P_HTM[5172]="*Mā ca kho tvaṃ, ayye, sekhaṃ appattamānasaṃ lābhasakkārasiloko anupāpuṇātūti.**‘And my darling, may you not come into possessions, honor, and popularity while you’re still a trainee and haven’t achieved your heart’s desire.’*";
P_HTM[5173]="*Tañce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniṃ sekhaṃ appattamānasaṃ lābhasakkārasiloko anupāpuṇāti, so tassā hoti antarāyāya.**If a trainee who hasn’t achieved their heart’s desire comes into possessions, honor, and popularity it’s an obstacle for them.*";
P_HTM[5174]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5175]="*evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5176]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5177]="*5. Samaṇabrāhmaṇasuttaṃ**Ascetics and Brahmins*";
P_HTM[5178]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5179]="*“Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā lābhasakkārasilokassa assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ nappajānanti,**“Mendicants, there are ascetics and brahmins who don’t truly understand the gratification, drawback, and escape when it comes to possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[5180]="*na me te, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā samaṇesu vā samaṇasammatā brāhmaṇesu vā brāhmaṇasammatā, na ca pana te āyasmantā sāmaññatthaṃ vā brahmaññatthaṃ vā diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharanti.**I don’t regard them as true ascetics and brahmins. Those venerables don’t realize the goal of life as an ascetic or brahmin, and don’t live having realized it with their own insight.*";
P_HTM[5181]="*Ye ca kho keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā lābhasakkārasilokassa assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ pajānanti,**There are ascetics and brahmins who do truly understand the gratification, drawback, and escape when it comes to possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[5182]="*te ca kho me, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā samaṇesu ceva samaṇasammatā brāhmaṇesu ca brāhmaṇasammatā, te ca panāyasmanto sāmaññatthañca brahmaññatthañca diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharantī”ti.**I regard them as true ascetics and brahmins. Those venerables realize the goal of life as an ascetic or brahmin, and live having realized it with their own insight.”*";
P_HTM[5183]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5184]="*6. Dutiyasamaṇabrāhmaṇasuttaṃ**Ascetics and Brahmins (2nd)*";
P_HTM[5185]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5186]="*“Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā lābhasakkārasilokassa samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ nappajānanti … pe …**“There are ascetics and brahmins who don’t truly understand the origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape when it comes to possessions, honor, and popularity …*";
P_HTM[5187]="*pajānanti … pe …**There are ascetics and brahmins who do truly understand …”*";
P_HTM[5188]="*sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharantī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5189]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5190]="*7. Tatiyasamaṇabrāhmaṇasuttaṃ**Ascetics and Brahmins (3rd)*";
P_HTM[5191]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5192]="*“Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā lābhasakkārasilokaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānanti, lābhasakkārasilokasamudayaṃ nappajānanti, lābhasakkārasilokanirodhaṃ nappajānanti, lābhasakkārasilokanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ nappajānanti … pe …**“There are ascetics and brahmins who don’t truly understand possessions, honor, and popularity, their origin, their cessation, and the path that leads to their cessation …*";
P_HTM[5193]="*pajānanti … pe …**There are ascetics and brahmins who do truly understand …”*";
P_HTM[5194]="*sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharantī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5195]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5196]="*8. Chavisuttaṃ**Skin*";
P_HTM[5197]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5198]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko.**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal …*";
P_HTM[5199]="*Lābhasakkārasiloko, bhikkhave, chaviṃ chindati, chaviṃ chetvā cammaṃ chindati, cammaṃ chetvā maṃsaṃ chindati, maṃsaṃ chetvā nhāruṃ chindati, nhāruṃ chetvā aṭṭhiṃ chindati, aṭṭhiṃ chetvā aṭṭhimiñjaṃ āhacca tiṭṭhati.**They cut through the outer skin, the inner skin, the flesh, sinews, and bones, until they reach the marrow and stay pressing there.*";
P_HTM[5200]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5201]="*evañhi vo bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5202]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5203]="*9. Rajjusuttaṃ**A Rope*";
P_HTM[5204]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5205]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko.**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal …*";
P_HTM[5206]="*Lābhasakkārasiloko, bhikkhave, chaviṃ chindati, chaviṃ chetvā cammaṃ chindati, cammaṃ chetvā maṃsaṃ chindati, maṃsaṃ chetvā nhāruṃ chindati, nhāruṃ chetvā aṭṭhiṃ chindati, aṭṭhiṃ chetvā aṭṭhimiñjaṃ āhacca tiṭṭhati.**They cut through the outer skin, the inner skin, the flesh, sinews, and bones, until they reach the marrow and stay pressing there.*";
P_HTM[5207]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, balavā puriso daḷhāya vāḷarajjuyā jaṅghaṃ veṭhetvā ghaṃseyya.**Suppose a strong man was to twist a tough horse-hair rope around your shin and tighten it.*";
P_HTM[5208]="*Sā chaviṃ chindeyya, chaviṃ chetvā cammaṃ chindeyya, cammaṃ chetvā maṃsaṃ chindeyya, maṃsaṃ chetvā nhāruṃ chindeyya, nhāruṃ chetvā aṭṭhiṃ chindeyya, aṭṭhiṃ chetvā aṭṭhimiñjaṃ āhacca tiṭṭheyya.**It would cut through the outer skin, the inner skin, the flesh, sinews, and bones, until it reached the marrow and stayed pressing there.*";
P_HTM[5209]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko chaviṃ chindati, chaviṃ chetvā cammaṃ chindati, cammaṃ chetvā maṃsaṃ chindati, maṃsaṃ chetvā nhāruṃ chindati, nhāruṃ chetvā aṭṭhiṃ chindati, aṭṭhiṃ chetvā aṭṭhimiñjaṃ āhacca tiṭṭhati.**In the same way, possessions, honor, and popularity cut through the outer skin, the inner skin, the flesh, sinews, and bones, until they reach the marrow and stay pressing there.*";
P_HTM[5210]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5211]="*evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5212]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5213]="*10. Bhikkhusuttaṃ**A Mendicant With Defilements Ended*";
P_HTM[5214]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5215]="*“Yopi so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo tassapāhaṃ lābhasakkārasiloko antarāyāya vadāmī”ti.**“Mendicants, possessions, honor, and popularity are an obstacle even for a mendicant who is perfected, with defilements ended.”*";
P_HTM[5216]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Venerable Ānanda said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[5217]="*“kissa pana, bhante, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno lābhasakkārasiloko antarāyāyā”ti?**“Sir, what do possessions, honor, and popularity obstruct for a mendicant with defilements ended?”*";
P_HTM[5218]="*“Yā hissa sā, ānanda, akuppā cetovimutti nāhaṃ tassā lābhasakkārasilokaṃ antarāyāya vadāmi.**“Ānanda, I don’t say that possessions, honor, and popularity obstruct the unshakable freedom of heart.*";
P_HTM[5219]="*Ye ca khvassa, ānanda, appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārā adhigatā tesāhamassa lābhasakkārasilokaṃ antarāyāya vadāmi.**But I do say that possessions, honor, and popularity obstruct the achievement of blissful meditations in this very life for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute.*";
P_HTM[5220]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, ānanda, lābhasakkārasiloko kaṭuko pharuso antarāyiko anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya.**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity—bitter and harsh, an obstacle to reaching the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[5221]="*Tasmātihānanda, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[5222]="*‘uppannaṃ lābhasakkārasilokaṃ pajahissāma, na ca no uppanno lābhasakkārasiloko cittaṃ pariyādāya ṭhassatī’ti.**‘We will give up arisen possessions, honor, and popularity, and we won’t let them occupy our minds.’*";
P_HTM[5223]="*Evañhi vo, ānanda, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[5224]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5225]="*Tatiyo vaggo.* **";
P_HTM[5226]="*Mātugāmo ca kalyāṇī,* **";
P_HTM[5227]="*putto ca ekadhītu ca;* **";
P_HTM[5228]="*Samaṇabrāhmaṇā tīṇi,* **";
P_HTM[5229]="*chavi rajju ca bhikkhunāti.* **";
P_HTM[5230]="*4. Kaḷārakhattiyavaggo**The Fourth Chapter*";
P_HTM[5231]="*1. Bhindisuttaṃ**Schism*";
P_HTM[5232]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5233]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko.**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal …*";
P_HTM[5234]="*Lābhasakkārasilokena abhibhūto pariyādiṇṇacitto, bhikkhave, devadatto saṃghaṃ bhindi.**Devadatta caused a schism in the Saṅgha because his mind was overcome and overwhelmed by possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[5235]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5236]="*sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5237]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5238]="*2. Kusalamūlasuttaṃ**Skillful Root*";
P_HTM[5239]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5240]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko.**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal …*";
P_HTM[5241]="*Lābhasakkārasilokena abhibhūtassa pariyādiṇṇacittassa, bhikkhave, devadattassa kusalamūlaṃ samucchedamagamā.**Devadatta cut off his skillful root because his mind was overcome and overwhelmed by possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[5242]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5243]="*sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5244]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5245]="*3. Kusaladhammasuttaṃ**Skillful Quality*";
P_HTM[5246]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5247]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko.**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal …*";
P_HTM[5248]="*Lābhasakkārasilokena abhibhūtassa pariyādiṇṇacittassa, bhikkhave, devadattassa kusalo dhammo samucchedamagamā.**Devadatta cut off his skillful quality because his mind was overcome and overwhelmed by possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[5249]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5250]="*sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5251]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5252]="*4. Sukkadhammasuttaṃ**Bright Quality*";
P_HTM[5253]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5254]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko.**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal …*";
P_HTM[5255]="*Lābhasakkārasilokena abhibhūtassa pariyādiṇṇacittassa, bhikkhave, devadattassa sukko dhammo samucchedamagamā.**Devadatta cut off his bright quality because his mind was overcome and overwhelmed by possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[5256]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5257]="*sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5258]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5259]="*5. Acirapakkantasuttaṃ**Shortly After He Left*";
P_HTM[5260]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate acirapakkante devadatte.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain, not long after Devadatta had left.*";
P_HTM[5261]="*Tatra kho bhagavā devadattaṃ ārabbha bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha spoke to the mendicants about Devadatta:*";
P_HTM[5262]="*“attavadhāya, bhikkhave, devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi.**“Possessions, honor, and popularity came to Devadatta for his own ruin and downfall.*";
P_HTM[5263]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, kadalī attavadhāya phalaṃ deti, parābhavāya phalaṃ deti;**It’s like a banana tree …*";
P_HTM[5264]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi.* **";
P_HTM[5265]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, veḷu attavadhāya phalaṃ deti, parābhavāya phalaṃ deti;**or a bamboo …*";
P_HTM[5266]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi.* **";
P_HTM[5267]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, naḷo attavadhāya phalaṃ deti, parābhavāya phalaṃ deti;**or a reed, all of which bear fruit to their own ruin and downfall …*";
P_HTM[5268]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi.* **";
P_HTM[5269]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, assatarī attavadhāya gabbhaṃ gaṇhāti, parābhavāya gabbhaṃ gaṇhāti;**It’s like a mule, which becomes pregnant to its own ruin and downfall.*";
P_HTM[5270]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi.**In the same way, possessions, honor, and popularity came to Devadatta for his own ruin and downfall.*";
P_HTM[5271]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko.**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5272]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[5273]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[5274]="*Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:**Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:*";
P_HTM[5275]="*“Phalaṃ ve kadaliṃ hanti,**“The banana tree is destroyed by its own fruit,*";
P_HTM[5276]="*phalaṃ veḷuṃ phalaṃ naḷaṃ;**as are the bamboo and the reed.*";
P_HTM[5277]="*Sakkāro kāpurisaṃ hanti,**Honor destroys a sinner,*";
P_HTM[5278]="*gabbho assatariṃ yathā”ti.**as pregnancy destroys a mule.”*";
P_HTM[5279]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5280]="*6. Pañcarathasatasuttaṃ**Five Hundred Carts*";
P_HTM[5281]="*Rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**Near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[5282]="*Tena kho pana samayena devadattassa ajātasattukumāro pañcahi rathasatehi sāyaṃ pātaṃ upaṭṭhānaṃ gacchati, pañca ca thālipākasatāni bhattābhihāro abhiharīyati.**Now at that time Prince Ajātasattu was going with five hundred carts in the morning and the evening to attend on Devadatta, presenting him with an offering of five hundred servings of food.*";
P_HTM[5283]="*Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then several mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[5284]="*“devadattassa, bhante, ajātasattukumāro pañcahi rathasatehi sāyaṃ pātaṃ upaṭṭhānaṃ gacchati, pañca ca thālipākasatāni bhattābhihāro abhiharīyatī”ti.**“Sir, Prince Ajātasattu is going with five hundred carts in the morning and the evening to attend on Devadatta, presenting him with an offering of five hundred servings of food.”*";
P_HTM[5285]="*“Mā, bhikkhave, devadattassa lābhasakkārasilokaṃ pihayittha.**“Mendicants, don’t envy Devadatta’s possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[5286]="*Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, devadattassa ajātasattukumāro pañcahi rathasatehi sāyaṃ pātaṃ upaṭṭhānaṃ gamissati, pañca ca thālipākasatāni bhattābhihāro āharīyissati, hāniyeva, bhikkhave, devadattassa pāṭikaṅkhā kusalesu dhammesu, no vuddhi.**As long as Prince Ajātasattu goes with five hundred carts in the morning and the evening to attend on Devadatta, presenting him with an offering of five hundred servings of food, Devadatta can expect decline, not growth, in skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[5287]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, caṇḍassa kukkurassa nāsāya pittaṃ bhindeyyuṃ, evañhi so, bhikkhave, kukkuro bhiyyoso mattāya caṇḍataro assa;**If bile were to burst from a wild dog’s nose, it would become even wilder.*";
P_HTM[5288]="*evameva, bhikkhave, yāvakīvañca devadattassa ajātasattukumāro pañcahi rathasatehi sāyaṃ pātaṃ upaṭṭhānaṃ gamissati, pañca ca thālipākasatāni bhattābhihāro āharīyissati, hāniyeva, bhikkhave, devadattassa pāṭikaṅkhā kusalesu dhammesu, no vuddhi.**In the same way, as long as Prince Ajātasattu goes with five hundred carts in the morning and the evening to attend on Devadatta, presenting him with an offering of five hundred servings of food, Devadatta can expect decline, not growth, in skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[5289]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”*";
P_HTM[5290]="*evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5291]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5292]="*7. Mātusuttaṃ**Mother*";
P_HTM[5293]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5294]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko kaṭuko pharuso antarāyiko anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya.**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal, bitter, and harsh. They’re an obstacle to reaching the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[5295]="*Idhāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:**When I’ve comprehended the mind of a certain person, I understand:*";
P_HTM[5296]="*‘na cāyamāyasmā mātupi hetu sampajānamusā bhāseyyā’ti.**‘This venerable would not tell a deliberate lie even for the sake of their mother.’*";
P_HTM[5297]="*Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena lābhasakkārasilokena abhibhūtaṃ pariyādiṇṇacittaṃ sampajānamusā bhāsantaṃ.**But some time later I see them tell a deliberate lie because their mind is overcome and overwhelmed by possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[5298]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko kaṭuko pharuso antarāyiko anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya.**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity—bitter and harsh, an obstacle to reaching the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[5299]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[5300]="*‘uppannaṃ lābhasakkārasilokaṃ pajahissāma.**‘We will give up arisen possessions, honor, and popularity, and we won’t let them occupy our minds.’*";
P_HTM[5301]="*Na ca no uppanno lābhasakkārasiloko cittaṃ pariyādāya ṭhassatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5302]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[5303]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5304]="*8-13. Pitusuttādichakkaṃ**38–43. Pitusuttādichakka*";
P_HTM[5305]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5306]="*“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko kaṭuko pharuso antarāyiko anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya.**“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal, bitter, and harsh. They’re an obstacle to reaching the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[5307]="*Idhāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:**When I’ve comprehended the mind of a certain person, I understand:*";
P_HTM[5308]="*‘na cāyamāyasmā pitupi hetu … pe …**‘This venerable would not tell a deliberate lie even for the sake of their father. …*";
P_HTM[5309]="*(vitthāretabbaṃ) …**(To be expanded as in SN 17.37.)*";
P_HTM[5310]="*bhātupi hetu …**brother …*";
P_HTM[5311]="*bhaginiyāpi hetu …**sister …*";
P_HTM[5312]="*puttassapi hetu …**son …*";
P_HTM[5313]="*dhītuyāpi hetu …**daughter …*";
P_HTM[5314]="*pajāpatiyāpi hetu sampajānamusā bhāseyyā’ti.**wife.’*";
P_HTM[5315]="*Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena lābhasakkārasilokena abhibhūtaṃ pariyādiṇṇacittaṃ sampajānamusā bhāsantaṃ.**But some time later I see them tell a deliberate lie because their mind is overcome and overwhelmed by possessions, honor, and popularity.*";
P_HTM[5316]="*Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko kaṭuko pharuso antarāyiko anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya.**So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity—bitter and harsh, an obstacle to reaching the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[5317]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[5318]="*‘uppannaṃ lābhasakkārasilokaṃ pajahissāma, na ca no uppanno lābhasakkārasiloko cittaṃ pariyādāya ṭhassatī’ti.**‘We will give up arisen possessions, honor, and popularity, and we won’t let them occupy our minds.’*";
P_HTM[5319]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[5320]="*Terasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5321]="*Catuttho vaggo.* **";
P_HTM[5322]="*Bhindi mūlaṃ duve dhammā,* **";
P_HTM[5323]="*pakkantaṃ ratha mātari;* **";
P_HTM[5324]="*Pitā bhātā ca bhaginī,* **";
P_HTM[5325]="*putto dhītā pajāpatīti.* **";
P_HTM[5326]="*Lābhasakkārasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ.**The Linked Discourses on possessions, honor, and popularity are complete.*";
P_HTM[5327]="*18. Rāhulasaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[5328]="*1. Buddhavaggo**The First Chapter*";
P_HTM[5329]="*1. Cakkhusuttaṃ**The Eye, Etc.*";
P_HTM[5330]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[5331]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[5332]="*Atha kho āyasmā rāhulo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā rāhulo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Venerable Rāhula went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[5333]="*“sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā saṃkhittena dhammaṃ desetu, yamahaṃ bhagavato dhammaṃ sutvā eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto vihareyyan”ti.**“Sir, may the Buddha please teach me Dhamma in brief. When I’ve heard it, I’ll live alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute.”*";
P_HTM[5334]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rāhula,**“What do you think, Rāhula?*";
P_HTM[5335]="*cakkhuṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**Is the eye permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5336]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5337]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[5338]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5339]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:**“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be regarded thus:*";
P_HTM[5340]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[5341]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5342]="*“Sotaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**“Is the ear permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5343]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe ….**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5344]="*“Ghānaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**“Is the nose permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5345]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5346]="*“Jivhā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?**“Is the tongue permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5347]="*“Aniccā, bhante” …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5348]="*“Kāyo nicco vā anicco vā”ti?**“Is the body permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5349]="*“Anicco, bhante” …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5350]="*“Mano nicco vā anicco vā”ti?**“Is the mind permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5351]="*“Anicco, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5352]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[5353]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5354]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:**“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be regarded thus:*";
P_HTM[5355]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[5356]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5357]="*“Evaṃ passaṃ, rāhula, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati … pe … sotasmimpi nibbindati … ghānasmimpi nibbindati … jivhāyapi nibbindati … kāyasmimpi nibbindati … manasmimpi nibbindati;**“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, the ear, the nose, the tongue, the body, and the mind.*";
P_HTM[5358]="*nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[5359]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[5360]="*(Etena peyyālena dasa suttantā kātabbā.)**(The ten discourses of this series should be treated in the same way.)*";
P_HTM[5361]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5362]="*2. Rūpasuttaṃ**Sights, Etc.*";
P_HTM[5363]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5364]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rāhula,**“What do you think, Rāhula?*";
P_HTM[5365]="*rūpā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?**Are sights permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5366]="*“Aniccā, bhante” … pe …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5367]="*saddā …**“… sounds …*";
P_HTM[5368]="*gandhā …**smells …*";
P_HTM[5369]="*rasā …**tastes …*";
P_HTM[5370]="*phoṭṭhabbā …**touches …*";
P_HTM[5371]="*dhammā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?**Are thoughts permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5372]="*“Aniccā, bhante” …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5373]="*“evaṃ passaṃ, rāhula, sutavā ariyasāvako rūpesupi nibbindati … saddesupi nibbindati … gandhesupi nibbindati … rasesupi nibbindati … phoṭṭhabbesupi nibbindati … dhammesupi nibbindati;**“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with sights, sounds, smells, tastes, touches, and thoughts.*";
P_HTM[5374]="*nibbindaṃ virajjati … pe …**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. …”*";
P_HTM[5375]="*pajānātī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5376]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5377]="*3. Viññāṇasuttaṃ**Consciousness*";
P_HTM[5378]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5379]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rāhula,**“What do you think, Rāhula?*";
P_HTM[5380]="*cakkhuviññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**Is eye consciousness permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5381]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5382]="*“sotaviññāṇaṃ … pe …**“… ear consciousness …*";
P_HTM[5383]="*ghānaviññāṇaṃ …**nose consciousness …*";
P_HTM[5384]="*jivhāviññāṇaṃ …**tongue consciousness …*";
P_HTM[5385]="*kāyaviññāṇaṃ …**body consciousness …*";
P_HTM[5386]="*manoviññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**Is mind consciousness permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5387]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5388]="*“evaṃ passaṃ, rāhula, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhuviññāṇasmimpi nibbindati … pe … sotaviññāṇasmimpi nibbindati … ghānaviññāṇasmimpi nibbindati … jivhāviññāṇasmimpi nibbindati … kāyaviññāṇasmimpi nibbindati … manoviññāṇasmimpi nibbindati;**“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with eye consciousness, ear consciousness, nose consciousness, tongue consciousness, body consciousness, and mind consciousness.*";
P_HTM[5389]="*nibbindaṃ virajjati … pe …**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. …”*";
P_HTM[5390]="*pajānātī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5391]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5392]="*4. Samphassasuttaṃ**Contact*";
P_HTM[5393]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5394]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rāhula,**“What do you think, Rāhula?*";
P_HTM[5395]="*cakkhusamphasso nicco vā anicco vā”ti?**Is eye contact permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5396]="*“Anicco, bhante” …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5397]="*“sotasamphasso … pe …**“… ear contact …*";
P_HTM[5398]="*ghānasamphasso …**nose contact …*";
P_HTM[5399]="*jivhāsamphasso …**tongue contact …*";
P_HTM[5400]="*kāyasamphasso …**body contact …*";
P_HTM[5401]="*manosamphasso nicco vā anicco vā”ti?**Is mind contact permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5402]="*“Anicco, bhante” …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5403]="*“evaṃ passaṃ, rāhula, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusamphassasmimpi nibbindati … pe … sotasamphassasmimpi nibbindati … ghānasamphassasmimpi nibbindati … jivhāsamphassasmimpi nibbindati … kāyasamphassasmimpi nibbindati … manosamphassasmimpi nibbindati;**“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with eye contact, ear contact, nose contact, tongue contact, body contact, and mind contact.*";
P_HTM[5404]="*nibbindaṃ virajjati … pe …**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. …”*";
P_HTM[5405]="*pajānātī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5406]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5407]="*5. Vedanāsuttaṃ**Feeling*";
P_HTM[5408]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5409]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rāhula,**“What do you think, Rāhula?*";
P_HTM[5410]="*cakkhusamphassajā vedanā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?**Is feeling born of eye contact permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5411]="*“Aniccā, bhante” …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5412]="*“sotasamphassajā vedanā … pe …**“… feeling born of ear contact …*";
P_HTM[5413]="*ghānasamphassajā vedanā …**feeling born of nose contact …*";
P_HTM[5414]="*jivhāsamphassajā vedanā …**feeling born of tongue contact …*";
P_HTM[5415]="*kāyasamphassajā vedanā …**feeling born of body contact …*";
P_HTM[5416]="*manosamphassajā vedanā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?**Is feeling born of mind contact permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5417]="*“Aniccā, bhante” …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5418]="*“evaṃ passaṃ, rāhula, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusamphassajāya vedanāyapi nibbindati … pe … sota … ghāna … jivhā … kāya … manosamphassajāya vedanāyapi nibbindati … pe …**“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with feeling born of eye contact, ear contact, nose contact, tongue contact, body contact, and mind contact. …”*";
P_HTM[5419]="*pajānātī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5420]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5421]="*6. Saññāsuttaṃ**Perceptions*";
P_HTM[5422]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5423]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rāhula,**“What do you think, Rāhula?*";
P_HTM[5424]="*rūpasaññā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?**Is perception of sights permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5425]="*“Aniccā, bhante” …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5426]="*“saddasaññā … pe …**“… perception of sounds …*";
P_HTM[5427]="*gandhasaññā …**perception of smells …*";
P_HTM[5428]="*rasasaññā …**perception of tastes …*";
P_HTM[5429]="*phoṭṭhabbasaññā …**perception of touches …*";
P_HTM[5430]="*dhammasaññā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?**Is perception of thoughts permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5431]="*“Aniccā, bhante” …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5432]="*“evaṃ passaṃ, rāhula, sutavā ariyasāvako rūpasaññāyapi nibbindati … pe … saddasaññāyapi nibbindati … gandhasaññāyapi nibbindati … rasasaññāyapi nibbindati … phoṭṭhabbasaññāyapi nibbindati … dhammasaññāyapi nibbindati … pe …**“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the perception of sights, sounds, smells, tastes, touches, and thoughts. …”*";
P_HTM[5433]="*pajānātī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5434]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5435]="*7. Sañcetanāsuttaṃ**Intention*";
P_HTM[5436]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5437]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rāhula,**“What do you think, Rāhula?*";
P_HTM[5438]="*rūpasañcetanā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?**Is intention regarding sights permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5439]="*“Aniccā, bhante” …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5440]="*“saddasañcetanā … pe …**“… intention regarding sounds …*";
P_HTM[5441]="*gandhasañcetanā …**intention regarding smells …*";
P_HTM[5442]="*rasasañcetanā …**intention regarding tastes …*";
P_HTM[5443]="*phoṭṭhabbasañcetanā …**intention regarding touches …*";
P_HTM[5444]="*dhammasañcetanā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?**Is intention regarding thoughts permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5445]="*“Aniccā, bhante” …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5446]="*“evaṃ passaṃ, rāhula, sutavā ariyasāvako rūpasañcetanāyapi nibbindati … pe … saddasañcetanāyapi nibbindati … gandhasañcetanāyapi nibbindati … rasasañcetanāyapi nibbindati … phoṭṭhabbasañcetanāyapi nibbindati … dhammasañcetanāyapi nibbindati … pe …**“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with intention regarding sights, sounds, smells, tastes, touches, and thoughts. …”*";
P_HTM[5447]="*pajānātī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5448]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5449]="*8. Taṇhāsuttaṃ**Craving*";
P_HTM[5450]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5451]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rāhula,**“What do you think, Rāhula?*";
P_HTM[5452]="*rūpataṇhā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?**Is craving for sights permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5453]="*“Aniccā, bhante” …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5454]="*“saddataṇhā … pe …**“… craving for sounds …*";
P_HTM[5455]="*gandhataṇhā …**craving for smells …*";
P_HTM[5456]="*rasataṇhā …**craving for tastes …*";
P_HTM[5457]="*phoṭṭhabbataṇhā …**craving for touches …*";
P_HTM[5458]="*dhammataṇhā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?**Is craving for thoughts permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5459]="*“Aniccā, bhante” …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5460]="*“evaṃ passaṃ, rāhula, sutavā ariyasāvako rūpataṇhāyapi nibbindati … pe … saddataṇhāyapi nibbindati … gandhataṇhāyapi nibbindati … rasataṇhāyapi nibbindati … phoṭṭhabbataṇhāyapi nibbindati … dhammataṇhāyapi nibbindati … pe …**“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with craving for sights, sounds, smells, tastes, touches, and thoughts. …”*";
P_HTM[5461]="*pajānātī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5462]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5463]="*9. Dhātusuttaṃ**Elements*";
P_HTM[5464]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5465]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rāhula,**“What do you think, Rāhula?*";
P_HTM[5466]="*pathavīdhātu niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?**Is the earth element permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5467]="*“Aniccā, bhante” …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5468]="*“āpodhātu … pe …**“… the water element …*";
P_HTM[5469]="*tejodhātu …**the fire element …*";
P_HTM[5470]="*vāyodhātu …**the air element …*";
P_HTM[5471]="*ākāsadhātu …**the space element …*";
P_HTM[5472]="*viññāṇadhātu niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?**Is the consciousness element permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5473]="*“Aniccā, bhante” …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5474]="*“evaṃ passaṃ, rāhula, sutavā ariyasāvako pathavīdhātuyāpi nibbindati … pe … āpodhātuyāpi nibbindati … tejodhātuyāpi nibbindati … vāyodhātuyāpi nibbindati … ākāsadhātuyāpi nibbindati … viññāṇadhātuyāpi nibbindati … pe …**“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the earth element, water element, fire element, air element, space element, and consciousness element …”*";
P_HTM[5475]="*pajānātī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5476]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5477]="*10. Khandhasuttaṃ**The Aggregates*";
P_HTM[5478]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5479]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rāhula,**“What do you think, Rāhula?*";
P_HTM[5480]="*rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**Is form permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5481]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5482]="*“vedanā … pe …**“… feeling …*";
P_HTM[5483]="*saññā …**perception …*";
P_HTM[5484]="*saṅkhārā …**choices …*";
P_HTM[5485]="*viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**Is consciousness permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5486]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” …**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[5487]="*“evaṃ passaṃ, rāhula, sutavā ariyasāvako rūpasmimpi nibbindati … pe … vedanāyapi nibbindati … saññāyapi nibbindati … saṅkhāresupi nibbindati … viññāṇasmimpi nibbindati;**“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness.*";
P_HTM[5488]="*nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[5489]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[5490]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
