P_HTM[5494]="*Saññā sañcetanā taṇhā,* **";
P_HTM[5495]="*dhātu khandhena te dasāti.* **";
P_HTM[5496]="*2. Āhāravaggo**The Second Chapter*";
P_HTM[5497]="*1. Cakkhusuttaṃ**The Eye, Etc.*";
P_HTM[5498]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[5499]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5500]="*Atha kho āyasmā rāhulo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ rāhulaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then Venerable Rāhula went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[5501]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rāhula,**“What do you think, Rāhula?*";
P_HTM[5502]="*cakkhuṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**Is the eye permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5503]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5504]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[5505]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5506]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:**“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be regarded thus:*";
P_HTM[5507]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[5508]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5509]="*“Sotaṃ … pe …**“… the ear …*";
P_HTM[5510]="*ghānaṃ …**the nose …*";
P_HTM[5511]="*jivhā …**the tongue …*";
P_HTM[5512]="*kāyo …**the body …*";
P_HTM[5513]="*mano nicco vā anicco vā”ti?**Is the mind permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[5514]="*“Anicco, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5515]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[5516]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5517]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:**“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be regarded thus:*";
P_HTM[5518]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[5519]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5520]="*“Evaṃ passaṃ, rāhula, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati … pe … sotasmimpi nibbindati … ghānasmimpi nibbindati … jivhāyapi nibbindati … kāyasmimpi nibbindati … manasmimpi nibbindati;**“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, the ear, the nose, the tongue, the body, and the mind.*";
P_HTM[5521]="*nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[5522]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[5523]="*(Etena peyyālena dasa suttantā kātabbā.)**(The ten discourses of this series should be treated in the same way.)*";
P_HTM[5524]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
