P_HTM[5586]="*11. Anusayasuttaṃ**Tendency*";
P_HTM[5587]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5588]="*Atha kho āyasmā rāhulo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā rāhulo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Venerable Rāhula went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[5589]="*“kathaṃ nu kho, bhante, jānato kathaṃ passato imasmiñca saviññāṇake kāye bahiddhā ca sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā na hontī”ti?**“Sir, how does one know and see so that there’s no ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to conceit for this conscious body and all external stimuli?”*";
P_HTM[5590]="*“Yaṃ kiñci, rāhula, rūpaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ rūpaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passati.**“Rāhula, one truly sees any kind of form at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: all form—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[5591]="*Yā kāci vedanā … pe …**One truly sees any kind of feeling …*";
P_HTM[5592]="*yā kāci saññā …**perception …*";
P_HTM[5593]="*ye keci saṅkhārā …**choices …*";
P_HTM[5594]="*yaṃ kiñci viññāṇaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ viññāṇaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passati.**consciousness at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: all consciousness—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[5595]="*Evaṃ kho, rāhula, jānato evaṃ passato imasmiñca saviññāṇake kāye bahiddhā ca sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā na hontī”ti.**That’s how to know and see so that there’s no ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to conceit for this conscious body and all external stimuli.”*";
P_HTM[5596]="*Ekādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5597]="*12. Apagatasuttaṃ**Rid of Conceit*";
P_HTM[5598]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5599]="*Atha kho āyasmā rāhulo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā rāhulo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then Venerable Rāhula went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[5600]="*“kathaṃ nu kho, bhante, jānato kathaṃ passato imasmiṃ ca saviññāṇake kāye bahiddhā ca sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānāpagataṃ mānasaṃ hoti vidhā samatikkantaṃ santaṃ suvimuttan”ti?**“Sir, how does one know and see so that the mind is rid of ego, possessiveness, and conceit for this conscious body and all external stimuli; and going beyond discrimination, it’s peaceful and well freed?”*";
P_HTM[5601]="*“Yaṃ kiñci, rāhula, rūpaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā sabbaṃ rūpaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā anupādā vimutto hoti.**“Rāhula, when one truly sees any kind of form at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: all form—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self,’ one is freed by not grasping.*";
P_HTM[5602]="*Yā kāci vedanā … pe …**When one truly sees any kind of feeling …*";
P_HTM[5603]="*yā kāci saññā …**perception …*";
P_HTM[5604]="*ye keci saṅkhārā …**choices …*";
P_HTM[5605]="*yaṃ kiñci viññāṇaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ viññāṇaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā anupādā vimutto hoti.**When one truly sees any kind of consciousness at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: all consciousness—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self,’ one is freed by not grasping.*";
P_HTM[5606]="*Evaṃ kho, rāhula, jānato evaṃ passato imasmiñca saviññāṇake kāye bahiddhā ca sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānāpagataṃ mānasaṃ hoti vidhā samatikkantaṃ santaṃ suvimuttan”ti.**That’s how to know and see so that the mind is rid of ego, possessiveness, and conceit for this conscious body and all external stimuli; and going beyond discrimination, it’s peaceful and well freed.”*";
P_HTM[5607]="*Dvādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5608]="*Dutiyo vaggo.* **";
P_HTM[5609]="*Cakkhu rūpañca viññāṇaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[5610]="*Samphasso vedanāya ca;* **";
P_HTM[5611]="*Saññā sañcetanā taṇhā,* **";
P_HTM[5612]="*Dhātu khandhena te dasa;* **";
P_HTM[5613]="*Anusayaṃ apagatañceva,* **";
P_HTM[5614]="*Vaggo tena pavuccatīti.* **";
P_HTM[5615]="*Rāhulasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ.**The Linked Discourses with Rāhula are complete.*";
P_HTM[5616]="*19. Lakkhaṇasaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[5617]="*1. Buddhavaggo**The First Chapter*";
P_HTM[5618]="*1. Aṭṭhisuttaṃ**A Skeleton*";
P_HTM[5619]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[5620]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[5621]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā ca lakkhaṇo āyasmā ca mahāmoggallāno gijjhakūṭe pabbate viharanti.**Now at that time Venerable Lakkhaṇa and Venerable Mahāmoggallāna were staying on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain.*";
P_HTM[5622]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yenāyasmā lakkhaṇo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ lakkhaṇaṃ etadavoca:**Then Mahāmoggallāna robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to Lakkhaṇa and said to him,*";
P_HTM[5623]="*“āyāmāvuso lakkhaṇa, rājagahaṃ piṇḍāya pavisissāmā”ti.**“Come, Reverend Lakkhaṇa, let’s enter Rājagaha for alms.”*";
P_HTM[5624]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā lakkhaṇo āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa paccassosi.**“Yes, reverend,” Lakkhaṇa replied.*";
P_HTM[5625]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto aññatarasmiṃ padese sitaṃ pātvākāsi.**As Mahāmoggallāna was descending from Vulture’s Peak Mountain he smiled at a certain spot.*";
P_HTM[5626]="*Atha kho āyasmā lakkhaṇo āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ etadavoca:**So Lakkhaṇa said to Mahāmoggallāna,*";
P_HTM[5627]="*“ko nu kho, āvuso moggallāna, hetu ko paccayo sitassa pātukammāyā”ti?**“What is the cause, Reverend Moggallāna, what is the reason you smiled?”*";
P_HTM[5628]="*“Akālo kho, āvuso lakkhaṇa, etassa pañhassa.**“Reverend Lakkhaṇa, it’s the wrong time for this question.*";
P_HTM[5629]="*Bhagavato maṃ santike etaṃ pañhaṃ pucchā”ti.**Ask me when we’re in the Buddha’s presence.”*";
P_HTM[5630]="*Atha kho āyasmā ca lakkhaṇo āyasmā ca mahāmoggallāno rājagahe piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā lakkhaṇo āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ etadavoca:**Then Lakkhaṇa and Mahāmoggallāna wandered for alms in Rājagaha. After the meal, on their return from alms-round, they went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. Lakkhaṇa said to Mahāmoggallāna:*";
P_HTM[5631]="*“idhāyasmā mahāmoggallāno gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto aññatarasmiṃ padese sitaṃ pātvākāsi.**“Just now, as Mahāmoggallāna was descending from Vulture’s Peak Mountain he smiled at a certain spot.*";
P_HTM[5632]="*Ko nu kho, āvuso moggallāna, hetu ko paccayo sitassa pātukammāyā”ti?**What is the cause, Reverend Moggallāna, what is the reason you smiled?”*";
P_HTM[5633]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ aṭṭhikasaṅkhalikaṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantiṃ.**“Just now, reverend, as I was descending from Vulture’s Peak Mountain I saw a skeleton flying through the air.*";
P_HTM[5634]="*Tamenaṃ gijjhāpi kākāpi kulalāpi anupatitvā anupatitvā phāsuḷantarikāhi vitudenti vitacchenti virājenti.**Vultures, crows, and hawks kept chasing it, pecking and clawing*";
P_HTM[5635]="*Sā sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti.**as it screeched in pain.*";
P_HTM[5636]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, āvuso, etadahosi:**It occurred to me:*";
P_HTM[5637]="*‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho.**‘It’s incredible, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[5638]="*Evarūpopi nāma satto bhavissati.**That there can be such a sentient being,*";
P_HTM[5639]="*Evarūpopi nāma yakkho bhavissati.**such an entity,*";
P_HTM[5640]="*Evarūpopi nāma attabhāvapaṭilābho bhavissatī’”ti.**such an incarnation!’”*";
P_HTM[5641]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[5642]="*“cakkhubhūtā vata, bhikkhave, sāvakā viharanti;**“Mendicants, there are disciples who live full of vision and knowledge,*";
P_HTM[5643]="*ñāṇabhūtā vata, bhikkhave, sāvakā viharanti, yatra hi nāma sāvako evarūpaṃ ñassati vā dakkhati vā sakkhiṃ vā karissati.**since a disciple knows, sees, and witnesses such a thing.*";
P_HTM[5644]="*Pubbeva me so, bhikkhave, satto diṭṭho ahosi, api cāhaṃ na byākāsiṃ.**Formerly, I too saw that being, but I did not speak of it.*";
P_HTM[5645]="*Ahañcetaṃ byākareyyaṃ, pare ca me na saddaheyyuṃ.**For if I had spoken of it others would not have believed me,*";
P_HTM[5646]="*Ye me na saddaheyyuṃ, tesaṃ taṃ assa dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya.**which would be for their lasting harm and suffering.*";
P_HTM[5647]="*Eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe goghātako ahosi.**That being used to be a cattle butcher right here in Rājagaha.*";
P_HTM[5648]="*So tassa kammassa vipākena bahūni vassāni bahūni vassasatāni bahūni vassasahassāni bahūni vassasatasahassāni niraye paccitvā tasseva kammassa vipākāvasesena evarūpaṃ attabhāvapaṭilābhaṃ paṭisaṃvedayatī”ti.**As a result of that deed he burned in hell for many years, many hundreds, many thousands, many hundreds of thousands of years. Now he experiences the residual result of that deed in such an incarnation.”*";
P_HTM[5649]="*(Sabbesaṃ suttantānaṃ eseva peyyālo.)**(All these discourses should be expanded like this.)*";
P_HTM[5650]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5651]="*2. Pesisuttaṃ**A Piece of Meat*";
P_HTM[5652]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ maṃsapesiṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantiṃ.**“Just now, reverend, as I was descending from Vulture’s Peak Mountain I saw a lump of meat flying through the air.*";
P_HTM[5653]="*Tamenaṃ gijjhāpi kākāpi kulalāpi anupatitvā anupatitvā vitacchenti virājenti.**Vultures, crows, and hawks kept chasing it, pecking and clawing*";
P_HTM[5654]="*Sā sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …**as it screeched in pain. …” …*";
P_HTM[5655]="*eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe goghātako ahosi … pe ….**“That being used to be a cattle butcher right here in Rājagaha. …”*";
P_HTM[5656]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5657]="*3. Piṇḍasuttaṃ**A Piece of Flesh*";
P_HTM[5658]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ maṃsapiṇḍaṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantaṃ.**“Just now, reverend, as I was descending from Vulture’s Peak Mountain I saw a piece of flesh flying through the air.*";
P_HTM[5659]="*Tamenaṃ gijjhāpi kākāpi kulalāpi anupatitvā anupatitvā vitacchenti virājenti.**Vultures, crows, and hawks kept chasing it, pecking and clawing*";
P_HTM[5660]="*Sā sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …**as it screeched in pain. …” …*";
P_HTM[5661]="*eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe sākuṇiko ahosi … pe ….**“That being used to be a bird hunter right here in Rājagaha. …”*";
P_HTM[5662]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5663]="*4. Nicchavisuttaṃ**A Flayed Man*";
P_HTM[5664]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ nicchaviṃ purisaṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantaṃ.**“Just now, reverend, as I was descending from Vulture’s Peak Mountain I saw a flayed man flying through the air.*";
P_HTM[5665]="*Tamenaṃ gijjhāpi kākāpi kulalāpi anupatitvā anupatitvā vitacchenti virājenti.**Vultures, crows, and hawks kept chasing it, pecking and clawing*";
P_HTM[5666]="*So sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …**as he screamed in pain. …” …*";
P_HTM[5667]="*eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe orabbhiko ahosi … pe ….**“That being used to be a sheep butcher right here in Rājagaha. …”*";
P_HTM[5668]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5669]="*5. Asilomasuttaṃ**Sword Hairs*";
P_HTM[5670]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ asilomaṃ purisaṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantaṃ.**“Just now, reverend, as I was descending from Vulture’s Peak Mountain I saw a man whose body hairs were swords flying through the air.*";
P_HTM[5671]="*Tassa te asī uppatitvā uppatitvā tasseva kāye nipatanti.**And those swords kept rising up and falling on his body*";
P_HTM[5672]="*So sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …**as he screamed in pain. …” …*";
P_HTM[5673]="*eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe sūkariko ahosi … pe ….**“That being used to be a pig butcher right here in Rājagaha. …”*";
P_HTM[5674]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5675]="*6. Sattisuttaṃ**Spear Hairs*";
P_HTM[5676]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ sattilomaṃ purisaṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantaṃ.**“Just now, reverend, as I was descending from Vulture’s Peak Mountain I saw a man whose body hairs were spears flying through the air.*";
P_HTM[5677]="*Tassa tā sattiyo uppatitvā uppatitvā tasseva kāye nipatanti.**And those spears kept rising up and falling on his body*";
P_HTM[5678]="*So sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …**as he screamed in pain. …” …*";
P_HTM[5679]="*eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe māgaviko ahosi … pe ….**“That being used to be a deer hunter right here in Rājagaha. …”*";
P_HTM[5680]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5681]="*7. Usulomasuttaṃ**Arrow Hairs*";
P_HTM[5682]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ usulomaṃ purisaṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantaṃ.**“Just now, reverend, as I was descending from Vulture’s Peak Mountain I saw a man whose body hairs were arrows flying through the air.*";
P_HTM[5683]="*Tassa te usū uppatitvā uppatitvā tasseva kāye nipatanti.**And those arrows kept rising up and falling on his body*";
P_HTM[5684]="*So sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …**as he screamed in pain. …” …*";
P_HTM[5685]="*eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe kāraṇiko ahosi … pe ….**“That being used to be a torturer right here in Rājagaha. …”*";
P_HTM[5686]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5687]="*8. Sūcilomasuttaṃ**Needle Hairs*";
P_HTM[5688]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ sūcilomaṃ purisaṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantaṃ.**“Just now, reverend, as I was descending from Vulture’s Peak Mountain I saw a man whose body hairs were needles flying through the air.*";
P_HTM[5689]="*Tassa tā sūciyo uppatitvā uppatitvā tasseva kāye nipatanti.**And those needles kept rising up and falling on his body*";
P_HTM[5690]="*So sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …**as he screamed in pain. …” …*";
P_HTM[5691]="*eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe sūto ahosi … pe ….**“That being used to be a war herald right here in Rājagaha. …”*";
P_HTM[5692]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5693]="*9. Dutiyasūcilomasuttaṃ**Needle Hairs (2nd)*";
P_HTM[5694]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ sūcilomaṃ purisaṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantaṃ.**“Just now, reverend, as I was descending from Vulture’s Peak Mountain I saw a man whose body hairs were needles flying through the air.*";
P_HTM[5695]="*Tassa tā sūciyo sīse pavisitvā mukhato nikkhamanti;**The needles bored into his head and out his mouth,*";
P_HTM[5696]="*mukhe pavisitvā urato nikkhamanti;**into his mouth and out his chest,*";
P_HTM[5697]="*ure pavisitvā udarato nikkhamanti;**into his chest and out his belly,*";
P_HTM[5698]="*udare pavisitvā ūrūhi nikkhamanti;**into his belly and out his thighs,*";
P_HTM[5699]="*ūrūsu pavisitvā jaṅghāhi nikkhamanti;**into his thighs and out his calves,*";
P_HTM[5700]="*jaṅghāsu pavisitvā pādehi nikkhamanti;**and into his calves and out his feet.*";
P_HTM[5701]="*so sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …**And he screamed in pain. …” …*";
P_HTM[5702]="*eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe sūcako ahosi … pe ….**“That being used to be an informant right here in Rājagaha. …”*";
P_HTM[5703]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5704]="*10. Kumbhaṇḍasuttaṃ**Pot Balls*";
P_HTM[5705]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ kumbhaṇḍaṃ purisaṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantaṃ.**“Just now, reverend, as I was descending from Vulture’s Peak Mountain I saw a man with testicles as big as pots flying through the air.*";
P_HTM[5706]="*So gacchantopi teva aṇḍe khandhe āropetvā gacchati.**When he was walking he had to lift his testicles on to his shoulder.*";
P_HTM[5707]="*Nisīdantopi tesveva aṇḍesu nisīdati.**And when he sat down, he sat right on them.*";
P_HTM[5708]="*Tamenaṃ gijjhāpi kākāpi kulalāpi anupatitvā anupatitvā vitacchenti virājenti.**Vultures, crows, and hawks kept chasing him, pecking, plucking, and hacking*";
P_HTM[5709]="*So sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …**as he screamed in pain. …” …*";
P_HTM[5710]="*eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe gāmakūṭako ahosi … pe ….**“That being used to be a corrupt official right here in Rājagaha. …”*";
P_HTM[5711]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5712]="*Paṭhamo vaggo.* **";
P_HTM[5713]="*Aṭṭhi pesi ubho gāvaghātakā,* **";
P_HTM[5714]="*Piṇḍo sākuṇiyo nicchavorabbhi;* **";
P_HTM[5715]="*Asi sūkariko sattimāgavi,* **";
P_HTM[5716]="*Usu kāraṇiko sūci sārathi;* **";
P_HTM[5717]="*Yo ca sibbiyati sūcako hi so,* **";
P_HTM[5718]="*Aṇḍabhāri ahu gāmakūṭakoti.* **";
P_HTM[5719]="*2. Āhāravaggo**The Second Chapter*";
P_HTM[5720]="*1. Sasīsakasuttaṃ**Over His Head*";
P_HTM[5721]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[5722]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ rājagahe veḷuvane.**At one time near Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove...*";
P_HTM[5723]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ purisaṃ gūthakūpe sasīsakaṃ nimuggaṃ … pe …**“Just now, reverend, as I was descending from Vulture’s Peak Mountain I saw a man sunk over his head in a sewer. …” …*";
P_HTM[5724]="*eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe pāradāriko ahosi … pe ….**“That being used to be an adulterer right here in Rājagaha. …”*";
P_HTM[5725]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5726]="*2. Gūthakhādasuttaṃ**A Dung Eater*";
P_HTM[5727]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ purisaṃ gūthakūpe nimuggaṃ ubhohi hatthehi gūthaṃ khādantaṃ … pe …**“Just now, reverend, as I was descending from Vulture’s Peak Mountain I saw a man sunk in a sewer, eating dung with both hands. …” …*";
P_HTM[5728]="*eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe duṭṭhabrāhmaṇo ahosi.**“That being used to be a nasty brahmin right here in Rājagaha.*";
P_HTM[5729]="*So kassapassa sammāsambuddhassa pāvacane bhikkhusaṃghaṃ bhattena nimantetvā doṇiyo gūthassa pūrāpetvā etadavoca—**In the time of the Buddha Kassapa’s dispensation he invited the Saṅgha of mendicants for a meal. He filled a trough with dung and said:*";
P_HTM[5730]="*aho bhonto yāvadatthaṃ bhuñjantu ceva harantu cā’ti … pe ….**‘My good men, eat as much as you like, and take what’s left.’ …”*";
P_HTM[5731]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5732]="*3. Nicchavitthisuttaṃ**A Flayed Woman*";
P_HTM[5733]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ nicchaviṃ itthiṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantiṃ.**“Just now, reverend, as I was descending from Vulture’s Peak Mountain I saw a flayed woman flying through the air.*";
P_HTM[5734]="*Tamenaṃ gijjhāpi kākāpi kulalāpi anupatitvā anupatitvā vitacchenti virājenti.**Vultures, crows, and hawks kept chasing her, pecking, plucking, and hacking*";
P_HTM[5735]="*Sā sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …**as she screamed in pain. …” …*";
P_HTM[5736]="*esā, bhikkhave, itthī imasmiṃyeva rājagahe aticārinī ahosi … pe ….**“That woman used to be an adulteress right here in Rājagaha. …”*";
P_HTM[5737]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5738]="*4. Maṅgulitthisuttaṃ**A Fishwife*";
P_HTM[5739]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ itthiṃ duggandhaṃ maṅguliṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantiṃ.**“Just now, reverend, as I was descending from Vulture’s Peak Mountain I saw a stinking fishwife flying through the air.*";
P_HTM[5740]="*Tamenaṃ gijjhāpi kākāpi kulalāpi anupatitvā anupatitvā vitacchenti virājenti.**Vultures, crows, and hawks kept chasing her, pecking, plucking, and hacking*";
P_HTM[5741]="*Sā sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …**as she screamed in pain. …” …*";
P_HTM[5742]="*esā, bhikkhave, itthī imasmiṃyeva rājagahe ikkhaṇikā ahosi … pe ….**“That woman used to be a fortune-teller right here in Rājagaha. …”*";
P_HTM[5743]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5744]="*5. Okilinīsuttaṃ**A Sweltering Woman*";
P_HTM[5745]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ itthiṃ uppakkaṃ okiliniṃ okiriniṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantiṃ.**“Just now, reverend, as I was descending from Vulture’s Peak Mountain I saw a scorched woman, sooty and sweaty, flying through the air,*";
P_HTM[5746]="*Sā sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …**as she screamed in pain. …” …*";
P_HTM[5747]="*esā, bhikkhave, itthī kaliṅgassa rañño aggamahesī ahosi.**“That woman used to be the king of Kaliṅga’s chief queen.*";
P_HTM[5748]="*Sā issāpakatā sapattiṃ aṅgārakaṭāhena okiri … pe ….**She was of jealous nature, and poured a brazier of hot coals over her co-wife. …” …*";
P_HTM[5749]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5750]="*6. Asīsakasuttaṃ**A Headless Trunk*";
P_HTM[5751]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ asīsakaṃ kabandhaṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantaṃ.**“Just now, reverend, as I was descending from Vulture’s Peak Mountain I saw a headless trunk flying through the air.*";
P_HTM[5752]="*Tassa ure akkhīni ceva honti mukhañca.**Its eyes and mouth were on its chest.*";
P_HTM[5753]="*Tamenaṃ gijjhāpi kākāpi kulalāpi anupatitvā anupatitvā vitacchenti virājenti.**Vultures, crows, and hawks kept chasing it, pecking and clawing*";
P_HTM[5754]="*So sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …**as it screamed in pain. …” …*";
P_HTM[5755]="*eso, bhikkhave, satto imasmiṃyeva rājagahe hāriko nāma coraghātako ahosi … pe ….**“That being used to be an executioner called Hārika right here in Rājagaha. …”*";
P_HTM[5756]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5757]="*7. Pāpabhikkhusuttaṃ**A Bad Monk*";
P_HTM[5758]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ bhikkhuṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantaṃ.**“Just now, reverend, as I was descending from Vulture’s Peak Mountain I saw a monk flying through the air.*";
P_HTM[5759]="*Tassa saṅghāṭipi ādittā sampajjalitā sajotibhūtā, pattopi āditto sampajjalito sajotibhūto, kāyabandhanampi ādittaṃ sampajjalitaṃ sajotibhūtaṃ, kāyopi āditto sampajjalito sajotibhūto.**His outer robe, bowl, belt, and body were burning, blazing, and glowing*";
P_HTM[5760]="*So sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe …**as he screamed in pain. …” …*";
P_HTM[5761]="*eso, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kassapassa sammāsambuddhassa pāvacane pāpabhikkhu ahosi … pe ….**“That monk used to be a bad monk in the time of Buddha Kassapa’s dispensation. …”*";
P_HTM[5762]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5763]="*8. Pāpabhikkhunīsuttaṃ**A Bad Nun*";
P_HTM[5764]="*“Addasaṃ bhikkhuniṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantiṃ.**“I saw a nun flying through the air.*";
P_HTM[5765]="*Tassā saṅghāṭipi ādittā … pe …**Her outer robe was burning …” …*";
P_HTM[5766]="*pāpabhikkhunī ahosi … pe ….**“She used to be a bad nun …”*";
P_HTM[5767]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5768]="*9. Pāpasikkhamānasuttaṃ**A Bad Trainee Nun*";
P_HTM[5769]="*“Addasaṃ sikkhamānaṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantiṃ.**“I saw a trainee nun flying through the air.*";
P_HTM[5770]="*Tassā saṅghāṭipi ādittā … pe …**Her outer robe was burning …” …*";
P_HTM[5771]="*pāpasikkhamānā ahosi … pe ….**“She used to be a bad trainee nun …”*";
P_HTM[5772]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5773]="*10. Pāpasāmaṇerasuttaṃ**A Bad Novice Monk*";
P_HTM[5774]="*“Addasaṃ sāmaṇeraṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantaṃ.**“I saw a novice monk flying through the air.*";
P_HTM[5775]="*Tassa saṅghāṭipi ādittā … pe …**His outer robe was burning …” …*";
P_HTM[5776]="*pāpasāmaṇero ahosi … pe ….**“He used to be a bad novice monk …”*";
P_HTM[5777]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5778]="*11. Pāpasāmaṇerīsuttaṃ**A Bad Novice Nun*";
P_HTM[5779]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ sāmaṇeriṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantiṃ.**“Just now, reverend, as I was descending from Vulture’s Peak Mountain I saw a novice nun flying through the air.*";
P_HTM[5780]="*Tassā saṅghāṭipi ādittā sampajjalitā sajotibhūtā, pattopi āditto sampajjalito sajotibhūto, kāyabandhanampi ādittaṃ sampajjalitaṃ sajotibhūtaṃ, kāyopi āditto sampajjalito sajotibhūto.**Her outer robe, bowl, belt, and body were burning, blazing, and glowing*";
P_HTM[5781]="*Sā sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti.**as she screamed in pain.*";
P_HTM[5782]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, āvuso, etadahosi:**It occurred to me:*";
P_HTM[5783]="*‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho.**‘It’s incredible, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[5784]="*Evarūpopi nāma satto bhavissati.**That there can be such a sentient being,*";
P_HTM[5785]="*Evarūpopi nāma yakkho bhavissati.**such an entity,*";
P_HTM[5786]="*Evarūpopi nāma attabhāvapaṭilābho bhavissatī’”ti.**such an incarnation!’”*";
P_HTM[5787]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[5788]="*“cakkhubhūtā vata, bhikkhave, sāvakā viharanti;**“Mendicants, there are disciples who live full of vision and knowledge,*";
P_HTM[5789]="*ñāṇabhūtā vata, bhikkhave, sāvakā viharanti, yatra hi nāma sāvako evarūpaṃ ñassati vā dakkhati vā sakkhiṃ vā karissati.**since a disciple knows, sees, and witnesses such a thing.*";
P_HTM[5790]="*Pubbeva me sā, bhikkhave, sāmaṇerī diṭṭhā ahosi.**Formerly, I too saw that novice nun, but I did not speak of it.*";
P_HTM[5791]="*Api cāhaṃ na byākāsiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5792]="*Ahañcetaṃ byākareyyaṃ, pare ca me na saddaheyyuṃ.**For if I had spoken of it others would not have believed me,*";
P_HTM[5793]="*Ye me na saddaheyyuṃ, tesaṃ taṃ assa dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya.**which would be for their lasting harm and suffering.*";
P_HTM[5794]="*Esā, bhikkhave, sāmaṇerī kassapassa sammāsambuddhassa pāvacane pāpasāmaṇerī ahosi.**That female novice used to be a bad novice nun in the time of the Buddha Kassapa’s dispensation.*";
P_HTM[5795]="*Sā tassa kammassa vipākena bahūni vassāni bahūni vassasatāni bahūni vassasahassāni bahūni vassasatasahassāni niraye paccitvā tasseva kammassa vipākāvasesena evarūpaṃ attabhāvapaṭilābhaṃ paṭisaṃvedayatī”ti.**As a result of that deed she burned in hell for many years, many hundreds, many thousands, many hundreds of thousands of years. Now she experiences the residual result of that deed in such an incarnation.”*";
P_HTM[5796]="*Ekādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5797]="*Dutiyo vaggo.* **";
P_HTM[5798]="*Kūpe nimuggo hi so pāradāriko,* **";
P_HTM[5799]="*Gūthakhādi ahu duṭṭhabrāhmaṇo;* **";
P_HTM[5800]="*Nicchavitthi aticārinī ahu,* **";
P_HTM[5801]="*Maṅgulitthi ahu ikkhaṇitthikā;* **";
P_HTM[5802]="*Okilini sapattaṅgārokiri,* **";
P_HTM[5803]="*Sīsacchinno ahu coraghātako.* **";
P_HTM[5804]="*Bhikkhu bhikkhunī sikkhamānā,* **";
P_HTM[5805]="*Sāmaṇero atha sāmaṇerikā;* **";
P_HTM[5806]="*Kassapassa vinayasmiṃ pabbajjaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[5807]="*Pāpakammaṃ kariṃsu tāvadeti.* **";
P_HTM[5808]="*Lakkhaṇasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ.**The Linked Discourses with Lakkhaṇa are complete.*";
P_HTM[5809]="*20. Opammasaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[5810]="*1. Buddhavaggo**Similes*";
P_HTM[5811]="*1. Kūṭasuttaṃ**A Roof Peak*";
P_HTM[5812]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[5813]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[5814]="*Tatra kho bhagavā … pe … etadavoca:**There the Buddha … said:*";
P_HTM[5815]="*“seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, kūṭāgārassa yā kāci gopānasiyo sabbā tā kūṭaṅgamā kūṭasamosaraṇā kūṭasamugghātā sabbā tā samugghātaṃ gacchanti;**“Mendicants, the rafters of a bungalow all lean to the peak and meet at the peak, and when the peak is demolished they’re all demolished too.*";
P_HTM[5816]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye keci akusalā dhammā sabbe te avijjāmūlakā avijjāsamosaraṇā avijjāsamugghātā, sabbe te samugghātaṃ gacchanti.**In the same way any unskillful qualities are rooted in ignorance and meet in ignorance, and when ignorance is demolished they’re all demolished too.*";
P_HTM[5817]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[5818]="*‘appamattā viharissāmā’ti.**‘We will stay diligent.’*";
P_HTM[5819]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[5820]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5821]="*2. Nakhasikhasuttaṃ**A Fingernail*";
P_HTM[5822]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5823]="*Atha kho bhagavā parittaṃ nakhasikhāyaṃ paṃsuṃ āropetvā bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha, picking up a little bit of dirt under his fingernail, addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[5824]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**“What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[5825]="*katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ, yo cāyaṃ mayā paritto nakhasikhāyaṃ paṃsu āropito yā cāyaṃ mahāpathavī”ti?**Which is more: the little bit of dirt under my fingernail, or this great earth?”*";
P_HTM[5826]="*“Etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ yadidaṃ mahāpathavī.**“Sir, the great earth is far more.*";
P_HTM[5827]="*Appamattakoyaṃ bhagavatā paritto nakhasikhāyaṃ paṃsu āropito.**The little bit of dirt under your fingernail is tiny.*";
P_HTM[5828]="*Saṅkhampi na upeti upanidhimpi na upeti kalabhāgampi na upeti mahāpathaviṃ upanidhāya bhagavatā paritto nakhasikhāyaṃ paṃsu āropito”ti.**Compared to the great earth, it can’t be reckoned or compared, it’s not even a fraction.”*";
P_HTM[5829]="*“Evameva kho, bhikkhave, appakā te sattā ye manussesu paccājāyanti;**“In the same way the sentient beings reborn as humans are few,*";
P_HTM[5830]="*atha kho eteyeva bahutarā sattā ye aññatra manussehi paccājāyanti.**while those not reborn as humans are many.*";
P_HTM[5831]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[5832]="*‘appamattā viharissāmā’ti.**‘We will stay diligent.’*";
P_HTM[5833]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[5834]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5835]="*3. Kulasuttaṃ**Families*";
P_HTM[5836]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5837]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yāni kānici kulāni bahutthikāni appapurisāni tāni suppadhaṃsiyāni honti corehi kumbhatthenakehi;**“Mendicants, those families with many women and few men are easy prey for bandits and thieves.*";
P_HTM[5838]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, yassa kassaci bhikkhuno mettācetovimutti abhāvitā abahulīkatā so suppadhaṃsiyo hoti amanussehi.**In the same way any mendicant who has not developed and cultivated the heart’s release by love is easy prey for non-humans.*";
P_HTM[5839]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yāni kānici kulāni appitthikāni bahupurisāni tāni duppadhaṃsiyāni honti corehi kumbhatthenakehi;**Those families with few women and many men are hard prey for bandits and thieves.*";
P_HTM[5840]="*evameva kho, bhikkhave, yassa kassaci bhikkhuno mettācetovimutti bhāvitā bahulīkatā so duppadhaṃsiyo hoti amanussehi.**In the same way a mendicant who has developed and cultivated the heart’s release by love is hard prey for non-humans.*";
P_HTM[5841]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[5842]="*‘mettā no cetovimutti bhāvitā bhavissati bahulīkatā yānīkatā vatthukatā anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā’ti.**‘We will develop the heart’s release by love. We’ll cultivate it, make it our vehicle and our basis, keep it up, consolidate it, and properly implement it.’*";
P_HTM[5843]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[5844]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5845]="*4. Okkhāsuttaṃ**Rice Pots*";
P_HTM[5846]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5847]="*“Yo, bhikkhave, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ okkhāsataṃ dānaṃ dadeyya, yo majjhanhikasamayaṃ okkhāsataṃ dānaṃ dadeyya, yo sāyanhasamayaṃ okkhāsataṃ dānaṃ dadeyya, yo vā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ antamaso gadduhanamattampi mettacittaṃ bhāveyya, yo vā majjhanhikasamayaṃ antamaso gadduhanamattampi mettacittaṃ bhāveyya, yo vā sāyanhasamayaṃ antamaso gadduhanamattampi mettacittaṃ bhāveyya, idaṃ tato mahapphalataraṃ.**“Mendicants, suppose one person was to give a gift of a hundred pots of rice in the morning, at midday, and in the evening. And someone else was to develop a heart of love, even just as long as it takes to pull a cow’s udder. The latter would be more fruitful.*";
P_HTM[5848]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[5849]="*‘mettā no cetovimutti bhāvitā bhavissati bahulīkatā yānīkatā vatthukatā anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā’ti.**‘We will develop the heart’s release by love. We’ll cultivate it, make it our vehicle and our basis, keep it up, consolidate it, and properly implement it.’*";
P_HTM[5850]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[5851]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5852]="*5. Sattisuttaṃ**A Spear*";
P_HTM[5853]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5854]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, satti tiṇhaphalā.**“Mendicants, suppose there was a sharp-pointed spear.*";
P_HTM[5855]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya:**And a man came along and thought,*";
P_HTM[5856]="*‘ahaṃ imaṃ sattiṃ tiṇhaphalaṃ pāṇinā vā muṭṭhinā vā paṭileṇissāmi paṭikoṭṭissāmi paṭivaṭṭessāmī’ti.**‘With my hand or fist I’ll fold this sharp spear over, bend it back, and twist it around!’*";
P_HTM[5857]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[5858]="*bhabbo nu kho so puriso amuṃ sattiṃ tiṇhaphalaṃ pāṇinā vā muṭṭhinā vā paṭileṇetuṃ paṭikoṭṭetuṃ paṭivaṭṭetun”ti?**Is that man capable of doing so?”*";
P_HTM[5859]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.*";
P_HTM[5860]="*“Taṃ kissa hetu”?**Why not?*";
P_HTM[5861]="*“Asu hi, bhante, satti tiṇhaphalā na sukarā pāṇinā vā muṭṭhinā vā paṭileṇetuṃ paṭikoṭṭetuṃ paṭivaṭṭetuṃ.**Because it’s not easy to fold that sharp spear over, bend it back, and twist it around with the hand or fist.*";
P_HTM[5862]="*Yāvadeva ca pana so puriso kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī assā”ti.**That man will eventually get weary and frustrated.”*";
P_HTM[5863]="*“Evameva kho, bhikkhave, yassa kassaci bhikkhuno mettācetovimutti bhāvitā bahulīkatā yānīkatā vatthukatā anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā, tassa ce amanusso cittaṃ khipitabbaṃ maññeyya;**“In the same way, suppose a mendicant has developed the heart’s release by love, has cultivated it, made it a vehicle and a basis, kept it up, consolidated it, and properly implemented it. Should any non-human think to overthrow their mind,*";
P_HTM[5864]="*atha kho sveva amanusso kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī assa.**they’ll eventually get weary and frustrated.*";
P_HTM[5865]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[5866]="*‘mettā no cetovimutti bhāvitā bhavissati bahulīkatā yānīkatā vatthukatā anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā’ti.**‘We will develop the heart’s release by love. We’ll cultivate it, make it our vehicle and our basis, keep it up, consolidate it, and properly implement it.’*";
P_HTM[5867]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[5868]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5869]="*6. Dhanuggahasuttaṃ**The Archers*";
P_HTM[5870]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5871]="*“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, cattāro daḷhadhammā dhanuggahā susikkhitā katahatthā katūpāsanā catuddisā ṭhitā assu.**“Mendicants, suppose there were four well-trained expert archers with strong bows standing in the four directions.*";
P_HTM[5872]="*Atha puriso āgaccheyya:**And a man came along and thought,*";
P_HTM[5873]="*‘ahaṃ imesaṃ catunnaṃ daḷhadhammānaṃ dhanuggahānaṃ susikkhitānaṃ katahatthānaṃ katūpāsanānaṃ catuddisā kaṇḍe khitte appatiṭṭhite pathaviyaṃ gahetvā āharissāmī’ti.**‘When these four well-trained expert archers shoot arrows in four directions, I’ll catch them before they reach the ground, and then I’ll bring them back.’*";
P_HTM[5874]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[5875]="*‘javano puriso paramena javena samannāgato’ti alaṃvacanāyā”ti?**Are they qualified to be called ‘a speedster, with ultimate speed’?”*";
P_HTM[5876]="*“Ekassa cepi, bhante, daḷhadhammassa dhanuggahassa susikkhitassa katahatthassa katūpāsanassa kaṇḍaṃ khittaṃ appatiṭṭhitaṃ pathaviyaṃ gahetvā āhareyya:**“If he could catch an arrow shot by just one well-trained expert archer before it reaches the ground and bring it back,*";
P_HTM[5877]="*‘javano puriso paramena javena samannāgato’ti alaṃvacanāya, ko pana vādo catunnaṃ daḷhadhammānaṃ dhanuggahānaṃ susikkhitānaṃ katahatthānaṃ katūpāsanānan”ti?**he’d be qualified to be called ‘a speedster, with ultimate speed’. How much more so arrows shot by four archers!”*";
P_HTM[5878]="*“Yathā ca, bhikkhave, tassa purisassa javo, yathā ca candimasūriyānaṃ javo, tato sīghataro.**“As fast as that man is, the sun and moon are faster.*";
P_HTM[5879]="*Yathā ca, bhikkhave, tassa purisassa javo yathā ca candimasūriyānaṃ javo yathā ca yā devatā candimasūriyānaṃ purato dhāvanti tāsaṃ devatānaṃ javo, () tato sīghataraṃ āyusaṅkhārā khīyanti.**As fast as that man is, as fast as the sun and moon are, and as fast as the deities that run before the sun and moon are, the waning of the life forces is faster.*";
P_HTM[5880]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[5881]="*‘appamattā viharissāmā’ti.**‘We will stay diligent.’*";
P_HTM[5882]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[5883]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5884]="*7. Āṇisuttaṃ**The Drum Peg*";
P_HTM[5885]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5886]="*“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, dasārahānaṃ ānako nāma mudiṅgo ahosi.**“Once upon a time, mendicants, the Dasārahas had a clay drum called the Commander.*";
P_HTM[5887]="*Tassa dasārahā ānake ghaṭite aññaṃ āṇiṃ odahiṃsu.**Each time the Commander split they repaired it by inserting another peg.*";
P_HTM[5888]="*Ahu kho so, bhikkhave, samayo yaṃ ānakassa mudiṅgassa porāṇaṃ pokkharaphalakaṃ antaradhāyi.**But there came a time when the clay drum Commander’s original wooden rim disappeared*";
P_HTM[5889]="*Āṇisaṅghāṭova avasissi.**and only a mass of pegs remained.*";
P_HTM[5890]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhavissanti bhikkhū anāgatamaddhānaṃ, ye te suttantā tathāgatabhāsitā gambhīrā gambhīratthā lokuttarā suññatappaṭisaṃyuttā, tesu bhaññamānesu na sussūsissanti na sotaṃ odahissanti na aññā cittaṃ upaṭṭhāpessanti na ca te dhamme uggahetabbaṃ pariyāpuṇitabbaṃ maññissanti.**In the same way, in a future time there will be mendicants who won’t want to listen when discourses spoken by the Realized One—deep, profound, transcendent, dealing with emptiness—are being recited. They won’t pay attention or apply their minds to understand them, nor will they think those teachings are worth learning and memorizing.*";
P_HTM[5891]="*Ye pana te suttantā kavikatā kāveyyā cittakkharā cittabyañjanā bāhirakā sāvakabhāsitā, tesu bhaññamānesu sussūsissanti, sotaṃ odahissanti, aññā cittaṃ upaṭṭhāpessanti, te ca dhamme uggahetabbaṃ pariyāpuṇitabbaṃ maññissanti.**But when discourses composed by poets—poetry, with fancy words and phrases, composed by outsiders or spoken by disciples—are being recited they will want to listen. They’ll pay attention and apply their minds to understand them, and they’ll think those teachings are worth learning and memorizing.*";
P_HTM[5892]="*Evametesaṃ, bhikkhave, suttantānaṃ tathāgatabhāsitānaṃ gambhīrānaṃ gambhīratthānaṃ lokuttarānaṃ suññatappaṭisaṃyuttānaṃ antaradhānaṃ bhavissati.**And that is how the discourses spoken by the Realized One—deep, profound, transcendent, dealing with emptiness—will disappear.*";
P_HTM[5893]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[5894]="*‘ye te suttantā tathāgatabhāsitā gambhīrā gambhīratthā lokuttarā suññatappaṭisaṃyuttā, tesu bhaññamānesu sussūsissāma, sotaṃ odahissāma, aññā cittaṃ upaṭṭhāpessāma, te ca dhamme uggahetabbaṃ pariyāpuṇitabbaṃ maññissāmā’ti.**‘When discourses spoken by the Realized One—deep, profound, transcendent, dealing with emptiness—are being recited we will want to listen. We will pay attention and apply our minds to understand them, and we will think those teachings are worth learning and memorizing.’*";
P_HTM[5895]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[5896]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5897]="*8. Kaliṅgarasuttaṃ**Wood Blocks*";
P_HTM[5898]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[5899]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof.*";
P_HTM[5900]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[5901]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[5902]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[5903]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[5904]="*“Kaliṅgarūpadhānā, bhikkhave, etarahi licchavī viharanti appamattā ātāpino upāsanasmiṃ.**“Mendicants, these days the Licchavis live using wood blocks as pillows, and they exercise diligently and keenly.*";
P_HTM[5905]="*Tesaṃ rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto na labhati otāraṃ na labhati ārammaṇaṃ.**King Ajātasattu Vedehiputta of Magadha finds no vulnerability, he’s got no foothold.*";
P_HTM[5906]="*Bhavissanti, bhikkhave, anāgatamaddhānaṃ licchavī sukhumālā mudutalunahatthapādā**But in the future the Licchavis will become delicate, with soft and tender hands and feet.*";
P_HTM[5907]="*te mudukāsu seyyāsu tūlabibbohanāsu yāvasūriyuggamanā seyyaṃ kappissanti.**They’ll sleep on soft beds with down pillows until the sun comes up.*";
P_HTM[5908]="*Tesaṃ rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto lacchati otāraṃ lacchati ārammaṇaṃ.**King Ajātasattu Vedehiputta of Magadha will find a vulnerability, he’ll get his foothold.*";
P_HTM[5909]="*Kaliṅgarūpadhānā, bhikkhave, etarahi bhikkhū viharanti appamattā ātāpino padhānasmiṃ.**These days the mendicants live using wood blocks as pillows, and they meditate diligently and keenly.*";
P_HTM[5910]="*Tesaṃ māro pāpimā na labhati otāraṃ na labhati ārammaṇaṃ.**Māra the Wicked finds no vulnerability, he's got no foothold.*";
P_HTM[5911]="*Bhavissanti, bhikkhave, anāgatamaddhānaṃ bhikkhū sukhumā mudutalunahatthapādā.**But in the future the mendicants will become delicate, with soft and tender hands and feet.*";
P_HTM[5912]="*Te mudukāsu seyyāsu tūlabibbohanāsu yāvasūriyuggamanā seyyaṃ kappissanti.**They’ll sleep on soft beds with down pillows until the sun comes up.*";
P_HTM[5913]="*Tesaṃ māro pāpimā lacchati otāraṃ lacchati ārammaṇaṃ.**Māra the Wicked will find a vulnerability and will get a foothold.*";
P_HTM[5914]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[5915]="*‘kaliṅgarūpadhānā viharissāma appamattā ātāpino padhānasmin’ti.**‘We will live using wood blocks as pillows, and we will meditate diligently and keenly.’*";
P_HTM[5916]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[5917]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5918]="*9. Nāgasuttaṃ**A Bull Elephant*";
P_HTM[5919]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[5920]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[5921]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro navo bhikkhu ativelaṃ kulāni upasaṅkamati.**Now at that time a certain junior mendicant went to visit families too often.*";
P_HTM[5922]="*Tamenaṃ bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu:**The mendicants said to him,*";
P_HTM[5923]="*“māyasmā ativelaṃ kulāni upasaṅkamī”ti.**“Venerable, don’t go to visit families too often.”*";
P_HTM[5924]="*So bhikkhu bhikkhūhi vuccamāno evamāha:**But that mendicant, when spoken to by the mendicants, said this,*";
P_HTM[5925]="*“ime hi nāma therā bhikkhū kulāni upasaṅkamitabbaṃ maññissanti, kimaṅgaṃ panāhan”ti?**“But these senior mendicants think they can go to visit families, so why can’t I?”*";
P_HTM[5926]="*Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**And then several mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened. The Buddha said:*";
P_HTM[5927]="*“idha, bhante, aññataro navo bhikkhu ativelaṃ kulāni upasaṅkamati.* **";
P_HTM[5928]="*Tamenaṃ bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu:* **";
P_HTM[5929]="*‘māyasmā ativelaṃ kulāni upasaṅkamī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5930]="*So bhikkhu bhikkhūhi vuccamāno evamāha:* **";
P_HTM[5931]="*‘ime hi nāma therā bhikkhū kulāni upasaṅkamitabbaṃ maññissanti, kimaṅgaṃ panāhan’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5932]="*“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, araññāyatane mahāsarasī.**“Once upon a time, mendicants, there was a great lake in the jungle,*";
P_HTM[5933]="*Taṃ nāgā upanissāya viharanti.**with bull elephants living nearby.*";
P_HTM[5934]="*Te taṃ sarasiṃ ogāhetvā soṇḍāya bhisamuḷālaṃ abbuhetvā suvikkhālitaṃ vikkhāletvā akaddamaṃ saṅkhāditvā ajjhoharanti.**They’d plunge into the lake and pull up lotus bulbs with their trunks. They’d wash them thoroughly until they were free of mud before chewing and swallowing them.*";
P_HTM[5935]="*Tesaṃ taṃ vaṇṇāya ceva hoti balāya ca, na ca tatonidānaṃ maraṇaṃ vā nigacchanti maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhaṃ.**That was good for their appearance and health, and wouldn’t result in death or deadly pain.*";
P_HTM[5936]="*Tesaṃyeva kho pana, bhikkhave, mahānāgānaṃ anusikkhamānā taruṇā bhiṅkacchāpā taṃ sarasiṃ ogāhetvā soṇḍāya bhisamuḷālaṃ abbuhetvā na suvikkhālitaṃ vikkhāletvā sakaddamaṃ asaṅkhāditvā ajjhoharanti.**The young cubs, following the example of the great bull elephants, plunged into the lake and pulled up lotus bulbs with their trunks. But they didn’t wash them thoroughly, and while they were still muddy they chewed and swallowed them.*";
P_HTM[5937]="*Tesaṃ taṃ neva vaṇṇāya hoti na balāya.**That was not good for their appearance and health, and resulted in death or deadly pain.*";
P_HTM[5938]="*Tatonidānaṃ maraṇaṃ vā nigacchanti maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5939]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, idha therā bhikkhū pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisanti.**In the same way, there are senior mendicants who robe up in the morning and, taking their bowl and robe, enter the town or village for alms.*";
P_HTM[5940]="*Te tattha dhammaṃ bhāsanti.**There they speak on the teachings,*";
P_HTM[5941]="*Tesaṃ gihī pasannākāraṃ karonti.**and lay people demonstrate their confidence in them.*";
P_HTM[5942]="*Te taṃ lābhaṃ agadhitā amucchitā anajjhopannā ādīnavadassāvino nissaraṇapaññā paribhuñjanti.**And when they get things, they use them untied, uninfatuated, unattached, seeing the drawbacks, and understanding the escape.*";
P_HTM[5943]="*Tesaṃ taṃ vaṇṇāya ceva hoti balāya ca, na ca tatonidānaṃ maraṇaṃ vā nigacchanti maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhaṃ.**That’s good for their appearance and health, and doesn’t result in death or deadly pain.*";
P_HTM[5944]="*Tesaṃyeva kho pana, bhikkhave, therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ anusikkhamānā navā bhikkhū pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisanti.**Junior mendicants, following the example of the senior mendicants, robe up in the morning and, taking their bowl and robe, enter the town or village for alms.*";
P_HTM[5945]="*Te tattha dhammaṃ bhāsanti.**There they speak on the teachings,*";
P_HTM[5946]="*Tesaṃ gihī pasannākāraṃ karonti.**and lay people demonstrate their confidence in them.*";
P_HTM[5947]="*Te taṃ lābhaṃ gadhitā mucchitā ajjhopannā anādīnavadassāvino anissaraṇapaññā paribhuñjanti.**But when they get things, they use them tied, infatuated, attached, blind to the drawbacks, not understanding the escape.*";
P_HTM[5948]="*Tesaṃ taṃ neva vaṇṇāya hoti na balāya, te tatonidānaṃ maraṇaṃ vā nigacchanti maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhaṃ.**That’s not good for their appearance and health, and results in death or deadly pain.*";
P_HTM[5949]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[5950]="*‘agadhitā amucchitā anajjhopannā ādīnavadassāvino nissaraṇapaññā taṃ lābhaṃ paribhuñjissāmā’ti.**‘When we get things, we will use them untied, uninfatuated, unattached, seeing the drawbacks, and understanding the escape.’*";
P_HTM[5951]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[5952]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5953]="*10. Biḷārasuttaṃ**A Cat*";
P_HTM[5954]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5955]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu ativelaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjati.**Now at that time a certain junior mendicant socialized with families too often.*";
P_HTM[5956]="*Tamenaṃ bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu:**The mendicants said to him,*";
P_HTM[5957]="*“māyasmā ativelaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjī”ti.**“Venerable, don’t socialize with families too often.”*";
P_HTM[5958]="*So bhikkhu bhikkhūhi vuccamāno na viramati.**But that mendicant, when spoken to by the mendicants, did not stop.*";
P_HTM[5959]="*Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**And then several mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened. The Buddha said:*";
P_HTM[5960]="*“idha, bhante, aññataro bhikkhu ativelaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjati.* **";
P_HTM[5961]="*Tamenaṃ bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu:* **";
P_HTM[5962]="*‘māyasmā ativelaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5963]="*So bhikkhu bhikkhūhi vuccamāno na viramatī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5964]="*“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, biḷāro sandhisamalasaṅkaṭīre ṭhito ahosi mudumūsiṃ maggayamāno:**“Once upon a time, mendicants, a cat was standing by an alley or a drain or a dustbin hunting a little mouse, thinking,*";
P_HTM[5965]="*‘yadāyaṃ mudumūsi gocarāya pakkamissati, tattheva naṃ gahetvā khādissāmī’ti.**‘When that little mouse comes out to feed, I’ll catch it right there and eat it!’*";
P_HTM[5966]="*Atha kho so, bhikkhave, mudumūsi gocarāya pakkāmi.**And then that little mouse came out to feed.*";
P_HTM[5967]="*Tamenaṃ biḷāro gahetvā sahasā saṅkhāditvā ajjhohari.**The cat caught it and hastily swallowed it without chewing.*";
P_HTM[5968]="*Tassa so mudumūsi antampi khādi, antaguṇampi khādi.**But that little mouse ate its intestines and mesentery,*";
P_HTM[5969]="*So tatonidānaṃ maraṇampi nigacchi maraṇamattampi dukkhaṃ.**resulting in death and deadly pain.*";
P_HTM[5970]="*Evameva kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhikkhu pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisati arakkhiteneva kāyena arakkhitāya vācāya arakkhitena cittena, anupaṭṭhitāya satiyā, asaṃvutehi indriyehi.**In the same way, take a certain monk who robes up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, enters the village or town for alms without guarding body, speech, and mind, without establishing mindfulness, and without restraining the sense faculties.*";
P_HTM[5971]="*So tattha passati mātugāmaṃ dunnivatthaṃ vā duppārutaṃ vā.**There he sees a female scantily clad, with revealing clothes.*";
P_HTM[5972]="*Tassa mātugāmaṃ disvā dunnivatthaṃ vā duppārutaṃ vā rāgo cittaṃ anuddhaṃseti.**Lust infects his mind,*";
P_HTM[5973]="*So rāgānuddhaṃsena cittena maraṇaṃ vā nigacchati maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhaṃ.**resulting in death or deadly pain.*";
P_HTM[5974]="*Maraṇañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyassa vinaye yo sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattati.**For it is death in the training of the noble one to reject the training and return to a lesser life.*";
P_HTM[5975]="*Maraṇamattañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ yadidaṃ aññataraṃ saṅkiliṭṭhaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati.**And it is deadly pain to commit one of the corrupt offenses*";
P_HTM[5976]="*Yathārūpāya āpattiyā vuṭṭhānaṃ paññāyati.**for which rehabilitation is possible.*";
P_HTM[5977]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[5978]="*‘rakkhiteneva kāyena rakkhitāya vācāya rakkhitena cittena, upaṭṭhitāya satiyā, saṃvutehi indriyehi gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisissāmā’ti.**‘We will enter the village or town for alms guarding body, speech, and mind, establishing mindfulness, and restraining the sense faculties.’*";
P_HTM[5979]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[5980]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5981]="*11. Siṅgālasuttaṃ**A Jackal*";
P_HTM[5982]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5983]="*“Assuttha no tumhe, bhikkhave, rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ jarasiṅgālassa vassamānassā”ti?**“Mendicants, did you hear an old jackal howling at the crack of dawn?”*";
P_HTM[5984]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5985]="*“Eso kho, bhikkhave, jarasiṅgālo ukkaṇḍakena nāma rogajātena phuṭṭho.**“That old jackal has the disease called mange.*";
P_HTM[5986]="*So yena yena icchati tena tena gacchati;**Yet it still goes where it wants,*";
P_HTM[5987]="*yattha yattha icchati tattha tattha tiṭṭhati;**stands where it wants,*";
P_HTM[5988]="*yattha yattha icchati tattha tattha nisīdati;**sits where it wants,*";
P_HTM[5989]="*yattha yattha icchati tattha tattha nipajjati;**and lies down where it wants.*";
P_HTM[5990]="*sītakopi naṃ vāto upavāyati.**And the cool breeze still blows on it.*";
P_HTM[5991]="*Sādhu khvassa, bhikkhave, yaṃ idhekacco sakyaputtiyapaṭiñño evarūpampi attabhāvapaṭilābhaṃ paṭisaṃvediyetha.**A certain person here who claims to be a follower of the Sakyan son would be lucky to experience even such an incarnation.*";
P_HTM[5992]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[5993]="*‘appamattā viharissāmā’ti.**‘We will stay diligent.’*";
P_HTM[5994]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[5995]="*Ekādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[5996]="*12. Dutiyasiṅgālasuttaṃ**A Jackal (2nd)*";
P_HTM[5997]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[5998]="*“Assuttha no tumhe, bhikkhave, rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ jarasiṅgālassa vassamānassā”ti?**“Mendicants, did you hear an old jackal howling at the crack of dawn?”*";
P_HTM[5999]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6000]="*“Siyā kho, bhikkhave, tasmiṃ jarasiṅgāle yā kāci kataññutā kataveditā, na tveva idhekacce sakyaputtiyapaṭiññe siyā yā kāci kataññutā kataveditā.**“There might be some gratitude and thankfulness in that old jackal, but there is none in a certain person here who claims to be a follower of the Sakyan son.*";
P_HTM[6001]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[6002]="*‘kataññuno bhavissāma katavedino;**‘We will be grateful and thankful.*";
P_HTM[6003]="*na ca no amhesu appakampi kataṃ nassissatī’ti.**We won’t forget even a small thing done for us.’*";
P_HTM[6004]="*Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[6005]="*Dvādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6006]="*Opammavaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[6007]="*Kūṭaṃ nakhasikhaṃ kulaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[6008]="*okkhā satti dhanuggaho;* **";
P_HTM[6009]="*Āṇi kaliṅgaro nāgo,* **";
P_HTM[6010]="*biḷāro dve siṅgālakāti.* **";
P_HTM[6011]="*Opammasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ.**The Linked Discourses with similes are complete.*";
P_HTM[6012]="*21. Bhikkhusaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[6013]="*1. Buddhavaggo**Monks*";
P_HTM[6014]="*1. Kolitasuttaṃ**With Kolita*";
P_HTM[6015]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[6016]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[6017]="*Tatra kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhikkhū āmantesi:**There Venerable Mahāmoggallāna addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[6018]="*“āvuso bhikkhave”ti.**“Reverends, mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[6019]="*“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa paccassosuṃ.**“Reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[6020]="*Āyasmā mahāmoggallāno etadavoca:**Venerable Mahāmoggallāna said this:*";
P_HTM[6021]="*“idha mayhaṃ, āvuso, rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi:**“Just now, reverends, as I was in private retreat this thought came to mind:*";
P_HTM[6022]="*‘ariyo tuṇhībhāvo, ariyo tuṇhībhāvoti vuccati.**‘They speak of this thing called “noble silence”.*";
P_HTM[6023]="*Katamo nu kho ariyo tuṇhībhāvo’ti?**What then is this noble silence?’*";
P_HTM[6024]="*Tassa mayhaṃ āvuso, etadahosi:**It occurred to me:*";
P_HTM[6025]="*‘idha bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati.**‘As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[6026]="*Ayaṃ vuccati ariyo tuṇhībhāvo’ti.**This is called noble silence.’*";
P_HTM[6027]="*So khvāhaṃ, āvuso, vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihariṃ.**And so, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected were stilled, I was entering and remaining in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.*";
P_HTM[6028]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, āvuso, iminā vihārena viharato vitakkasahagatā saññā manasikārā samudācaranti.**While I was in that meditation, perceptions and attentions accompanied by placing the mind beset me.*";
P_HTM[6029]="*Atha kho maṃ, āvuso, bhagavā iddhiyā upasaṅkamitvā etadavoca:**Then the Buddha came up to me with his psychic power and said,*";
P_HTM[6030]="*‘moggallāna moggallāna, mā, brāhmaṇa, ariyaṃ tuṇhībhāvaṃ pamādo, ariye tuṇhībhāve cittaṃ saṇṭhapehi, ariye tuṇhībhāve cittaṃ ekodibhāvaṃ karohi, ariye tuṇhībhāve cittaṃ samādahā’ti.**‘Moggallāna, Moggallāna! Don’t neglect noble silence, brahmin! Settle your mind in noble silence; unify your mind and bring it to immersion in noble silence.’*";
P_HTM[6031]="*So khvāhaṃ, āvuso, aparena samayena vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharāmi.**And so, after some time, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected were stilled, I entered and remained in the second absorption …*";
P_HTM[6032]="*Yañhi taṃ, āvuso, sammā vadamāno vadeyya:**So if anyone should be rightly called*";
P_HTM[6033]="*‘satthārā anuggahito sāvako mahābhiññataṃ patto’ti, mamaṃ taṃ sammā vadamāno vadeyya:**a disciple who attained to great direct knowledge with help from the Teacher, it’s me.”*";
P_HTM[6034]="*‘satthārā anuggahito sāvako mahābhiññataṃ patto’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6035]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6036]="*2. Upatissasuttaṃ**With Upatissa*";
P_HTM[6037]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6038]="*Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:**There Sāriputta addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[6039]="*“āvuso bhikkhave”ti.**“Reverends, mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[6040]="*“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ.**“Reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[6041]="*Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca:**Sāriputta said this:*";
P_HTM[6042]="*“Idha mayhaṃ, āvuso, rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi:**“Just now, reverends, as I was in private retreat this thought came to mind:*";
P_HTM[6043]="*‘atthi nu kho taṃ kiñci lokasmiṃ yassa me vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā uppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā’ti?**‘Is there anything in the world whose changing and perishing would give rise to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress in me?’*";
P_HTM[6044]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, āvuso, etadahosi:**It occurred to me:*";
P_HTM[6045]="*‘natthi kho taṃ kiñci lokasmiṃ yassa me vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā uppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā’”ti.**‘There is nothing in the world whose changing and perishing would give rise to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress in me.’”*";
P_HTM[6046]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, Venerable Ānanda said to him,*";
P_HTM[6047]="*“satthupi kho te, āvuso sāriputta, vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā nuppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti?**“Even if the Teacher were to decay and perish? Wouldn’t that give rise to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress in you?”*";
P_HTM[6048]="*“Satthupi kho me, āvuso, vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā nuppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā, api ca me evamassa:**“Even if the Teacher were to decay and perish, that wouldn’t give rise to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress in me. Still, I would think:*";
P_HTM[6049]="*‘mahesakkho vata bho satthā antarahito mahiddhiko mahānubhāvo.**‘Alas, the illustrious Teacher, so mighty and powerful, has vanished!*";
P_HTM[6050]="*Sace hi bhagavā ciraṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ tiṭṭheyya tadassa bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānan’ti.**If the Buddha was to remain for a long time, that would be for the welfare and happiness of the people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans.’”*";
P_HTM[6051]="*Tathā hi panāyasmato sāriputtassa dīgharattaṃ ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā susamūhatā.**“That must be because Venerable Sāriputta has long ago totally eradicated ego, possessiveness, and the underlying tendency to conceit.*";
P_HTM[6052]="*Tasmā āyasmato sāriputtassa satthupi vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā nuppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti.**So even if the Teacher were to decay and perish, it wouldn’t give rise to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress in him.”*";
P_HTM[6053]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6054]="*3. Ghaṭasuttaṃ**A Mound of Salt*";
P_HTM[6055]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[6056]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[6057]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā ca sāriputto āyasmā ca mahāmoggallāno rājagahe viharanti veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe ekavihāre.**At that time Venerables Sāriputta and Moggallāna were staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[6058]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yenāyasmā mahāmoggallāno tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā mahāmoggallānena saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Sāriputta came out of retreat, went to Venerable Moggallāna, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[6059]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, Sāriputta sat down to one side, and said to Mahāmoggallāna:*";
P_HTM[6060]="*“Vippasannāni kho te, āvuso moggallāna, indriyāni;**“Reverend Moggallāna, your faculties are so very clear, and your complexion is pure and bright.*";
P_HTM[6061]="*parisuddho mukhavaṇṇo pariyodāto santena nūnāyasmā mahāmoggallāno ajja vihārena vihāsī”ti.**Have you spent the day in a peaceful meditation?”*";
P_HTM[6062]="*“Oḷārikena khvāhaṃ, āvuso, ajja vihārena vihāsiṃ.**“Reverend, I’ve spent the day in a coarse meditation.*";
P_HTM[6063]="*Api ca me ahosi dhammī kathā”ti.**But I have had some Dhamma talk.”*";
P_HTM[6064]="*“Kena saddhiṃ panāyasmato mahāmoggallānassa ahosi dhammī kathā”ti?**“Who did you have a Dhamma talk with?”*";
P_HTM[6065]="*“Bhagavatā kho me, āvuso, saddhiṃ ahosi dhammī kathā”ti.**“With the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[6066]="*“Dūre kho, āvuso, bhagavā etarahi sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**“But Reverend, the Buddha is far away. He’s staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[6067]="*Kiṃ nu kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhagavantaṃ iddhiyā upasaṅkami;**Did you go to him with your psychic power,*";
P_HTM[6068]="*udāhu bhagavā āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ iddhiyā upasaṅkamī”ti?**or did he come to you?”*";
P_HTM[6069]="*“Na khvāhaṃ, āvuso, bhagavantaṃ iddhiyā upasaṅkamiṃ;**“No reverend, I didn’t go to him with my psychic power,*";
P_HTM[6070]="*napi maṃ bhagavā iddhiyā upasaṅkami.**nor did he come to me.*";
P_HTM[6071]="*Api ca me yāvatā bhagavā ettāvatā dibbacakkhu visujjhi dibbā ca sotadhātu.**Rather, the Buddha cleared his clairvoyance and clairaudience towards me,*";
P_HTM[6072]="*Bhagavatopi yāvatāhaṃ ettāvatā dibbacakkhu visujjhi dibbā ca sotadhātū”ti.**and I cleared my clairvoyance and clairaudience towards him.”*";
P_HTM[6073]="*“Yathākathaṃ panāyasmato mahāmoggallānassa bhagavatā saddhiṃ ahosi dhammī kathā”ti?**“But what manner of Dhamma talk did you have together?”*";
P_HTM[6074]="*“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, bhagavantaṃ etadavocaṃ:**“Well, reverend, I said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[6075]="*‘āraddhavīriyo āraddhavīriyoti, bhante, vuccati.**‘Sir, they speak of one who is energetic.*";
P_HTM[6076]="*Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, āraddhavīriyo hotī’ti?**How is an energetic person defined?’*";
P_HTM[6077]="*Evaṃ vutte, maṃ, āvuso, bhagavā etadavoca:**When I said this, the Buddha said,*";
P_HTM[6078]="*‘idha, moggallāna, bhikkhu āraddhavīriyo viharati—**‘Moggallāna, it’s when a mendicant lives with energy roused up:*";
P_HTM[6079]="*kāmaṃ taco ca nhāru ca aṭṭhi ca avasissatu, sarīre upassussatu maṃsalohitaṃ, yaṃ taṃ purisathāmena purisavīriyena purisaparakkamena pattabbaṃ na taṃ apāpuṇitvā vīriyassa saṇṭhānaṃ bhavissatīti.**“Gladly, let only skin, sinews, and bones remain! Let the flesh and blood waste away in my body! I will not stop trying until I have achieved what is possible by manly strength, energy, and vigor.”*";
P_HTM[6080]="*Evaṃ kho, moggallāna, āraddhavīriyo hotī’ti.**That’s how a person is energetic.’*";
P_HTM[6081]="*Evaṃ kho me, āvuso, bhagavatā saddhiṃ ahosi dhammī kathā”ti.**That’s the Dhamma talk I had together with the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[6082]="*“Seyyathāpi, āvuso, himavato pabbatarājassa parittā pāsāṇasakkharā yāvadeva upanikkhepanamattāya;**“Reverend, next to Venerable Mahāmoggallāna I’m like a few pieces of gravel next to the Himalayas, the king of mountains.*";
P_HTM[6083]="*evameva kho mayaṃ āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa yāvadeva upanikkhepanamattāya.* **";
P_HTM[6084]="*Āyasmā hi mahāmoggallāno mahiddhiko mahānubhāvo ākaṅkhamāno kappaṃ tiṭṭheyyā”ti.**Venerable Mahāmoggallāna is so mighty and powerful he could, if he wished, live on for the eon.”*";
P_HTM[6085]="*“Seyyathāpi, āvuso, mahatiyā loṇaghaṭāya parittā loṇasakkharāya yāvadeva upanikkhepanamattāya;**“Reverend, next to Venerable Sāriputta I’m like a few grains of salt next to a mound of salt.*";
P_HTM[6086]="*evameva kho mayaṃ āyasmato sāriputtassa yāvadeva upanikkhepanamattāya.* **";
P_HTM[6087]="*Āyasmā hi sāriputto bhagavatā anekapariyāyena thomito vaṇṇito pasattho:**Venerable Sāriputta has been commended, complimented, and praised by the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[6088]="*‘Sāriputtova paññāya,**‘In wisdom,*";
P_HTM[6089]="*sīlena upasamena ca;**ethics, and peace,*";
P_HTM[6090]="*Yopi pāraṅgato bhikkhu,**any mendicant who has crossed over*";
P_HTM[6091]="*etāvaparamo siyā’”ti.**can at best equal Sāriputta.’”*";
P_HTM[6092]="*Itiha te ubho mahānāgā aññamaññassa subhāsitaṃ sulapitaṃ samanumodiṃsūti.**And so these two spiritual giants agreed with each others’ fine words.*";
P_HTM[6093]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6094]="*4. Navasuttaṃ**A Junior Mendicant*";
P_HTM[6095]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6096]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro navo bhikkhu pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto vihāraṃ pavisitvā appossukko tuṇhībhūto saṅkasāyati, na bhikkhūnaṃ veyyāvaccaṃ karoti cīvarakārasamaye.**Now at that time a certain junior monk, after his meal, on his return from alms-round, entered his dwelling, where he adhered to passivity and silence. And he didn’t help the mendicants out when it was time to sew robes.*";
P_HTM[6097]="*Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then several mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened.*";
P_HTM[6098]="*“idha, bhante, aññataro navo bhikkhu pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto vihāraṃ pavisitvā appossukko tuṇhībhūto saṅkasāyati, na bhikkhūnaṃ veyyāvaccaṃ karoti cīvarakārasamaye”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6099]="*Atha kho bhagavā aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ āmantesi:**So the Buddha said to a certain monk,*";
P_HTM[6100]="*“ehi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, mama vacanena taṃ bhikkhuṃ āmantehi ‘satthā taṃ, āvuso, āmantetī’”ti.**“Please, monk, in my name tell that monk that the Teacher summons him.”*";
P_HTM[6101]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu bhagavato paṭissutvā yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca:**“Yes, sir,” that monk replied. He went to that monk and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6102]="*“satthā taṃ, āvuso, āmantetī”ti.**“Reverend, the teacher summons you.”*";
P_HTM[6103]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho so bhikkhu tassa bhikkhuno paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho taṃ bhikkhuṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**“Yes, reverend,” that monk replied. He went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[6104]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto vihāraṃ pavisitvā appossukko tuṇhībhūto saṅkasāyasi, na bhikkhūnaṃ veyyāvaccaṃ karosi cīvarakārasamaye”ti?**“Is it really true, monk, that after your meal, on your return from alms-round, you entered your dwelling, where you adhered to passivity and silence, and you didn’t help the mendicants out when it was time to sew robes?”*";
P_HTM[6105]="*“Ahampi kho, bhante, sakaṃ kiccaṃ karomī”ti.**“Sir, I am doing my own work.”*";
P_HTM[6106]="*Atha kho bhagavā tassa bhikkhuno cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya bhikkhū āmantesi:**Then the Buddha, knowing what that monk was thinking, addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[6107]="*“mā kho tumhe, bhikkhave, etassa bhikkhuno ujjhāyittha.**“Mendicants, don’t complain about this monk.*";
P_HTM[6108]="*Eso kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, yassa catthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharatī”ti.**This monk gets the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that belong to the higher mind—when he wants, without trouble or difficulty. He has realized the supreme culmination of the spiritual path in this very life, and lives having achieved with his own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.”*";
P_HTM[6109]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[6110]="*Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:**Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:*";
P_HTM[6111]="*“Nayidaṃ sithilamārabbha,**“Not by being slack,*";
P_HTM[6112]="*nayidaṃ appena thāmasā;**or with little strength*";
P_HTM[6113]="*Nibbānaṃ adhigantabbaṃ,**is extinguishment realized,*";
P_HTM[6114]="*sabbadukkhappamocanaṃ.**the freedom from all suffering.*";
P_HTM[6115]="*Ayañca daharo bhikkhu,**This young monk,*";
P_HTM[6116]="*ayamuttamapuriso;**this best of men,*";
P_HTM[6117]="*Dhāreti antimaṃ dehaṃ,**carries his final body,*";
P_HTM[6118]="*jetvā māraṃ savāhinin”ti.**having vanquished Māra and his mount.”*";
P_HTM[6119]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6120]="*5. Sujātasuttaṃ**With Sujāta*";
P_HTM[6121]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6122]="*Atha kho āyasmā sujāto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami.**Then Venerable Sujāta went to see the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6123]="*Addasā kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ sujātaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**The Buddha saw him coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[6124]="*Disvāna bhikkhū āmantesi:**and addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[6125]="*“ubhayenevāyaṃ, bhikkhave, kulaputto sobhati—**“This gentleman is beautiful in both ways.*";
P_HTM[6126]="*yañca abhirūpo dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgato, yassa catthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti tadanuttaraṃ brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharatī”ti.**He’s attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty. And he has realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. He lives having achieved with his own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.”*";
P_HTM[6127]="*Idamavoca bhagavā … pe …**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[6128]="*satthā:**Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:*";
P_HTM[6129]="*“Sobhati vatāyaṃ bhikkhu,**“This mendicant is truly beautiful.*";
P_HTM[6130]="*ujubhūtena cetasā;**His heart is upright,*";
P_HTM[6131]="*Vippayutto visaṃyutto,**he’s unfettered, detached,*";
P_HTM[6132]="*anupādāya nibbuto;**extinguished by not grasping.*";
P_HTM[6133]="*Dhāreti antimaṃ dehaṃ,**He carries his final body,*";
P_HTM[6134]="*jetvā māraṃ savāhinin”ti.**having vanquished Māra and his mount.”*";
P_HTM[6135]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6136]="*6. Lakuṇḍakabhaddiyasuttaṃ**With Lakuṇṭaka Bhaddiya*";
P_HTM[6137]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6138]="*Atha kho āyasmā lakuṇḍakabhaddiyo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami.**Then Venerable Lakuṇṭaka Bhaddiya went to see the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6139]="*Addasā kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ lakuṇḍakabhaddiyaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**The Buddha saw him coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[6140]="*Disvāna bhikkhū āmantesi:**and addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[6141]="*“passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, etaṃ bhikkhuṃ āgacchantaṃ dubbaṇṇaṃ duddasikaṃ okoṭimakaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ paribhūtarūpan”ti?**“Mendicants, do you you see this monk coming—ugly, unsightly, deformed, and despised by the mendicants?”*";
P_HTM[6142]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6143]="*“Eso kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu mahiddhiko mahānubhāvo, na ca sā samāpatti sulabharūpā yā tena bhikkhunā asamāpannapubbā.**“That mendicant is very mighty and powerful. It’s not easy to find an attainment that he has not already attained.*";
P_HTM[6144]="*Yassa catthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharatī”ti.**And he has realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. He lives having achieved with his own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.”*";
P_HTM[6145]="*Idamavoca bhagavā … pe …**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[6146]="*satthā:**Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:*";
P_HTM[6147]="*“Haṃsā koñcā mayūrā ca,**“Geese, herons, and peacocks,*";
P_HTM[6148]="*hatthayo pasadā migā;**elephants and spotted deer—*";
P_HTM[6149]="*Sabbe sīhassa bhāyanti,**though their bodies are not equal,*";
P_HTM[6150]="*natthi kāyasmiṃ tulyatā.**they all fear the lion.*";
P_HTM[6151]="*Evameva manussesu,**So it is for humans—*";
P_HTM[6152]="*daharo cepi paññavā;**if a little person is wise,*";
P_HTM[6153]="*So hi tattha mahā hoti,**they’re the truly great one,*";
P_HTM[6154]="*neva bālo sarīravā”ti.**not the fool with a good body.”*";
P_HTM[6155]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6156]="*7. Visākhasuttaṃ**With Visākha, Pañcāli’s Son*";
P_HTM[6157]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[6158]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof.*";
P_HTM[6159]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā visākho pañcālaputto upaṭṭhānasālāyaṃ bhikkhū dhammiyā kathāya sandasseti samādapeti samuttejeti sampahaṃseti, poriyā vācāya vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā pariyāpannāya anissitāya.**Now at that time Venerable Visākha, Pañcāli’s son, was educating, encouraging, firing up, and inspiring the mendicants in the assembly hall with a Dhamma talk. His words were polished, clear, articulate, expressing the meaning, comprehensive, and independent.*";
P_HTM[6160]="*Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena upaṭṭhānasālā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha came out of retreat and went to the assembly hall. He sat down on the seat spread out,*";
P_HTM[6161]="*Nisajja kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**and addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[6162]="*“ko nu kho, bhikkhave, upaṭṭhānasālāyaṃ bhikkhū dhammiyā kathāya sandasseti samādapeti samuttejeti sampahaṃseti poriyā vācāya vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā pariyāpannāya anissitāyā”ti?**“Mendicants, who was educating, encouraging, firing up, and inspiring the mendicants in the assembly hall with a Dhamma talk?”*";
P_HTM[6163]="*“Āyasmā, bhante, visākho pañcālaputto upaṭṭhānasālāyaṃ bhikkhū dhammiyā kathāya sandasseti samādapeti samuttejeti sampahaṃseti, poriyā vācāya vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā pariyāpannāya anissitāyā”ti.**“Sir, it was Venerable Visākha, Pañcāli’s son.”*";
P_HTM[6164]="*Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ visākhaṃ pañcālaputtaṃ āmantesi:**Then the Buddha said to Visākha:*";
P_HTM[6165]="*“sādhu sādhu, visākha,**“Good, good, Visākha!*";
P_HTM[6166]="*sādhu kho tvaṃ, visākha, bhikkhū dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi … pe … atthassa viññāpaniyā pariyāpannāya anissitāyā”ti.**It’s good that you educate, encourage, fire up, and inspire the mendicants in the assembly hall with a Dhamma talk, with words that are polished, clear, articulate, expressing the meaning, comprehensive, and independent.”*";
P_HTM[6167]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[6168]="*Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:**Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:*";
P_HTM[6169]="*“Nābhāsamānaṃ jānanti,**“Though an astute person is mixed up with fools,*";
P_HTM[6170]="*missaṃ bālehi paṇḍitaṃ;**they don’t know unless he speaks.*";
P_HTM[6171]="*Bhāsamānañca jānanti,**But when he speaks they know,*";
P_HTM[6172]="*desentaṃ amataṃ padaṃ.**he’s teaching the deathless state.*";
P_HTM[6173]="*Bhāsaye jotaye dhammaṃ,**He should speak and illustrate the teaching,*";
P_HTM[6174]="*paggaṇhe isinaṃ dhajaṃ;**holding up the banner of the hermits.*";
P_HTM[6175]="*Subhāsitadhajā isayo,**Words well spoken are the hermits’ banner,*";
P_HTM[6176]="*dhammo hi isinaṃ dhajo”ti.**for the teaching is the banner of the hermits.”*";
P_HTM[6177]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6178]="*8. Nandasuttaṃ**With Nanda*";
P_HTM[6179]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6180]="*Atha kho āyasmā nando bhagavato mātucchāputto ākoṭitapaccākoṭitāni cīvarāni pārupitvā akkhīni añjetvā acchaṃ pattaṃ gahetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ nandaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then Venerable Nanda—the Buddha’s cousin on his mother’s side—dressed in nicely pressed and ironed robes, applied eyeshadow, and took a polished black bowl. He went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[6181]="*“na kho te taṃ, nanda, patirūpaṃ kulaputtassa saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitassa, yaṃ tvaṃ ākoṭitapaccākoṭitāni cīvarāni pārupeyyāsi, akkhīni ca añjeyyāsi, acchañca pattaṃ dhāreyyāsi.**“Nanda, as a gentleman who has gone forth in faith from the lay life to homelessness, it’s not appropriate for you to dress in nicely pressed and ironed robes, apply eyeshadow, and carry a polished black bowl.*";
P_HTM[6182]="*Etaṃ kho te, nanda, patirūpaṃ kulaputtassa saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitassa, yaṃ tvaṃ āraññiko ca assasi, piṇḍapātiko ca paṃsukūliko ca kāmesu ca anapekkho vihareyyāsī”ti.**It’s appropriate for you to stay in the wilderness, eat only alms-food, wear rag robes, and live without concern for sensual pleasures.”*";
P_HTM[6183]="*Idamavoca bhagavā … pe …**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[6184]="*satthā:**Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:*";
P_HTM[6185]="*“Kadāhaṃ nandaṃ passeyyaṃ,**“When will I see Nanda*";
P_HTM[6186]="*āraññaṃ paṃsukūlikaṃ;**in the wilderness, wearing rag robes,*";
P_HTM[6187]="*Aññātuñchena yāpentaṃ,**feeding on scraps offered by strangers,*";
P_HTM[6188]="*kāmesu anapekkhinan”ti.**unconcerned for sensual pleasures?”*";
P_HTM[6189]="*Atha kho āyasmā nando aparena samayena āraññiko ca piṇḍapātiko ca paṃsukūliko ca kāmesu ca anapekkho vihāsīti.**Then some time later Venerable Nanda stayed in the wilderness, ate only alms-food, wore rag robes, and lived without concern for sensual pleasures.*";
P_HTM[6190]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6191]="*9. Tissasuttaṃ**With Tissa*";
P_HTM[6192]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6193]="*Atha kho āyasmā tisso bhagavato pitucchāputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi dukkhī dummano assūni pavattayamāno. Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ tissaṃ etadavoca:**Then Venerable Tissa—the Buddha’s cousin on his father’s side—went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. He was miserable and sad, with tears flowing. Then the Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[6194]="*“kiṃ nu kho tvaṃ, tissa, ekamantaṃ nisinno dukkhī dummano assūni pavattayamāno”ti?**“Tissa, why are you sitting there so miserable and sad, with tears flowing?”*";
P_HTM[6195]="*“Tathā hi pana maṃ, bhante, bhikkhū samantā vācāyasannitodakena sañjambharimakaṃsū”ti.**“Sir, it’s because the mendicants on all sides provoke me with barbed words.”*";
P_HTM[6196]="*“Tathāhi pana tvaṃ, tissa, vattā no ca vacanakkhamo;**“That’s because you admonish others, but don’t accept admonition yourself.*";
P_HTM[6197]="*na kho te taṃ, tissa, patirūpaṃ kulaputtassa saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitassa, yaṃ tvaṃ vattā no ca vacanakkhamo.**As a gentleman who has gone forth in faith from the lay life to homelessness, it’s not appropriate for you to admonish others without accepting admonition yourself.*";
P_HTM[6198]="*Etaṃ kho te, tissa, patirūpaṃ kulaputtassa saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitassa:**It’s appropriate for you to*";
P_HTM[6199]="*‘yaṃ tvaṃ vattā ca assa vacanakkhamo cā’”ti.**admonish others and accept admonition yourself.”*";
P_HTM[6200]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[6201]="*Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:**Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:*";
P_HTM[6202]="*“Kiṃ nu kujjhasi mā kujjhi,**“Why are you angry? Don’t be angry!*";
P_HTM[6203]="*Akkodho tissa te varaṃ;**It’s better to not be angry, Tissa.*";
P_HTM[6204]="*Kodhamānamakkhavinayatthañhi,**For this spiritual life is lived*";
P_HTM[6205]="*Tissa brahmacariyaṃ vussatī”ti.**in order to remove anger, conceit, and denigration.”*";
P_HTM[6206]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6207]="*10. Theranāmakasuttaṃ**A Mendicant Named Senior*";
P_HTM[6208]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[6209]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu theranāmako ekavihārī ceva hoti ekavihārassa ca vaṇṇavādī.**Now at that time there was a certain mendicant named Senior. He lived alone and praised living alone.*";
P_HTM[6210]="*So eko gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pavisati eko paṭikkamati eko raho nisīdati eko caṅkamaṃ adhiṭṭhāti.**He entered the village for alms alone, returned alone, sat in private alone, and concentrated on walking meditation alone.*";
P_HTM[6211]="*Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then several mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6212]="*“idha, bhante, aññataro bhikkhu theranāmako ekavihārī ekavihārassa ca vaṇṇavādī”ti.**“Sir, there’s a certain mendicant named Senior who lives alone and praises living alone.”*";
P_HTM[6213]="*Atha kho bhagavā aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ āmantesi:**So the Buddha said to a certain monk,*";
P_HTM[6214]="*“ehi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, mama vacanena theraṃ bhikkhuṃ āmantehi:**“Please, monk, in my name tell the mendicant Senior that*";
P_HTM[6215]="*‘satthā taṃ, āvuso thera, āmantetī’”ti.**the teacher summons him.”*";
P_HTM[6216]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu bhagavato paṭissutvā yenāyasmā thero tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ theraṃ etadavoca:**“Yes, sir,” that monk replied. He went to Venerable Senior and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6217]="*“satthā taṃ, āvuso thera, āmantetī”ti.**“Reverend Senior, the teacher summons you.”*";
P_HTM[6218]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā thero tassa bhikkhuno paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ theraṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**“Yes, reverend,” that monk replied. He went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[6219]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, thera, ekavihārī ekavihārassa ca vaṇṇavādī”ti?**“Is it really true, Senior, that you live alone and praise living alone?”*";
P_HTM[6220]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6221]="*“Yathā kathaṃ pana tvaṃ, thera, ekavihārī ekavihārassa ca vaṇṇavādī”ti?**“But in what way do you live alone and praise living alone?”*";
P_HTM[6222]="*“Idhāhaṃ, bhante, eko gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pavisāmi eko paṭikkamāmi eko raho nisīdāmi eko caṅkamaṃ adhiṭṭhāmi.**“Well, sir, I enter the village for alms alone, return alone, sit in private alone, and concentrate on walking meditation alone.*";
P_HTM[6223]="*Evaṃ khvāhaṃ, bhante, ekavihārī ekavihārassa ca vaṇṇavādī”ti.**That’s how I live alone and praise living alone.”*";
P_HTM[6224]="*“Attheso, thera, ekavihāro neso natthīti vadāmi.**“That is a kind of living alone, I don’t deny it.*";
P_HTM[6225]="*Api ca, thera, yathā ekavihāro vitthārena paripuṇṇo hoti**But as to how living alone is fulfilled in detail,*";
P_HTM[6226]="*taṃ suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti.**listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[6227]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho … pe ….**“Yes, sir,” he replied.*";
P_HTM[6228]="*“Kathañca, thera, ekavihāro vitthārena paripuṇṇo hoti.**“And how, Senior, is living alone fulfilled in detail?*";
P_HTM[6229]="*Idha, thera, yaṃ atītaṃ taṃ pahīnaṃ, yaṃ anāgataṃ taṃ paṭinissaṭṭhaṃ, paccuppannesu ca attabhāvapaṭilābhesu chandarāgo suppaṭivinīto.**It’s when what’s in the past is given up, what’s in the future is relinquished, and desire and greed for present incarnations is eliminated.*";
P_HTM[6230]="*Evaṃ kho, thera, ekavihāro vitthārena paripuṇṇo hotī”ti.**That’s how living alone is fulfilled in detail.”*";
P_HTM[6231]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[6232]="*Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:**Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:*";
P_HTM[6233]="*“Sabbābhibhuṃ sabbaviduṃ sumedhaṃ,**“The sage, champion, knower of all,*";
P_HTM[6234]="*Sabbesu dhammesu anūpalittaṃ;**is unsullied in the midst of all things.*";
P_HTM[6235]="*Sabbañjahaṃ taṇhākkhaye vimuttaṃ,**He’s given up all, freed in the ending of craving:*";
P_HTM[6236]="*Tamahaṃ naraṃ ekavihārīti brūmī”ti.**I declare that man to be one who lives alone.”*";
P_HTM[6237]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6238]="*11. Mahākappinasuttaṃ**With Mahākappina*";
P_HTM[6239]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6240]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākappino yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami.**Then Venerable Mahākappina went to see the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6241]="*Addasā kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ mahākappinaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**The Buddha saw him coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[6242]="*Disvāna bhikkhū āmantesi:**and addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[6243]="*“passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, etaṃ bhikkhuṃ āgacchantaṃ odātakaṃ tanukaṃ tuṅganāsikan”ti?**“Mendicants, do you you see that monk coming—white, thin, with a pointy nose?”*";
P_HTM[6244]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6245]="*“Eso kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu mahiddhiko mahānubhāvo.**“That mendicant is very mighty and powerful. It’s not easy to find an attainment that he has not already attained.*";
P_HTM[6246]="*Na ca sā samāpatti sulabharūpā yā tena bhikkhunā asamāpannapubbā.* **";
P_HTM[6247]="*Yassa catthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti tadanuttaraṃ brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharatī”ti.**And he has realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. He lives having achieved with his own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.”*";
P_HTM[6248]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[6249]="*Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:**Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:*";
P_HTM[6250]="*“Khattiyo seṭṭho janetasmiṃ,**“The aristocrat is best of those people*";
P_HTM[6251]="*ye gottapaṭisārino;**who take clan as the standard.*";
P_HTM[6252]="*Vijjācaraṇasampanno,**But one accomplished in knowledge and conduct*";
P_HTM[6253]="*so seṭṭho devamānuse.**is best of gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[6254]="*Divā tapati ādicco,**The sun shines by day,*";
P_HTM[6255]="*rattimābhāti candimā;**the moon glows at night,*";
P_HTM[6256]="*Sannaddho khattiyo tapati,**the aristocrat shines in armor,*";
P_HTM[6257]="*jhāyī tapati brāhmaṇo;**and the brahmin shines in absorption.*";
P_HTM[6258]="*Atha sabbamahorattiṃ,**But all day and all night,*";
P_HTM[6259]="*buddho tapati tejasā”ti.**the Buddha shines with glory.”*";
P_HTM[6260]="*Ekādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6261]="*12. Sahāyakasuttaṃ**Companions*";
P_HTM[6262]="*Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[6263]="*Atha kho dve bhikkhū sahāyakā āyasmato mahākappinassa saddhivihārino yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu.**Then two mendicants who were companions, pupils of Venerable Mahākappina, went to see the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6264]="*Addasā kho bhagavā te bhikkhū dūratova āgacchante.**The Buddha saw them coming off in the distance,*";
P_HTM[6265]="*Disvāna bhikkhū āmantesi:**and addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[6266]="*“passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, ete bhikkhū sahāyake āgacchante kappinassa saddhivihārino”ti?**“Mendicants, do you you see those monks coming who are companions, pupils of Venerable Mahākappina?”*";
P_HTM[6267]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[6268]="*“Ete kho te bhikkhū mahiddhikā mahānubhāvā.**“Those mendicants are very mighty and powerful. It’s not easy to find an attainment that they have not already attained.*";
P_HTM[6269]="*Na ca sā samāpatti sulabharūpā, yā tehi bhikkhūhi asamāpannapubbā.* **";
P_HTM[6270]="*Yassa catthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti tadanuttaraṃ brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharantī”ti.**And they’ve realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. They live having achieved with their own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.”*";
P_HTM[6271]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[6272]="*Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:**Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:*";
P_HTM[6273]="*“Sahāyāvatime bhikkhū,**“These companion mendicants*";
P_HTM[6274]="*cirarattaṃ sametikā;**have been together for a long time.*";
P_HTM[6275]="*Sameti nesaṃ saddhammo,**The true teaching has brought them together,*";
P_HTM[6276]="*dhamme buddhappavedite.**the teaching proclaimed by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6277]="*Suvinītā kappinena,**They’ve been well trained by Kappina*";
P_HTM[6278]="*dhamme ariyappavedite;**in the teaching proclaimed by the noble one.*";
P_HTM[6279]="*Dhārenti antimaṃ dehaṃ,**They bear their final body,*";
P_HTM[6280]="*jetvā māraṃ savāhinin”ti.**having vanquished Māra and his mount.”*";
P_HTM[6281]="*Dvādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[6282]="*Bhikkhuvaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[6283]="*Kolito upatisso ca,* **";
P_HTM[6284]="*ghaṭo cāpi pavuccati;* **";
P_HTM[6285]="*Navo sujāto bhaddi ca,* **";
P_HTM[6286]="*visākho nando tisso ca;* **";
P_HTM[6287]="*Theranāmo ca kappino,* **";
P_HTM[6288]="*sahāyena ca dvādasāti.* **";
P_HTM[6289]="*Bhikkhusaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ.**The Linked Discourses on monks are complete.*";
P_HTM[6290]="*Nidānavaggo dutiyo.* **";
P_HTM[6291]="*Nidānābhisamayadhātu,* **";
P_HTM[6292]="*anamataggena kassapaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[6293]="*Sakkārarāhulalakkhaṇo,* **";
P_HTM[6294]="*opammabhikkhunā vaggo.* **";
P_HTM[6295]="*Dutiyo tena pavuccatīti.* **";
P_HTM[6296]="*Nidānavaggasaṃyuttapāḷi niṭṭhitā.**The Book of Causality is finished.*";
